<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="ROM" stage="Final" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="John Wimbish" created="2009-10-05 05:48:27Z" when="2009-10-05 05:48:27Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Lazarus Aplugi; keyboarded by Helena Aplugi; team revision October 2008; with advisor Jan 2009 (Kupang-S); Consultant Check at UBB office in Kupang, 15-20 July 2009, Consultant: Catherine Rountree (in Florida) Advisor: Chuck Grimes (running the check by proxy); Team Coordinator: Michael Sina (Kupang-based) Team present: Lazarus Aplugi (main drafter); Lazarus Lusi (Dhao-based); Helena Aplugi (keyboard); [Rev. Dr. Ayub Ranoh Th.D. had on-going responsibilities on Alor island]</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Roma</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Sasuri Paulus<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">hia dhèu parcaya ètu kota<bt>to the believers in the city of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Roma<bt>Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii maho'o<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Sasuri ne nèti ja'a, Paulus. Ama Lamatua pili nare le ja'a ho j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Yesus Kristus. Ka Na ded'e ja'a j'aj'i ana pua-paleha Kristus, ho laku lole Lii Lolo Be'a Na dènge dhèu ètu mia-mia.<bt>This letter is from me, Paulus. God has chosen me to be Yesus Kristus' *apostle (commissioned servant) (doublet). And He appointed me to become Kristus' servant/slave (person habitually ordered around) (doublet) to go tell His *Good News to people people all over the place. [EXEG: the function of ‘Kristus’ as per TBT article is spelled out in following verses, so doesn't need to be explicated here. It would skew the focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus ne'e, nuka Dhèu dhu Lamatua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Kristus ne'e, nuka Dhèu dhu Lamatua hag'e nare sèna ka hia mai madhutu lii pajaji Na. ... Te, Nèngu ka dhu ded'e ja'a ho pakako sasab'a èèna</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doulos: slave, LXX servant of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">doulos: slave, LXX servant of the Lord. habitual servant, personal retainer like Hawaiian &amp; Rotinese kings had (relationship, not job) apóstolos: special messenger<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called to be an apostle, set apart for the gospel of God,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2-3" />Uru èèna, Ama Lamatua dhu ator tèke le, ho dhèu rèti lii padhai Na suri j'ara-j'ara nèti Lii Lolo Be'a èèna ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na. Te, ètu d'ara Sasuri ne, Lamatua pajaji neo hia mai Ana Na Yesus, ho j'aj'i dhèu rai-haha. De limuri ne, lii moa Na èèna j'aj'i le, lula Yesus dhu mai le nèti ana-èpu dhèu aae Daud.<bt>Long ago, God had arranged ahead.of.time for His spokespersons (*prophets) to write about that Good News in His Clean/Holy (doublet) Writings. Cuz (elaboration) in that aforementioned Writing, So (consequently) now, His promise happened/was fulfilled, because Yesus has come as king Daud's descendant (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perì: topic of the Good News"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">perì: topic of the Good News katà sárka: as far as being human is concerned, on the human side<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>NRSV: which he promised beforehand through his prophets in the holy scriptures, the gospel concerning his Son, who was descended from David according to the flesh</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te ngaa re èci hari, Ama Lamatua pad'elo tadha, peka na, Yesus Kristus èèna, Ana Nèngu kahèi. Te Roh Yesus èèna, mola-mèci tare'a-re'a, sama sèmi Ama Lamatua. Aa Lamatua pake koasa Na, sèna ka pamamuri hari Yesus nèti mamadhe Na. Nèti èèna ka, èdhi te'a, na, Ana Ama Lamatua èèna, nuka Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>But on the other side/hand, God showed sign/evidence that, Yesus Kristus, was also His Child/Offspring. Cuz (elaboration) Yesus' Spirit is truly clean/holy/pure (doublet), just like God. And God2 [short form] also used His power/authority to cause Yesus to live again from His death. Because of that, we know that God's Child is our-inc Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus. [EXEG: SSA] [NOTE: Roh here is grammatically Jesus' spirit not the H.S. Indo Christian conventions require it to be capitalised. But then this makes the common understanding lean towards it being the H.S. Any mention of spirit relating to Jesus is going to default to H.S.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà pneuma hagiosúnees: not used for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">katà pneuma hagiosúnees: not used for the Holy Spirit in the New Testament; contrasts with katà sárka NRSV: and was declared to be Son of God with power according to the spirit of holiness by resurrection from the dead, Jesus Christ our Lord,<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Yesus pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ja'a, te Na pili nare le ja'a j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Na, ho lole lii aj'a-nori Na buli mia-mia. Dad'èi Na, dhèu dhu Yahudi boe parcaya Ne kahèi, aa mamuri madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua. Ja'a neo kahèi, sèna ka dhèu nèti suku aa'i-aa'i lèka Kristus, aa mamuri madhutu dad'èi Na.<bt>Yesus showed his good insides (*grace/goodness/kindness/ generosity) to me, cuz (elaboration) He chose me to be His *apostle to tell His message/teachings (doublet) all over the place. His desire is that non Yahudi people also believe in Him, and live according to God's will. I also want people from all ethnic.groups to believe2 in Kristus and live according to His will. [EXEG: SSA, HCE. On switch from ‘we’ to ‘I’, SSA, Moo, and others consider this to be what is called an ‘epistolary “we”’ or an ‘editorial “we”’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chárin: privilege hypèr tò onómatos autou:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">chárin: privilege hypèr tò onómatos autou: goes with the whole sentence, the reason why Paul and his friends are motivated is that they know what sort of person (onómatos) Jesus is.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: through whom we have received grace and apostleship to bring about the obedience of faith among all the Gentiles for the sake of his name,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge miu ètu kota Roma. Miu j'aj'i nèti suku ae-ae nèti mia-mia, Yesus Kristus dhu hag'e nare le miu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mai ka! Mai j'aj'i dhèu unu Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also with you-pl in Roma city. You came/originate from many ethnic.groups in many places. Yesus Kristus has chosen/picked out (from a group) you, saying, &lt;&lt;Come on! Come and become My person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: including yourselves who are called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: including yourselves who are called to belong to Jesus Christ,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Nèti èèna ka, ja'a pa'adhu sasuri ne hia miu ètu Roma, dènge pasanèd'e, peka na, Ama Lamatua sue miu. Nèngu manèngi kahèi ho miu j'aj'i dhèu unu Na dhu mamuri mola-mèci.<bt>That is why I am sending this letter to you in Roma, and reminding [you], that, God loves you. He also requests that you become His people who live holy/cleanly. [Message]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ja'a sabaj'a sèna ka Ama èdhi, Ama Lamatua, dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, pad'elo d'ara hua iia Ra, aa hia miu mamuri dènge mera-milu.<bt>I pray that God2, our-inc Father, and Yesus Kristus, our Head/Leader, show Their good insides (*grace), and enable you to live in peace (external &amp; relational). [EXEG: Morris' and others comments that /eirene/ is restricted in this context to inner peace have no support from the immediate context, from standard Gk lexicons (e.g. BAGD, LN, etc.), nor from the meaning of Heb. /shalom/ with which they acknowledge this greeting is in parallel. The restriction seems to be someone's western psychological fabrication that gets repeated, rather than one than has a solid basis. See Chuck's PPT word study on /eirene/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To all God's beloved in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: To all God's beloved in Rome, who are called to be saints: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus sabaj'a hia angalai na sèra<bt>Paulus prays for his friends</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ja'a bhoke sasuri ja'a ne, dènge manèngi makasi ae-ae mi Ama Lamatua, lula Yesus Kristus sab'a ètu d'ara miu. Ja'a manèngi makasi kahèi, lula dhèu dhu pea ètu rae-rae d'ara paredha Roma, ra palolo lula-nèti parcaya miu mi Yesus.<bt>I open this letter of mine by thanking God hugely, because Yesus Kristus is working in your livers/hearts. I also say thank you, because people who live in all the Roma government's areas, are talking about your belief/faith in Yesus. [EXEG: Gk. “throughout” the world is hyperbole. KM clarifies this as meaning “throughout the Roman world/empire”; ALT vague hyperbole “people everywhere” is also acceptable, but check that it is taken as hyperbole, not literally (e.g. is this saying that in Paul's time, their faith had been proclaimed in Semau and Ndao?)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Prooton: first, but there isn't any"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Prooton: first, but there isn't any "second"; take it as "first of all" or "let me begin" NRSV: First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because your faith is proclaimed throughout the world.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ja'a loe boe sabaj'a hia miu. Tare'a! Lamatua mesa Na ne'a, na, ngaa dhu ja'a padhai ne, lèke. Nèngu ne'a kahèi, na, ja'a ne sab'a dènge d'ara kateme ho lole dènge dhèu Lii Lolo Be'a nèti Ana Na.<bt>I pray without stopping for you-pl. That's true! God2 himself knows that, what I say here, is true2. He also knows that I work with full enthusiasm/wholeheartedly, to tell people about His Child's Good Story/News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en tooi pneúmatí mou: Gk idiom--Paul's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">en tooi pneúmatí mou: Gk idiom--Paul's inner being, his total being, without holding back NRSV: For God, whom I serve with my spirit by announcing the gospel of his Son, is my witness that without ceasing I remember you always in my prayers,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Lod'o-lod'o ja'a manèngi-mangaj'i, ja'a peka sèmi ne'e ka: &lt;&lt;Lamatua, ja'a mesa ku ke'a boe j'ara na tasamia. Te ngaa, ladhe madhutu dad'èi Lamatua, na, bhoke la j'ara, sèna ka ja'a bisa laku pangad'o dènge angalai ja'a sèra ètu Roma.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every time I pray, I request like.this: &lt;&lt;God2, I myself don't know how it can be/happen. But in accord with God2's (=your) will, then, open the path/way so I can go visit my friends in Roma.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poos: somehow euodootheésomai: I will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">poos: somehow euodootheésomai: I will be helped on my way there<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>NRSV: asking that by God's will I may somehow at last succeed in coming to you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ja'a sabaj'a sèmi èèna, te ja'a neo titu kèna kèdhi miu, sèna ka ja'a bisa bagi hia miu koasa nèti Roh Lamatua, ho hud'i laa miu j'aj'i dhèu unu Lamatua dhu taha pa'èra-èra.<bt>I pray like that, cuz (elaboration) I really want to see you-pl, so that I can give/divide up among you power/authority from God2's Spirit, so that you become God2's people who endure strongly</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stjrichthjnai: established, stronger in the sense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">stjrichthjnai: established, stronger in the sense of more firm and unchanging in attitude or belief . NRSV: For I am longing to see you so that I may share with you some spiritual gift to strengthen [establish] you-<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Madhutu a'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e ka: ladhe ja'a j'aj'i dhiu pea dènge miu, ja'a neo pa'èra d'ara miu, ho sèna ka parcaya miu asa èra. Aa ja'a neo kahèi ho miu pa'èra d'ara ja'a.<bt>My intent/opinion is like this: if it works out for me to come by and stay with you-pl, I want to strengthen your insides (=encourage), so that your faith can be increasingly stronger. And I want for you-pl also to strengthen my insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: or rather so that we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: or rather so that we may be mutually encouraged by each other's faith, both yours and mine.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />A'ari pasue aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a d'èi ladhe miu me'a, na, ja'a neo ae le ho dhiu pangad'o dènge miu ètu Roma. Te ngaa toke sange ne'e, dhodhoka tao nelu di. De ladhe ja'a j'aj'i dhiu, ja'a sanao sèna ka abhu dhèu ae era dhu lèka èra Kristus, sama sèmi dhu ja'a abhu ètu era-era leo. Ladhe sèmi èèna, na, rui-j'aj'èra ja'a abhu hua-hela dhu be'a.<bt>Beloved siblings! I want you-pl to know, that, already many times my intention was to come visit you in Roma. But until now it has just been a plan. So (consequently), if/when I do manage to come, I hope there will be many people who still believe2 strongly in Kristus, the same as I encounter in other places. In that way, my efforts (idiom: bone suffering) will have good results/yield/success/harvest. [EXEG: what is the hasil bae referring to? CEV says more converts; SSA says broader meaning.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao nelu di = hanya rencana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tao nelu di = hanya rencana sa ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphoí: fellow believers, the way Christians"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">adelphoí: fellow believers, the way Christians talk to each other karpòn: fruit, results, outcome; win converts, have something tangible happen<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>NRSV: I want you to know, brothers and sisters, that I have often intended to come to you (but thus far have been prevented), in order that I may reap some harvest among you as I have among the rest of the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 19:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14-15" />Masi ka, tasamia èèna ka, ja'a hud'i lole ku Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i. Mi dhèu dhu pake lii Yunani do, dhèu dintiu dhu pake lii leo, dhèu kapai do, dhèu haha do, dhèu sakola do, dhèu sakola boe. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a pa'èra neo dhiu sa Roma, sèna ka paraga dènge miu.<bt>No matter what, I must tell God2's Good News to all people. Whether to people who speak Greek or, dintiu (without major/civilised religion, follow traditional beliefs) who use other languages, big/important people or, little/no social status people or, schooled/learned people, or non schooled people. That's why I am ready to go to Roma to meet with you-pl. [EXEG: Gk Greeks and barbarians evokes several aspects, so we've explicated more than one.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dintiu = kafir ~ dinitiu (lama)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dintiu = kafir ~ dinitiu (lama)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Helleesín: Greeks = civilized and cultured"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Helleesín: Greeks = civilized and cultured vs. savage sophois: educated vs. ignorant<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>opheilétees: under obligation próthymon: eager, really want to help, enthusiastic, psyched<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>NRSV: I am a debtor both to Greeks and to barbarians, both to the wise and to the foolish -hence my eagerness to proclaim the gospel to you also who are in Rome</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua dènge koasa ho hia mamuri mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i<bt>The Good News of God2's, has power/authority to save all people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ja'a makae boe ciki sa, dènge Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua Yesus. Te ladhe abhu dhèu dhu parcaya Ama Lamatua, Lii Lolo Be'a ne dènge koasa nèti Lamatua, ho patabuli dhèu ne'e nèti koasa sasala-sasigo na. Dhèu Yahudi ka dhu re'a uuru j'ara ne'e ne, heka dhèu suku leo sèra kèna.<bt>I am not even a bit embarassed/ashamed about the Lord Yesus' Good News. Cuz (elaboration) if/when there is a person who believes in God, that Good News has power/authority from Him, to *save that person from his *wrongs (doublet). The Yahudi people got to know this matter first, and then other ethnic.groups also.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) (Literal: word-for-word): aad'o hia makae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">(al) (Literal: word-for-word): aad'o hia makae ja'a nèti lii lolo be'a (,) a'èra hia Lamatua nuka mi mamuri mi aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya (,) mi Yahudi bera-bera ka'èci dènge mi Yunani</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaischýnomai: feel shame because I trusted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">epaischýnomai: feel shame because I trusted something and it let me down prooton: probably time, not importance<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>NRSV: For I am not ashamed of the gospel; it is the power of God for salvation to everyone who has faith, to the Jew first and also to the Greek.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 8:38</note><v n="17" />Lii Lolo Be'a ne pad'elo kahèi j'ara Lamatua ho pamola dhèu nèti sasala ra. Aa'i-aa'i sèra sa bisa j'aj'i, sad'i dhèu parcaya Ne. Te dhu suri le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, peka na,<bt>That Good News also shows God2's way for straightening out/restoring people from their wrongs. It all is able to happen/come into being, as long as people believe in Him. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings, that, [NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dhèu hud'i parcaya uuru ku Ama Lamatua,<bt>&lt;&lt;People must first believe in God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">heka bisa pabe'a dènge Nèngu kèna.<bt>only.then can they be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ladhe ra mamuri dènge parcaya Ne,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when they live believing in Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">heka abhu mamuri dhu lèke kèna.&gt;&gt;<bt>only.then can they obtain/experience true life/can truly live.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dikaiosýnee: God's activity in putting people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">dikaiosýnee: God's activity in putting people in the right. Not God's character. No article. (CHECK PARALLELS FROM HERE.) NRSV: For in it the righteousness of God is revealed through faith for faith; as it is written, “The one who is righteous will live by faith.”<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 2:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua nasa dènge dhèu dhu ro'o boe tadhe Ne<bt>God2 is angry with people who don't want to know/acknowledge Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua peka le, na, abhu dhèu dhu pusi-pahae boe Nèngu. Aa abhu dhu ad'u-ue rupa-rupa j'ara bhelu-katub'a. Te ngaa Lamatua sèmi nare boe tatao rèngu sèra. Lula ètu d'ara iiki rèngu, dhu re'a le, mia ka dhu lèke. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa rèngu loe boe tao j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke boe sèra. Ra kakèj'i dhèu, toke dhèu re'a heka mia ka dhu lèke. Nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua papuru hahuku nèti dedha-liru, sèna ka paj'èra si.<bt>But God has told/made known/explained that, there are people who don't give.a.hoot (doublet) about Him. And there are those who do (doublet) various sorts of evil (doublet) things. But God2 doesn't accept /not put up with/rejects those deeds of theirs. Because in their small insides/consciences, they already know which (of options) is right/true/correct. Even that being the case, nevertheless they do not cease to do various things which are not right/correct/true. They keep trying to cajole/ persuade/ convince people to.point.that those people no longer know which is right/correct/true anymore. That's.why God (will) send down punishment from the sky to punish/ensuffer them. [HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baki hoe - buaya (some people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">baki hoe - buaya (some people on Dhao worshipped crocs)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nèti èèna ka Na neo papuru"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Nèti èèna ka Na neo papuru hahuku nèti dedha liru, sèna ka pajèra si. Dhèu se'e se dhu re'a le mia ka dhu lèke ètu dara rèngu. Te ngaa masi ka sèmi èèna rèngu loe boe nèti j'ara-j'ara karehe. Ra kakèj'i dhèu toke dhèu se, re'a heka mia ka dhu lèke.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asebeian: indifference to God, ungodliness ap'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">asebeian: indifference to God, ungodliness ap' ouranou: from heaven = from God himself (like "instructions from Washington")<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>katechóntoon: suppressing; they don't know the truth because of you. NRSV: For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and wickedness of those who by their wickedness suppress the truth.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19-20" />Dhèu se'e se, abhu boe alasan ho siri iisi ra, lula j'ara-j'ara dhu pahuni boe dhu dhèu bisa re'a mèu nèti Lamatua. Te Ama Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu pad'elo! A'abhu Ja'a sèmi ne'e ka: mulai nèti Na paj'aj'i dedha-liru dènge rai-haha, toke d'ai sange ne'e ne, ladhe dhèu neo re'a mèu nèti ngi'u Lamatua, aa dènge koasa Na dhu dènge boe too-lane èèna, bisa kahèi! Masi ka ladhe tèdhi boe Ama Lamatua, te ngaa dhèu bisa tadhe Ne nèti ngaa-ngaa dhu Na ad'u-ue. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a peka, na, dhèu bhelu sèra abhu boe alasan ho siri iisi ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a ke'a boe ngaa-ngaa nèti Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>These people don't have any reason/excuse/basis (loan) to defend themselves, because things which people can clearly know about God, are not hidden. Cuz (elaboration) God himself is the one who has shown/revealed them! My meaning/intent is like.this: beginning from Him making/creating the sky (doublet) and earth (doublet) until now, if people want to know/understand about God2's self/being, and His unbounded power/authority, of course they can! Even though we cannot actually see God, nevertheless we-inc humans still can know/recognise Him from what He does/makes (doublet). That's why I say that, those evil people don't have any reason/excuse/basis to be able to defend themselves, saying, “I don't know anything about God.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dióti: the reason NRSV: For what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">dióti: the reason NRSV: For what can be known about God is plain to them, because God has shown it to them. Ever since the creation of the world his eternal power and divine nature, invisible though they are, have been understood and seen through the things he has made. So they are without excuse;<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />De masi ka rèngu re'a j'ara-j'ara Lamatua, te ngaa ro'o boe mangaku, na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua èèna, Ama Lamatua èdhi!&gt;&gt; Rèngu se ro'o boe, manèngi makasi mi Lamatua kahèi. Ka ngangee ra j'aj'i kahèlu, toke ra re'a heka ngaa dhu lèke. Rèngu j'aj'i bingu aa padhai lii rupa-rupa dhu kolo-kapua aad'o lula-nèti Ama Lamatua. Aa d'ara ra maroga aatu-aatu.<bt>So (consequently), even though they know about the things/ways of God2, nevertheless they don't want to acknowledge Him, saying, &lt;&lt;That God2/Master, [is] our-inc God!&gt;&gt; They also don't want to give thanks to Him. And their thinking has become tangled/ chaotic/ confused, to.the.point.that they don't understand anything that is right/true/correct anymore. They become confused (loan) and say all sorts of things that have no basis (doublet/idiom: tip-base), about God. And2 their insides became dark (=unenlightened). [NLT - "And they began to think up foolish ideas of what God was like."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahèlu = tangled, menghambat, ke benang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kahèlu = tangled, menghambat, ke benang yang kusut</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padhai lii dhu dènge boe kolo-kapua,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">padhai lii dhu dènge boe kolo-kapua, nèti j'ara-j'ara dhu palèke dènge Lamatua. Te rèngu se re'a boe ngaa-ngaa toke ra malaa-maloha, aa dara ra maroga aatu-aatu.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emataioótheesan: nonsense, foolishness, no value eskotísthee:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">emataioótheesan: nonsense, foolishness, no value eskotísthee: failure to think right about moral issues. Not ignorance<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>asýnetos: stupid, empty headed, intellect without understanding NRSV: for though they knew God, they did not honor him as God or give thanks to him, but they became futile in their thinking, and their senseless minds were darkened.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Epesus 4:17-18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Rèngu èci-èci padedha iisi ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a ke'a mèu madha j'ara ae-ae!&gt;&gt; Masi ka ngangee ra sèmi èèna, te ngaa madhutu mola-mola na, rèngu goa titu kèna.<bt>They each elevate (=praise) themselves, saying, &lt;&lt;I clearly know/understand many things (=wise)!&gt;&gt; Even though they think like that, nevertheless the truth is, they are really stupid. [shows speaker attitude]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sophoì: wise (opposite ends of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">sophoì: wise (opposite ends of the wisdom scale) emoorántheesan: they have turned into fools<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>NRSV: Claiming to be wise, they became fools;</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ka dhèu se pahaha boe iisi ra mi Ama Lamatua dhu kapai risi eele èèna, te rèngu peka na, &lt;&lt;Ji'i pusi boe Lamatua sèmi èèna!&gt;&gt; Te ngaa ra sogo-tagu mi rupa-rupa patung, raropa sèmi dhèu rai-haha, sèmi manu-bhui sa, do sèmi badha leo sèra, toke d'ai patung dhu rupa sèmi mege sa. Dènge ra sogo-tagu sèmi èèna, rèngu tule eele Ama Lamatua dhu mamuri taa-taa, ho ra gati eele dènge mèdha-panyau dhu bisa madhe!<bt>And they don't worship God who is extremely amazing, cuz (elaboration) they say, &lt;&lt;We-exc don't need a God2/Master like that!&gt;&gt; But they traditional.worship (doublet) various statues (loan), patterned after humans, like birds, like other animals, even to being patterned like snakes (category). By traditional worshipping like that, they push.away/reject God who lives forever, to exchange/replace [Him] with things (doublet) that can die! [EXEG: SSA suggests that this is a “downward spiral of idolatry” - it got worse and worse, progressing from humans to animals...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and they exchanged the glory"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: and they exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images resembling a mortal human being or birds or four-footed animals or reptiles.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 4:16-18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Nèti èèna ka, Lamatua soro tèke si, sèna ka ra ad'u-ue madhutu dad'èi rèngu. Na soro tèke si, ho ra tao j'ara bhelu-katub'a rupa-rupa, dhu amo le ètu d'ara rèngu. Toke rèngu se re'a heka makae sa hèi. Hèia dènge ngi'u aae ra, rèngu ad'u-ue madha j'ara kaj'alu rupa-rupa, aa ra tao sèmi èèna kahèi dènge dhèu leo.<bt>That's.why God2 just abandons them (dismissively, let them do whatever--almost a curse word), so that they are allowed to do (doublet) according to their own desires. He allows them to do all sorts of evil (doublet) things which are rooted in their insides. To the point that they no longer know how to be embarrased/ashamed (~they have no sense of shame). Then with their own bodies, they did all.sorts of defilement and did like that also with other people. [HCE] [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful of trying to reduce too much redundancy and wind up undertranslating important points here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paredooken: he lets them be taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">paredooken: he lets them be taken over by their desires NRSV: Therefore God gave them up in the lusts of their hearts to impurity, to the degrading of their bodies among themselves,<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ètu d'ara iiki ra dhu re'a le j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke nèti Ama Lamatua, te ngaa ro'o boe madhutu. Ngangee rèngu dhu moca le, hèia ra pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Be'a risi èdhi tao rupa-rupa. Masi ka pakarehe aa'i-aa'i, ngaa-ngaa tao boe!&gt;&gt; Ra koa-kad'iri mèdha dhu Lamatua paj'aj'i, te ngaa rèngu pahaha boe iisi mi Lamatua dhu paj'aj'i mèdha se. Ra tao iisi sèmi dhèu dhu mola-mèci, te ngaa dhu mola-mèu lao di!<bt>In their inner insides, they already knew things which were true/correct about God, but they didn't want to go along with that. Their thinking was decayed/eaten away (internally), so they thought, saying, &lt;&lt;It's better, let us-exc just do whatever [negative implications-up to no good]. Even if [we] defile everything, it doesn't matter!&gt;&gt; They worshipped2/prasied (doublet) things which God2 had made/created, but they didn't want to worship1 God2 who made/created those things! They made themselves out to be holy/devout/ pious/religious (doublet), but there was no content/substance! [EXEG: last sentence is high-level summary of exchanging something of substance for an empty lie, which is otherwise lost.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhu mola mèu lao = kosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dhu mola mèu lao = kosong ; moca = loyo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dhu lèke ka, ladhe èdhi dhèu rai-haha ne koa-kio taruu Ama Lamatua! Èèna ka dhu mèci!<bt>What is correct/true/in actual fact, we-inc humans must keep praising (doublet) God continually! Now that's what is appropriate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: because they exchanged the truth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: because they exchanged the truth about God for a lie and worshiped and served the creature rather than the Creator, who is blessed forever! Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Nèti bhabhelu-katub'a rèngu sèra ka, Lamatua soro tèke si, ho rèngu tao karehe sèmi èèna madhutu dad'èi ra. Hèia ra tao rupa-rupa j'ara makae, dhu dènge heka d'ara makae. Bhèni ra, ro'o heka pa'èci dènge mone dhèu èmu ra, te ngaa d'èi tao dhu lèke boe. Te bhèni j'unu tao j'ara makae dènge bhèni.<bt>Because of that evil (doublet) of theirs, God2 allowed/permitted, so that they do difilement like that, according to their desires/passions. So they did all sorts of shameful things [UNS's always link this to sexual things in this prudish Dhao society], and had were shameless [broader behaviour]. Their wives/women didn't like to unite with their husbands anymore, but just liked what isn't right/natural. Cuz (elaboration) females slept doing shameful things (=sexual) with females!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dènge heka dara makae = sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dènge heka dara makae = sonde tau malu lai (idiom) ; baki hoe = buaya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For this reason God gave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For this reason God gave them up to degrading passions. Their women exchanged natural intercourse for unnatural,</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Dhèu mone sèmi èèna kahèi! Ra d'èi heka j'unu pa'èci dènge dhèu èmu ra, te ngaa d'èi j'unu dènge dhèu mone leo! Rèngu se, dhu dènge heka d'ara makae! Nèti èèna ka, pe rèngu dui rare j'aj'èra pamèci dènge tatao rèngu sèra! Te rèngu se dhu sigo eele kaj'èu le, nèti j'ara dhu lèke.<bt>Males were like that too! They didn't like to sleep united with their wives anymore, but they liked to sleep with males! They didn't have even a little bit of shame! That's why they bear a punishment/suffering that is appropriate to their deeds/behaviour! Cuz (elaboration) they had strayed/shifted far from the path that is right/true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sigo = stray, serong ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sigo = stray, serong ;  makae heka dara (old language)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and in the same way"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: and in the same way also the men, giving up natural intercourse with women, were consumed with passion for one another. Men committed shameless acts with men and received in their own persons the due penalty for their error.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ra pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Be'a risi baku patai-patapa dènge Lamatua.&gt;&gt; Nèti èèna ka, Lamatua soro tèke si, sèna ka ra tao madhutu dad'èi ra! De rèngu ngee dhoka dhu karehe di! Ka ra tao j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke boe!<bt>They were thinking, that, &lt;&lt;It's better to not associate (doublet) with God2.&gt;&gt; Because of that, God2 just let them do whatever (dismissively), so that they did according to their own desires! So (consequently), they only thought about things that were ruined/ broken (moral)! And so they did things that were not right/true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="patai-patapa = lekatkan diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">patai-patapa = lekatkan diri</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ton theon echein en epignoosei: acknowledge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">ton theon echein en epignoosei: acknowledge God (BAGD 1.7.1) NRSV: And since they did not see fit to acknowledge God, God gave them up to a debased mind and to things that should not be done.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Mamuri ra pènu dènge rupa-rupa bhabhelu-katub'a. Ka re'a heka tao dhu be'a, te ngaa dhoka dhu bhelu di. Rèngu manga'a. Èci tèke d'ara dènge èci. Èci d'èi boe karisi èci. Èci pamadhe èci. Ra d'èi patao-palaha. Ra kapod'e-kabèli. Ra leko-monya. Ra d'èi padhai-kakoli dhèu.<bt>Their lives became full of all.sorts of evil (doublet). They no longer knew how to do what is good, but only what is evil. They were greedy. They were vengeful with each other. They didn't want each other to be better/more than the other. They murdered each other. They liked to habitually argue (doublet). They lied/deceived (doublet). They like to con (doublet) people. They liked to gossip (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padhai-kakoli = gossip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">padhai-kakoli = gossip</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Èci lab'a èci, èci udhi èci."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Èci lab'a èci, èci udhi èci. Èci dèi boe karisi èci, èci pamadhe èci. Dèi patao-palaha, kapod'e-kabèli, leko-monya, dèi padhai-kakoli dhèu.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éridos: not just fighting, but partisanship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">éridos: not just fighting, but partisanship and factions dólou: deception, trickery<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>NRSV: They were filled with every kind of wickedness, evil, covetousness, malice. Full of envy, murder, strife, deceit, craftiness, they are gossips,</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Rèngu d'èi pa'ele iie kolongara dhèu. Ra palab'a dènge Ama Lamatua. Ra kurang ajar, d'èi pahahe dhèu, d'èi padedha iisi, d'èi tenge j'ara-j'ara karehe, aa d'èi palab'a dènge ina-ama ra.<bt>They liked to ruin other people's names/reputations. They opposed God [Dhao has no unambiguous word for hate]. They act inappropriately/rudely, like to look down on/despise people, like to lift.up=exalt themselves, like to find all.sorts.of rotten ideas/schemes, and like to reciprocally oppose/rebel against their parents/elders (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: slanderers, God-haters, insolent, haughty, boastful,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: slanderers, God-haters, insolent, haughty, boastful, inventors of evil, rebellious toward parents,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Ro'o boe re'a dènge j'ara dhu mola. Ro'o boe re'a dènge lii pamoa unu ra, ka dhèu lèka heka rèngu. Re'a boe sue dhèu. Dènge boe d'ara kasia ciki sa mi dedha dhèu.<bt>They don't want to know what was straight/right/true. They didn't want to know anything about their own promises, so people couldn't believe/trust them anymore. They didn't know how to love/pity people. They didn't have even a bit of pity/compassion/mercy for people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lèka = trust (here)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lèka = trust (here)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: foolish, faithless, heartless, ruthless."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: foolish, faithless, heartless, ruthless.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Rèngu re'a le atora Ama Lamatua dhu peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu tao rupa-rupa bhabhelu, hud'i abhu huku madhe.&gt;&gt; Masi ka re'a le atora ne, te ngaa loe boe tao rupa-rupa bhabhelu. Mesa boe se'e se di, te ngaa ra dadugu-rariu dhèu leo, sèna ka tao bhelu kahèi. Ne'e ne seli-kolane!<bt>They know God's regulation that says, “People who do various sorts of evil, must get/experience the death penalty/punished by death.” Even though they knew that regulation, nevertheless they did not stop doing various sorts of evil. And not just these things, but they also incited/persuaded/provoked (doublet) other people, so that they would also do evil. That's past the limits (=too much)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: They know God's decree, that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: They know God's decree, that those who practice such things deserve to die-yet they not only do them but even applaud others who practice them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua nasa kahèi dènge dhèu Yahudi dhu Na hag'e nare le<bt>God2 also is/gets angry with the Yahudi people whom He had chosen out/set aside</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Èu dhu tadèngi le rupa-rupa j'ara bhabhelu-katub'a deo na, si? Hèia èu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Bhabhelu dhèu se'e seli-kolane!&gt;&gt; Ladhe èu pangee le sèmi èèna, na, mu mage-mage, ee! Te èu mesa mu bhelu sèmi èèna kahèi. Nèti èèna ka, èu dènge boe alasan ho siri iisi èu, masi ka èu ne cee èèna ka. Ladhe èu peka, na, lèke tare'a dhèu dhu bhelu sèra abhu huku, te ngaa baku bhèlu, na, èu mesa mu ka pèci sasala mi ngi'u èu unu mu. Te èu tao sala sèmi èèna kahèi!<bt>You-sg heard about all.sorts.of evil just.then, right? So, you are thinking, saying, &lt;&lt;The evil of those people is just too much!&gt;&gt; If you are thinking like that, na, be careful, ee! Cuz (elaboration) you-sg yourself are also evil like that. That's why you don't have a reason/excuse to defend yourself, regardless of whoever you might be. If you say that, it's true/right/appropriate for evil people to get/be punished, don't forget, that you also are throwing wrong/accusing your own self. Cuz (elaboration) you-sg also have done wrong like that! [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anapologeetos: CHECK PARALLELS LITERALLY: Therefore, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">anapologeetos: CHECK PARALLELS LITERALLY: Therefore, you who judge another person are without excuse, whoever you are, because by the reason for which you judge another person, you judge yourself, because you do the same things.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:1, Lukas 6:37</note><v n="2" />Te ngaa èdhi te'a, peka na, ladhe Ama Lamatua hia huku mi dhèu bhelu sèra, tatu Nèngu pama'ète lii langu ra dènge mola.<bt>But we-inc know that if God punishes evil people, surely He decides their litigations/cases/ disputes/issues straightly/justly/fairly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ca j'ara, lula dhèu dhu tao"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ca j'ara, lula dhèu dhu tao bhelu, peka na: Lamatua pama'ète lii langu dhèu dènge mola.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we know that the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we know that the judgment of God is true about those who practise such things.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Do, tasamia? Ele boe èu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Lèke tare'a ladhe dhèu dhu tao bhelu-katub'a sèra abhu hahuku nèti Lamatua.&gt;&gt; Aa te ngaa èu kahèi dhu ad'u-ue bhabhelu sama sèmi rèngu. Te èu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a abhu boe hahuku nèti Lamatua.&gt;&gt; Ngangee èèna mai nèti mia?<bt>Or, what/how? Perhaps/probably you-sg are thinking, that, &lt;&lt;It is right/true/appropiate for people who do evil (doublet) to get punishment from God2.&gt;&gt; Whereas.in.actual.fact you are also doing (doublet) evil like them. But2 you are thinking, &lt;&lt;I won't get/experience God2's punishment.&gt;&gt; Where do you get that thinking from?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do you think, you who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do you think, you who judge those who do such things, and you do the same, that you will escape the judgment of God?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ama Lamatua dhu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èu. Aa Na mau-mau era, nèti tatao èu sèra. Te ngaa tasamia ka èu pahahe Ne? Ele boe èu me'a boe, na, Lamatua dhu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èu ne, sèna ka èu tèke eele sasala èu, aa lèpa hari asa Nèngu.<bt>God is showing His good insides (*grace/goodness/ kindness/generosity) to you-sg. And He is still patient about your deeds/behaviour. But how is it that are you disparaging, viewing with.contempt Him? Perhaps/probably you don't understand, that, He is showing His good insides to you, so that you leave/abandon your sins, and return to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sero = serong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sero = serong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Or do you despise the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Or do you despise the riches of his kindness/goodness, and forbearance/tolerance, and longsuffering/patience, not knowing that the kindness/goodness of God leads you to repentance?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te ngaa èu ne kètu hadhu, aa mo'o boe nanene! Aa mo'o boe core eele sasala èu, ciki sa hèi! De èu mesa mu ka dhu ad'u ho abhu huku dhu bia risi hari. Te ropa d'ai lod'o èle rai-haha ne, Lamatua tai-dadoo mamuri dhèu aa'i-aa'i. Aa èèna na dhèu aa'i-aa'i re'a, na, Lamatua pama'ète lii langu dènge mola. Pe Na huku èu bia, lula Na sèmi nare boe tatao èu sèra.<bt>But you here, are stubborn, and don't want to listen/obey! And you don't want to get rid of your sins, even a little! So (consequently), you yourself are the one who is making it so you get/experience an even heavier punishment. Cuz (elaboration) when the end of the world has come, God2 will weigh/evaluate (doublet) all people's lives. And then all people will know that, God2 decides people's cases/disputes in a straight/correct/fair manner. Then He will punish you heavily/severely, because He doesn't accept/put up with those deeds of yours.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tai-dadoo = timbang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tai-dadoo = timbang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you have a hard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you have a hard and stubborn/unrepentant heart. So then, you are making your own punishment even greater on the Day when God's wrath and right judgments will be revealed.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Mamuri èu tasamia èèna ka, pe Lamatua ka dhu b'ala madhutu tatao èu.<bt>However you are living, later God2 is the one who will reciprocate/respond according to your deeds/behaviour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who will give back to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who will give back to every person according to what he has done.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 62:12, Lii Hini 24:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Te dhèu dhu tao j'ara be'a taruu-taruu, Lamatua hia ne mamuri dhu mola d'ai mia-mia. Rèngu abhu pakab'ua nèti dhèu kahèi, kolongara hua iia, dènge mamuri taruu dènge Ne toke d'ai mia-mia la'e.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) people who continually do good things, God2 will give them straight/true life forever. They will get honor from people, a good name/reputation, and live continually with Him forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mamuri madhii = manèro"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">mamuri madhii = manèro</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Eternal life to those who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Eternal life to those who by patiently continuing to do good, are looking for glory and honor and immortality.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua sèmi nare boe dhèu dhu tao bhelu-katub'a. Nèngu nasa titu kèna dènge si, te re'a dhoka palab'a di. Dhèu se tao boe madhutu j'ara dhu lèke, te re'a dhoka tao madhutu j'ara dhu bhelu di.<bt>But God doesn't accept/put up with people who do evil (doublet). He gets/is really angry at them, cuz (elaboration) they only know how to reciprocally oppose. They don't do according to things which are right/correct/true, cuz (elaboration) they only know how to just do according to things which are evil. [EXEG: Gk /eritheia/ can mean 1) selfish ambition, or 2) rebellious, hostile. In the immediate context of vs.8 plus the larger context of chapters 1-2, the second sense is a better fit. HCE, LN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But anger and wrath to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But anger and wrath to those who are selfish / unsubmissive / rebellious / contentious, and do not obey the truth, but obey unrighteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu tao bhelu, bèli-camèd'a abhu j'aj'èra. Masi ka dhèu Yahudi, do dhèu Yahudi boe èèna ka, aa'i-aa'i ra pasae rare.<bt>All people who do evil, later will be afflicted with difficulty/suffering. Regardless of whether Yahudi people, or not Yahudi people, they will all bear theirs [NOTE: resonates with threat/curse].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tribulation/trouble and anguish/pain/distress to every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tribulation/trouble and anguish/pain/distress to every person who does evil, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;hia uru mi dhèu Yahudi, aa mi dhèu Yahudi boe kahèi.&gt;&gt; Ètu d'ara ayat ceo, sasoa na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu aa'i-aa'i abhu sasusa, risi-risi hari dhèu Yahudi, te ngaa dhèu Yahudi boe abhu kahèi.&gt;&gt; Ètu d'ara ayat canguru, sasoa na, &lt;&lt;Èèna na, Lamatua ded'e padedha-dedha dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu tao j'ara be'a, risi-risi hari dhèu Yahudi, te ngaa Na ded'e dhèu Yahudi boe kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yunani Bible writes, saying, “to the Yahudi people first/foremost, and to non Yahudi people too”. In verse 9 it means “Everyone will experience trouble/difficulty, particularly the Yahudi people, but also the non Yahudi people get it.” In verse 10 it means, “Later God2 will glorify/elevate on high everyone who does good things, particularly the Yahudi people, but He also elevates the non Yahudi people.”</bt></note><v n="10" />Te ngaa dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu tao j'ara dhu be'a, bèli-camèd'a Lamatua ded'e padedha-dedha, aa pakab'ua si, sèna ka ra abhu mamuri mera-milu. Masi ka dhèu Yahudi, do dhèu Yahudi boe èèna ka, rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra abhu.<bt>But all people who do good things, later God2 will *glorify them (=elevate on high), and honor them, so that they live in peace (safety &amp; relationships). Regardless of whether they are Yahudi people, or not Yahudi people, they will all obtain fruit/benefits [+positive].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But glory, honor, and peace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But glory, honor, and peace to everyone that does good, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Te Lamatua dhu hag'e boe rèhu dhèu!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 doesn't choose faces (=show preferences/bias)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because God does not show"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because God does not show preferences [judges everyone by the same standard].</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 10:17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Atora Lamatua lèke mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i. Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu re'a boe Atora ne, dhu tao sala, èèna na cèri eele nèngu nèti Lamatua. Aa ladhe dhèu dhu re'a le Atora ne, te ngaa na tao sala, pe Lamatua pake hari Atora ne, ho pama'ète hahuku na. Rèngu cèri eele nèti Lamatua kahèi, lula ra sisu le Atora Na.<bt>God's Regulations/Law applies to all people. If there is a person who doesn't know that Law, who does wrong, s/he will be separated off/cut off from God2. And if there is a person who already knows that Law, but s/he does wrong, later God2 will use that Law again to decide his punishment. They will also be separated off/ cut off from God2, because they have transgressed/ violated that Law of His. [EXEG: This is a safe middle ground rendering, reflected in most translations. 1) it deliberately preserves a kind of ambiguity presented in the Gk and debated among the commentators as to whether this is meaning a) the Torah Law given to Moses, or b) a universal law of God justice [as implied by vs.14]; 2) it reflects what all commentators agree about a) universal sinfulness, and b) universal punishment; 3) it reflects the different outcomes for the 2 groups from the Gk (don't force the two to be identical-they are not in the Gk), but makes explicit that the end result is the same; 4) the whole verse (higher level) is structured in parallel as is the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because as many as have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because as many as have sinned without the Law will also die without the Law. And as many as have sinned with the Law will also die with the Law. apolountai: perish; in the sense of eternal destruction, not just normal death, "dey goin get cut off from God"<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Neo pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, ladhe nanene dhoka Atora di, èèna d'ai mèka. Te hud'i tao madhutu ku Atora Na, heka Na sèmi nare si kèna. De baku dhoka nanene di!<bt>If [a person] wants to be in a reciprocally good/right relationship with God, it's not enough/sufficient to only just hear His Law. Cuz (elaboration) people must also do according to His Law, only.then will He accept them. Don't just only listen! [NOTE: Last sentence to emphasise/reinforce stylistically the point Paul is making.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akroatai: &quot;nuff&quot; is an intransitive verb,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">akroatai: "nuff" is an intransitive verb, not an adjective, so it takes "no" LITERALLY: Because it is not the hearers of the Law who are justified before God, but the doers of the Law are justified.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Masi ka dhèu Yahudi boe sèra, re'a boe isi nèti Atora Lamatua, te ngaa abhu kahèi nèti rèngu dhu tao madhutu Atora ne. Lula d'ara iiki rèngu unu ra ka dhu peka, mia ka dhu lèke, aa mia ka dhu sale.<bt>Even though people who are not Yahudi don't know the contents of God2's Law, nevertheless there are people from among them who do according to that Law. Because their own inner insides are what tells them, which (of choices) is right/correct/true, and which is wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when the Gentiles, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when the Gentiles, who do not have the Law, do by nature the things the Law says, they, who do not have the Law, are a Law for themselves.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dènge j'ara ne rèngu pad'elo, na, Atora Lamatua dhu suri ètu d'ara ra, nuka sèmi loa hèngu dhu Lamatua manènu ètu d'ara ra. D'ara rèngu mesa ra, ka dhu tai-dadoo ngaa dhu rèngu ad'u-ue. Hèia ngangee rèngu unu ra ka dhu galaa, na, rèngu dhu tao sale, aa peka na abhu dhu tao lèke.<bt>In that way, they show that, God2's Law is written in their insides, like a thread which God2 wove in their insides [MESSAGE: “woven into the very fabric of our creation”. Dhao is a weaving culture.] Their own insides are what evaluates/judges (doublet) what they do (doublet). So/Then their own thinking is what accuses/ condemns, (when) they do wrong, and lets them know/tells/affirms (when) they do right/correctly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They show the requirement of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They show the requirement of the Law written on their hearts, their consciences bearing witness, and their thoughts meanwhile accusing or excusing them,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />De lod'o Ama Lamatua ded'e Yesus Kristus j'aj'i Dhèu Pama'ète Lii Langu, Na parisa toke lutu j'ara-j'ara dhu pahuni ètu d'ara dhèu. Ja'a aj'a sèmi ne'e, sama sèmi dhu suri le ètu d'ara Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently), when God has lifted.up/appointed Yesus Kristus to be the Habitual Decider of Litigations (*judge), He will carefully/finely examine all the finest/tiniest things which are hidden in people's insides. I teach like.that, just like that which is written in God2's Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: in the day when God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: in the day when God will judge the secrets of people according to my Good News through Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Masi ka dhèu Yahudi tao madhutu Atora Lamatua, te ngaa j'ara èèna patabuli boe rèngu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra [\s2]<bt>Even if Yahudi people do according to God2's Law, nevertheless that doesn't save them [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />De miu dhèu Yahudi, tasamia? Miu d'èi padedha iisi, peka na, dhoka miu di dhu kèpe Atora Lamatua, dhu Na papuru mai re Musa, sina ma? Miu kahèi d'èi koa iisi, lula pa'èci miu dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently) you-pl who are Yahudi people, how is it? You-pl like to keep elevating/promoting yourselves, saying, you-pl are the only ones who hold God2's Law which He handed down via Musa, right? You-pl also like to praise yourselves, because of your being joined with God. [NOTE: Gk is 2s, but we go to 2p for genre reasons. ; EXEG: “in God” bragging (negatively valued) about unique relationship with God, fitting high-level themes. NRSV, NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèb'a ore = omong kotor, padhai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">hèb'a ore = omong kotor, padhai lii leli</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if you call yourself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if you call yourself a Jew, and you depend on the Law, and brag about God,</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Tare'a! Miu dhu me'a le, dad'èi Lamatua. Miu dhu me'a kahèi, mia ka dhu be'a risi. Miu me'a mèu le j'ara se aa'i-aa'i, lula mese agama ka dhu aj'a-nori miu nèti Atora Lamatua.<bt>That's right! You already know God2's will. You also already know what is the best/most good. You already know all these things, because religious teachers have taught you from God2's Law. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and know his will, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and know his will, and approve the things that are more excellent/superior/best, because you are instructed from the Law,</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Miu padedha iisi, peka na, miu bisa paj'uj'u j'ara hia dhèu dhu re'a boe lasi sa mia. Miu tao iisi nuka sèmi saraa dhu pasaraa dhèu dhu mamuri ètu d'ara maroga.<bt>You elevate yourselves, saying, you can show the way for people who don't know where to go [can imply morally or in life]. You consider yourselves like light that shines for all people who live in darkness. [CHECK /tao iisi/ as ‘anggap diri’]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and are sure that you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and are sure that you are a guide for the blind, a light for those who are in darkness,</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Lula miu kèpe pa'èra Atora Lamatua, ka miu pangee, na, miu me'a aa'i mèu-mèu, aa miu kèpe pa'èra-èra aa'i dhu lèke, sina ma? Nèti èèna ka, miu pangee, na, miu bisa nori dhèu goa dènge ana iiki dhu re'a boe ngaa-ngaa.<bt>Because you hold firmly to God2's Law, you think you know everything completely [grammatical construction suggests "everything there is to know"], and you already hold firmly everything that is true/correct, right? That's why you think you can teach ignorant/unschooled/stupid people and small children who don't know anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: an instructor of the foolish,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: an instructor of the foolish, a teacher of babies/the young, who has in the Law the full content of knowledge and truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: miu d'èi aj'a dhèu leo, te ngaa tasamia ka miu mo'o boe nori ngi'u mi?! Miu d'èi ca'e mimbar, ho peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu baku mana'u.&gt;&gt; Te ngaa, nga tao ka miu unu mi mana'u?!<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like.this: you-pl like to teach other people, but why do you yourselves not want to learn/be taught/be advised about anything?! You like to get up in the pulpit, to say, “People shouldn't steal.” But why is it that you yourselves steal?! [SSA: rhetorical questions as accusations.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mana'u pagogo-pagero"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">mana'u pagogo-pagero</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, you who teach another,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, you who teach another, don't you teach yourself? You who preach that a person should not steal, do you steal?</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Miu aj'a, na, &lt;&lt;Baku tao j'ara makae dènge dhèu dhu j'aj'i boe dhèu èmu-kamali mu.&gt;&gt; Te ngaa, nga tao ka miu mesa mi tao j'ara makae sèmi èèna?! Miu mesa mi d'èi boe mèdha sogo-tagu, te ngaa nga tao ka miu mana'u pahuni mèdha nèti d'ara èmu nidhu?<bt>You teach, saying, &lt;&lt;Don't do shameful things (sexually) with people who are not your-sg husband or your-sg wife.&gt;&gt; But why is that you yourselves do shameful things like that?! You yourselves don't like [no stronger word available] traditional.worship (doublet) things, but why is it that you quietly steal/pilfer things from the traditional.worship houses?!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karihu karehe = maen kotor ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">karihu karehe = maen kotor ; èmu nidhu = rumah berhala</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hierosyleis: profane their temples? plunder their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">hierosyleis: profane their temples? plunder their temples? How honest are you: do you profit from the things you denounce? LITERALLY: You who say a person should not commit adultery, do you commit adultery? You who hate/detest idols, do you rob temples?<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Miu d'èi lole pakapai Atora Lamatua, te ngaa nga tao ka miu mesa mi sisu Atora ne, aa pamakae Lamatua?!<bt>You like to speak.big=brag about God2's Law, but why is it that you yourselves trasngress/ violate that Law, and make God2 ashamed/ embarrassed?!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakapai = mengagungkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pakapai = mengagungkan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You who boast in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You who boast in the Law, do you dishonor God by breaking the Law?</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te karèi nèti uru ka, dhu suri tèke le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, na, &lt;&lt;Lula bhabhelu miu dhèu Yahudi, nèti èèna ka dhèu leo kara pahahe kolongara Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) beginning from long.ago, it was written in the Clean/Holy Writings, saying, &lt;&lt;Because of you-pl Yahudi people's evil, that's why the other/foreign (=non Yahudi) people often despise God's name/reputation.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the name of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the name of God is blasphemed by the Gentiles because of you, as it is written.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Masi ka dhèu Yahudi suna, te ngaa j'ara èèna patabuli boe rèngu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra [\s2]<bt>Even if Yahudi people get *circumcised, that also doesn't save them [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Miu dhèu Yahudi hud'i suna ku madhutu Atora Lamatua, sina ma? Èèna j'aj'i mi tadha, peka na, miu dhèu Yahudi dhu unu hak, ho sèmi mere lii padhadha Lamatua. Te ngaa ladhe miu sisu Atora Lamatua, na, Lamatua sèmi nare boe miu. Miu j'aj'i èci èèna ka dènge dhèu Yahudi boe, aa sama sèmi dhèu dhu suna rèdhi mèka.<bt>You-pl who are Yahudi people must be circumcised according to God2's Law, right? That is a sign, that, you are the ones who have the right to receive God2's promise(s). But if/when you violate God2's Law, God2 doesn't accept you. You become like (you) are not Yahudi people, and like people who were never circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because circumcision is good for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because circumcision is good for something if you keep the Law, but if you are a Law breaker, your circumcision becomes as uncircumcision.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Pangee paie-iie! Te ladhe dhèu dhu suna boe, tao madhutu Atora Lamatua, èèna na Lamatua sèmi nare ne, nuka sèmi dhèu Yahudi dhu suna, si?<bt>Think carefully! Cuz (elaboration) if a person who is not circumcised, acts/does according to God2's Law, later God will accept him, the same as if he were a Yahudi person who was circumcised, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, if he who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, if he who is not circumcised keeps the righteousness of the Law, won't his uncircumcision become as circumcision?</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Te ngaa baku pamud'e! Te ladhe dhèu Yahudi boe, dhu suna boe, tao madhutu Atora Lamatua, èèna na ra pad'elo ngaa? Ra pad'elo sasala miu, peka na, dhèu Yahudi dhu suna, sisu Atora Lamatua, masi ka miu dhu unu le Atora ne karèi nèti uru ka.<bt>But, be careful! Cuz (elaboration) if non Yahudi people who are not circumcised, do according to God2's Law, later they reveal/show what? They reveal your-pl wrongs, that, you Yahudi people who are circumcised, violate God2's Law, even though you have owned/possessed/had that Law from long.ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And shall not uncircumcision [Gentiles],"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And shall not uncircumcision [Gentiles], which is by nature, if it keep the Law, judge you [Jews], who by the letter [Law] and circumcision transgress the Law?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Baku pangee, na, dhèu dhu j'aj'i ana-èpu Abraham, aa dhu suna ètu ka'uri, èèna ka dhu tao ne j'aj'i dhèu unu Lamatua dhu lèke. Aad'o!<bt>Don't think that, a person who is Abraham's descendant, and who has been circumcised on/in the skin, that is what makes him be/become God2's true/real person. No!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he is not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he is not a Jew who is one outwardly, neither is the circumcision that which is outward in the flesh.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Dhu j'aj'i dhèu unu Lamatua dhu lèke, nuka dhèu dhu pabe'a dènge Lamatua. Te suna dhu lèke, èèna ka hia dhèu j'aj'i ana Ama Lamatua, dhu tao boe tadha ètu ka'uri, te ngaa tadha ètu d'ara dhèu, dhu Roh Lamatua tao. Dhèu rai-haha koa boe dhèu sèmi sèra, te ngaa Lamatua ka dhu ded'e padedha si.<bt>Those who are/become God2's true people, are the people who are in a reciprocally good/right relationship with God2. Cuz (elaboration) true circumcision, is that which makes people become God's child(ren), is not a sign on the skin, but a sign in the insides of a person (=heart) which God2's Spirit makes. Humans don't praise people like that, but God2 is the one who lifts.up=praises them up on high/glorifies them. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he is a Jew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he is a Jew who is one inwardly, and circumcision is from the heart, by the Spirit, and not from the letter. The praise for that is not from people, but from God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 30:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Masi ka dhèu Yahudi dènge hak ho abhu pusaka nèti lii padhadha Lamatua, te ngaa j'ara èèna patabuli boe rèngu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra [\s2]<bt>Even if/though Yahudi people have the right to receive the inheritance from God2's promise, that also doesn't save them [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Ladhe sèmi èèna, dhèu Yahudi dhu suna sèra, a'oto na ngaa? Ele boe miu pangee, na, dhèu Yahudi abhu ae dènge dhu be'a risi nèti dhèu Yahudi boe, do?<bt>If that's the case, becoming a *circumcised Yahudi person has what benefit? Perhaps/ probably you are thinking, that, the Yahudi people will get more (quantity) and better (quality) than the non Yahudi people, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what advantage does the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what advantage does the Jew have? Or what value is there in circumcision?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Tare'a! De dhèu Yahudi abhu oto ètu j'ara ae-ae. Ka èci, lula Lamatua pangèd'u sasab'a sa dhèu Yahudi, ho suri aa j'aga paie-iie Lii Holo-Nori Na.<bt>True! So (consequently) being a Yahudi person has advantages in many things/ways. First, because God2 gave the job/responsibility to the Yahudi people to write and carefully safeguard His Words. [#1-MESSAGE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Much indeed, in every way."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Much indeed, in every way. First, because the [message/words/sayings/promises] of God [was/were] [entrusted/committed] to them.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />De tasamia? Miu dhu pangee, na, Ama Lamatua bisa boe tao madhutu ngaa dhu Na padhai le, lula abhu dhèu Yahudi cahag'e dhu parcaya boe Nèngu, do?<bt>So (consequently), how is it? You-pl are thinking, that, God is not able to do according to what He said, because there are some Yahudi people who don't believe Him, or what?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What if some of them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What if some of them did not [believe/have faith]? Will their [unbelief/unfaithfulness] [cancel/nullify] the faithfulness of God?</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Bisa boe! Masi ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne kapod'e-kabèli, te ngaa Ama Lamatua padhai lii dhu mola taruu! Sanèd'e, te dhu suri tèke ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci lula-nèti ngi'u Lamatua, peka na,<bt>Impossible/no way! Even if/though all the people in this world are twisters-turners = decievers/liars (doublet), nevertheless God himself continues to speak what is straight/true! Remember, cuz (elaboration) what is written in the Clean/Holy Writings about God2's self, says,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapod'e-dod'e (less significant) = kapod'e-kabèli (heavier)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kapod'e-dod'e (less significant) = kapod'e-kabèli (heavier)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Abhu dhèu dhu pèci sasala, peka na,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who throw accusations, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nèngu pama'ète lii langu dhu bia cabèka.<bt>He judges disputes with prejudice/bias.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ngaa pe rèngu re'a, na,<bt>But later they will (come to) know, that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ngaa dhu Na peka-padhai èèna lèke tare'a.<bt>what He says, is really true.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèngu tatu segi,<bt>He will surely win,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lula Na bisa boe padhai lii sale.&gt;&gt;<bt>because it is not possible for Him to speak wrongly.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: context of Ps. 51 is David acknowledging the justice of God's judgement against him. But the wording and Pauline purpose here are different from Ps. 51, following the LXX, not the Hebrew, introducing the "win/prevail" term.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of course not! God must"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of course not! God must be true, even though every person is a liar. As it is written, "That you might be [shown to be right/proved right] in what you say, and might win when you are [judged/on trial]."</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 51:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te ngaa ladhe èdhi tao sala, èèna ka dhu peka paled'a mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i, ngaa dhu Lamatua tao èèna mema lèke tare'a. Ladhe sèmi èèna, èdhi peka ngaa hari? Neo peka, na, Lamatua adil boe ladhe Na huku èdhi, do? (Te abhu dhèu cahag'e dhu padhai lii sèmi èèna.)<bt>But if we-inc are doing wrong, that shows more clearly to all people, that, what God2 did then/there, is really correct. If that's the case, what can we-inc say further? Should [we] say, God2 isn't fair/just if He punishes us, or what? (Cuz (elaboration) there are some people who talk like that.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if our [unrighteousness/wrongdoing/injustice] shows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if our [unrighteousness/wrongdoing/injustice] shows the righteousness of God more clearly, what shall we say? Is God unjust to [punish us/brings his wrath on us/brings his anger on us]? (I am talking like a human being.)</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Bisa boe! Lamatua sala boe ladhe Na huku èdhi. Lula Na dènge hak ho huku dhèu dhu tao sala ètu rai-haha ne.<bt>Impossible/no way! God2 isn't wrong if He punishes us. Because He has the right to punish people who do wrong in this world. [EXEG: Morris argues against TEV, (NLT), saying “Some understand the question as “If God is not just, how can he judge the world?” (GNB), but this does not seem to be what the Greek means and it is not convincing. There is no theoretical reason why an unjust deity should not preside in an unjust judgment. Paul's point is rather that, assuming as all do that God will judge the world, some must be punished. Unless this happens, what occurs will not be judgment. It is the exercise of wrath, not the character of God, that is the point of it all.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of course not! Then how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of course not! Then how can God [judge/condemn] the world?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />De ladhe ja'a padhai lii monya, èèna peka na, hahuku Lamatua lèke tare'a. Ladhe ja'a pad'elo dadedha Na sèmi èèna, nga tao ka Nèngu parisa mamuri ja'a, ka pama'ète lii langu ja'a, na, ngaa dhu ja'a ad'u-ue ne, sala?<bt>So (consequently), if I speak.emptily=lie, that shows that, God2's punishment [is] true/correct. If I have already shown His high-ness/glory like.that, why does/will He examine my life and decide my case, saying, what I have done (doublet), is wrong/sin?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because if the truth of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because if the truth of God has increased through my lie, for his glory, then why am I judged to be a sinner?</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Baku sèmi èèna! Ladhe madhutu ka ngangee sèmi èèna, miu madhutu dhèu dhu peka, na, &lt;&lt;Hud'i laa èdhi tao bhelu-katub'a ae risi hari, sèna ka j'ara be'a asa tabha ae kahèi!&gt;&gt; Dhèu dhu peka sèmi èèna, pantas abhu huku. Te ngaa abhu dhèu dhu pa'ele iie kolongara ja'a, peka na, ja'a ka aj'a dhèu sèmi èèna.<bt>Don't do that! If (you want to) follow thinking like that, you-pl follow people who say, &lt;&lt;Just let us-inc do more evil (doublet), so that that which is good also increases more!&gt;&gt; People who speak like that, deserve to be punished. But there are people who speak destroying my name/reputation, saying I teach people that. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoon to krima endikon estin: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">hoon to krima endikon estin: the people, not the statement. LITERALLY: And not instead (as some slanderously report and affirm that we say), Let us do evil, that good may come? The condemnation for [that/them] is just.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu d'ara mola, te dhèu aa'i-aa'i tao sala<bt>There is not a single person who is truly straight insides (righteous), cuz (elaboration) everyone has done wrong</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />De tasamia? Miu pangee, na, èdhi dhèu Yahudi be'a risi nèti dhèu Yahudi boe, do? Aad'o! Te ja'a peka le dènge miu, na, dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu manahu le asa d'ara sasala, masi ka dhèu Yahudi, do dhèu Yahudi boe.<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Do you-pl think that those of us-inc who are Yahudi people are better than the non Yahudi people, (or what)? Impossible/no way! Cuz (elaboration) I have told/shown you, that, everybody falls into sin [entrenched phrase], whether s/he is a Yahudi person or, a non Yahudi person. [SSA, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then? Are we better"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then? Are we better than they? No, in no way. For we have already proved that both Jews and Gentiles are all under sin.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te dhu suri mema ètu d'ara Sasuri Ama Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci, na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings, that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu mamuri mola taruu.<bt>&lt;&lt;There is no person who lives straight/righteous continually.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èci sa aad'o!<bt>Not a single one!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;There"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "There is none righteous, no not one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu re'a mèu j'ara-j'ara Ama Lamatua.<bt>There is no person who truly knows/understands about God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abhu boe èci sa dhu neo patadha dènge Lamatua.<bt>Not even a single one who seeks to know2 God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is none that understands,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is none that understands, there is none that seeks for God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Rèngu pakaj'èu le nèti j'ara mamuri dhu mola.<bt>They all have distanced themselves from the life path that is straight/right.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ka rèngu se guna heka mi ngaa èci sa.<bt>So, they no longer have (social) use/value anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu pad'elo d'ara be'a.<bt>There is no person who shows a good insides (=good/kind/generous/gracious).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èci sa aad'o hèi!<bt>Not a single one!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They have all turned away,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They have all turned away, they have together become [unprofitable/worthless]. There is nobody that does good/kind/benevolent, no, not one.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 14:1-3, 53:1-3</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Lii padhai ra dhu hèu bhob'o,<bt>What they say, has a rotten stench,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèu bhob'o = bau busuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">hèu bhob'o = bau busuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nuka sèmi ro'a dhèu madhe dhu ra kèi hari.<bt>like a grave which people have dug up again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kèi = gali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kèi = gali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèti d'ara hèb'a ra kalua dhoka lii kapod'e-kabèli di.<bt>From their mouths comes out only sounds/words of twisting-turning=deceit/lies (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lii dhu kalua nèti d'ara hèb'a ra,<bt>Their words which come out from their months,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nuka sèmi raco mege.<bt>are like a snake's poison.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Their throat is an open"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Their throat is an open grave. They have used deceit with their tongues. The poison of snakes is under their lips.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 5:10, 140:4</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Hèb'a ra re'a dhoka padhèd'a di,<bt>Their mouths only know how to curse people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa lii padhai ra karehe, dhu papèd'a d'ara dhèu,<bt>and speak that which is rotten/defiling to make people have sick insides = hatred/vengeful,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te èèna ka dhu mai nèti d'ara rèngu dhu karehe.<bt>cuz (elaboration) that is what comes out from their rotten/evil insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whose mouth is full of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 10:7</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Re'a boe madha'u ladhe pamadhe dhèu.<bt>They're not afraid/hesitant to kill people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Their feet are swift to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Their feet are swift to shed blood.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Sad'i rèngu ètu mia èèna ka, na,<bt>Wherever they go, well,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lii langu, muri ètu èèna,<bt>disputes sprout up there,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="muri - hidup (here: timbul collocation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">muri - hidup (here: timbul collocation w/lii langu)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa pasusa rupa-rupa mi dedha dhèu.<bt>and cause all.sorts.of difficulty to people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [Destruction/ruin] and [misery/distress/trouble] are in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [Destruction/ruin] and [misery/distress/trouble] are in their paths.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Mamuri ra dhu re'a boe padame,<bt>They live without knowing how to live.in.mutual.peace/right relationships (=unable/unwilling/incapable),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa re'a boe mamuri dènge d'ara dhu mau.<bt>and don't know how to live with calm insides. [EXEG: explicating 2 of 3 senses of Gk. /eirene/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They have not known the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They have not known the way of peace.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:15-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 59:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Rèngu se bisa boe taha rare d'ara ra,<bt>They cannot control/restrain themselves,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lula dènge boe d'ara madha'u ciki sa mi Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>because they do not have even a bit of fear toward God.&gt;&gt; [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is no fear of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is no fear of God before their eyes.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 36:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />De èdhi te'a, na, Lamatua hia Atora Na mi dhèu dhu pahaha iisi mi Atora sèra. Dènge sèmi èèna, dhèu abhu boe alasan ho siri iisi, peka na, rèngu se, dhèu d'ara mola. Ladhe dhèu aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne hud'i paraga ku dènge Ama Lamatua, te Nèngu ka dhu j'ue lii langu dhu peka na, sala do aad'o.<bt>So (consequently), we-inc know that, God2 gave/gives His Law to people who must be.under/ subject.to that Law(s). In that way, they don't have any more excuses to defend themselves, saying they are straight/righteous people. When all people in this world must meet/face God, then He is the one who decides their case, saying they are wrong/guilty, or not. [EXEG: on Gk. /hypodikos/ focusing on the judging process, rather than the resulting punishment, see NRSV, SSA, LN.] [NOTE: Dhao team was the ones who explicated “excuse (for what)”. But they got it wrong (“excuse for rebelling”), so we followed the suggestion fr. Kupang note.][NOTE to daughter translations: if UNS's can't get WHY they have no more excuse, try /...apa-apa lai, ko bela diri, bilang, dong tu, orang hati lurus./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now we know that whatever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now we know that whatever the Law says, it says to those who are [under/subject to] the Law, that every mouth may be [stopped/silenced], and all the world may become [guilty/ answerable/ accountable/ subject to judgment/ liable to punishment] before God.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Nèti èèna ka, abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu bisa peka, na, &lt;&lt;Ama Lamatua cap ja'a, dhèu d'ara mola, lula ja'a tao madhutu aa'i Atora Lamatua.&gt;&gt; Bisa boe! Te Atora Lamatua ka dhu pad'elo, na, èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti tao sala.<bt>That's why there is not even a single person who can speak, saying, “God2 has stamped/branded/ categorised me as a straight insides/righteous person, because I do according to/obey all of God2's Laws.” Can't [say it]! Cuz (elaboration) God2's Law is which shows that, we-inc all do wrong. [NLT: For the more we know God's law, the clearer it becomes that we aren't obeying it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For that reason, no [person/human]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For that reason, no [person/human] can be [justified/made right] before [him/God] by the deeds of the Law. For by the Law the knowledge of sin comes.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 143:2, Galati 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hud'i parcaya uuru ku Lamatua Yesus, heka Ama Lamatua cap èdhi, dhèu d'ara mola<bt>(We-inc) must believe first in the Lord Yesus, only.then will God stamp/categorise us as straight insides/righteous people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Baku malaa dènge naneo Lamatua dhu paj'uj'u j'ara, ho èdhi bisa pabe'a hari dènge Nèngu. Dhu lèke, ladhe èdhi bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua, te ngaa lula boe nèti èdhi tao madhutu Atora Na. Te Atora Na dhu suri le sèmi èèna, aa dhèu rèti lii padhai Na uru-uru sèra, peka sèmi èèna kahèi ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na.<bt>Don't be confused about God2's plan which shows the path so that we can be in a reciprocally good/ right relationship with Him again. In actual fact, we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, but not because we are following His Law. Cuz (elaboration) His Law itself is what writes like that, and His spokespersons (*prophets) from long ago also told like that in His Clean/Holy Writings. [NLT - But now God has shown us a different way of being right in his sight-not by obeying the law but by the way promised in the Scriptures long ago.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now, the righteousness of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now, the righteousness of God is shown without the Law. The Law and the Prophets testify to that.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ama Lamatua peka, na, èdhi dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Ne, ropa èdhi parcaya Yesus Kristus. Nèngu dhu hag'e boe rèhu dhèu, te Na tao sèmi èèna mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Yesus.<bt>God says we-inc are straight insides/righteous people who are in a reciprocally good/right relationship with Him when we-inc believe in Yesus Kristus. He doesn't choose faces (=discriminate), cuz (elaboration) He does like that for all people who believe in Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Even the righteousness of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Even the righteousness of God which is by faith in Jesus Christ toward all who believe. For there is no difference.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galati 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Te dhèu aa'i-aa'i tao sala. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu dhu tenge-tenge j'ara ho neo pabe'a ngi'u rèngu dènge Ama Lamatua, bisa boe pamèci dènge dadedha Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) all people do wrong/sin. That's why people who keep trying to find a way to make themselves in a reciprocally good relationship with God, can't arrive/reach/get equal to the point of God2's high-ness/glory. [EXEG: SSA discusses Gk “have sinned” as a “gnomic or timeless aorist” expressing a general truth, so in Timor lgs best to not use perfective /su/; NLT, Message]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="madha-madha tenge j'ara = berlumba-lumba cari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">madha-madha tenge j'ara = berlumba-lumba cari jalan (masing-masing); madha = sendiri (?)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For all have sinned, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For all have sinned, and [come short of/fall short of/lack] the glory of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Ama Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na, aa pama'ète, peka na, èdhi dènge heka sasala. Na sèmi nare èdhi, lula Yesus Kristus sui nare le èdhi nèti sasala-sasigo èdhi.<bt>Even though that's the case, nevertheless God himself is the one who showed His good insides (=grace), and decided that, we-inc are no longer wrong/guilty. He accepts us, because Yesus Kristus has *redeemed/paid to set free us from our sins (doublet). [NLT] [NOTE: redeem word is used for getting back something from a pawn shop, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They are justified by his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They are justified by his free [grace/gift], through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Ama Lamatua paj'uj'u le Yesus, sèna ka j'aj'i korban papo makae ho saku eele sasala-sigo èdhi. Te ngaa èdhi hud'i parcaya Ne, na, Nèngu ka dhu tago nare hahuku èdhi. Ka Na pasuti raa Na, aa madhe gati èdhi. Dènge j'ara ne'e, Ama Lamatua peka na, ngaa dhu Na pama'ète ne, lèke tare'a. Uru èèna, d'ara Lamatua taleo titu kèna, hèia Na pama'ète ho pabhèlu eele sasala-sasigo dhu dhèu ad'u-ue le. Te ngaa ladhe Na huku boe dhèu dhu tao sala, Nèngu adil boe. De Na bhoke j'ara, sèna ka Yesus Kristus dui nare hahuku nèti dhèu sala. Limuri ne, Lamatua pad'elo mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i, peka na, Nèngu tao dhu be'a taruu. Ka dhèu sala aa'i-aa'i ra dhu parcaya Yesus, Na cap si dhèu mola.<bt>God has chosen/designated Yesus to be a covering-embarrassment/guilt (=paying penalty) sacrifice which wipes away our-inc wrongs (doublet). [CHECK /papo makae/, says broad, not just setting right sexual offences.] But we-inc must believe in Him, that, He is the one who bore our punishment. And He spilled His blood [a culturally significant phrase, e.g. used to acknowledge the service/sacrifice of war heroes or others dying for a higher cause], and died in exhange for us. In that way, God shows, that, what He has decided, is right/correct/true. Previously, God2's insides were very wide (=extremely patient), so He decided to completely forget the wrongs (doublet) which people had done. [NOTE to daughter translations: if vernacular equivalent of /korban tutu malu/ is restricted to sexual offenses, try /pili Yesus jadi korban ko bayar kotong pung denda/] But if He does not judge/punish wrong/guilty people, na, He is not just/fair. So (consequently) He opened the way/means so that Yesus Kristus could bear wrong/guilty people's punishment. Now, God2 shows all people, that, He does that which is good continually. So, all wrong/sinful/guilty people, who believe in Yesus, He stamp/brand/ categorise them as straight/righteous people. [EXEG/DISCOURSE: SSA, Uma; ellipsed propositions to connect 25 &amp; 26. UNS's not get it without this explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papo = sekedar ; korban papo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">papo = sekedar ; korban papo makae = korban tutu malu (menggantikan) ; UNSs not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: God presented Jesus to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: God presented Jesus to be a [means of cancelling guilt/sacrifice for cancelling guilt/means of forgiveness/ propitiation/sacrifice for sins], through faith in his blood, to declare his [righteousness/justice] for the forgiveness/passing by/disregarding of past sins because of the [patience/forbearance] of God. LITERALLY: To show his righteousness at this time, that he might be just, and the justifier of the one who believes in Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />De tasamia? Ele boe miu pangee, na, miu bisa padhai lii lela dedha, lula Ama Lamatua sèmi nare miu, do? Bisa boe! Miu neo pad'elo Atora èci dhu tao pabe'a miu dènge Lamatua, do? Miu pangee, na, Lamatua sèmi nare miu lula miu tao dhu be'a, do? Bisa boe! Èdhi te'a dhoka paj'uj'u mi Atora dhu peka na, Ama Lamatua sèmi nare èdhi, lula èdhi parcaya Yesus. Nèngu na, kèna!<bt>So, how is it? Perhaps you-pl are thinking you can talk-big=boast, right? Because God has accepted you, right? [You] Can't! You-pl want to show one Regulation that can make you-pl in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, right? Do you think God2 will accept you because you do good things, [tag question = huh]? [You] Can't! We-inc know/recognise only the Regulation that says, God receives/accepts us because we-inc believe in Yesus. That's it/all! [CONTEXT: “law of faith” = “believing in Jesus” has already been made explicit in vs.22-26. Out of context Paul would be talking about the Mosaic law, so Jesus here would be an anachronism. But in context it is not.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padhai lii lela dedha = omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">padhai lii lela dedha = omong tinggi, omong besar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Where is boasting then? It"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what rule/reason? By deeds? No, but by the rule of faith.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Nèti èèna ka, èdhi te'a sèmi ne'e: dhèu bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua, nèti ra parcaya Yesus, nèti boe rèngu tao madhutu Atora di.<bt>That's why now we know/understand like this: people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because they believe in Yesus, not just from doing according to his Law. [EXEG: if object of ‘faith’ needs clarification, SSA says “believe in Christ”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore we conclude that a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore we conclude that a person is justified by faith without the deeds of the Law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: Ama Lamatua sèmi nare dhoka dhèu Yahudi di, do Nèngu sèmi nare dhèu leo kahèi? Lèke! Na sèmi nare aa'i!<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: does God only receive/accept the Yahudi people, or, does He also accept other people? True! He accepts them all!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Is he the God of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Is he the God of the Jews only? Isn't he the God of the Gentiles too? Yes, also the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Te Ama Lamatua ne, dhoka èci di. Aa dhoka j'ara èci di, dhu Na sèmi nare sèna ka èdhi dhèu rai-haha ne bisa pabe'a dènge Ne. Nuka èdhi hud'i parcaya Kristus. J'ara ne pala mi dhèu Yahudi dènge dhèu Yahudi boe kahèi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) this.aforementioned God, is only just one. And there is only just one path/way which He accepts so.that we-inc humans can be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. That.is, we must believe in Kristus. That path is for the Yahudi people and the non Yahudi people also. [EXEG: NLT. Note ‘Kristus’ as object of faith here--it's explicit in Gk. in vs.22. (sort of), so we don't have to maintain the Abraham model here. See SSA.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because there is only one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because there is only one God, who will justify the circumcision from faith and the uncircumcision through faith.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 6:4, Galati 3:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: ladhe èdhi parcaya Lamatua, èèna na tao Atora Na j'aj'i heka ngaa-ngaa, do? Aad'o! Dhu lèke ka, parcaya èdhi èèna ka dhu tao pamèci Atora Na.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: if we-inc believe in the Lord/God2, does that make His Law no longer of validity/consequence, or [not]? No! In actual fact, our faith is what makes His Law legal/officially.validated/ complete/fulfilled. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /bekin sah/ is too challenging to translate, try /kasi tunju, bilang, itu Atoran tu, batúl/. We are deliberately vague with Lord/God as object of belief (can map to either God or Kristus). Higher-level context also allows, but does not require, /Yesus/ or /Kristus/. I (CEG) prefer this current rendering, because this section is building on the example of Abraham and the prophets believing in God.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haduli = hiraukan (peduli)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">haduli = hiraukan (peduli)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èèna na tèke eele Atora Na,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">èèna na tèke eele Atora Na, do? Aad'o! Dhu lèka ka, tao pamèci Atora Na.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do we then [make void/nullify/cancel]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do we then [make void/nullify/cancel] the Law by faith? Of course not! Instead, we [establish/uphold/confirm/validate/giving it its true value] the Law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Conto sèmi baki Abraham: nèngu pabe'a dènge Lamatua lula parcaya Ne [\s2]<bt>Example from forefather Abraham. He was in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because [he] believed in Him [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Èdhi tare conto nèti Abraham, baki ji'i dhèu Yahudi. Èdhi bisa te'a ngaa nèti nèngu lula-nèti dhèu bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua, lula parcaya Kristus?<bt>Let's take an example from Abraham, our-exc Yahudi people's forefather. From him, what can we learn/know that makes us in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because.of believing in Kristus? [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="De, ladhe èdhi tare conto nèti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">De, ladhe èdhi tare conto nèti Abraham, baki ji'i dhèu Yahudi, èdhi bisa aj'a j'ara ngaa dhu bisa pabe'a èdhi dènge Lamatua, lula parcaya Kristus èèna?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what shall we say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what shall we say that Abraham, our physical ancestor, has found?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Èdhi bisa te'a sèmi ne'e: ladhe Abraham bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua, lula na tao j'ara be'a, nèngu kahèi abhu hak ho koa iisi ètu madha dhèu rai-haha. Te ngaa ètu madha Lamatua, nèngu bisa boe bhoka hèb'a.<bt>We-inc can learn like.this: if Abraham could be in reciprocally right relationship with God2, because he did good things, he also has a right to praise himself in front of humans. But in God2's eyes (=view), he can't open his mouth (=say anything).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if Abraham were justified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if Abraham were justified by deeds, he would have something to boast about, but not before God.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te dhu suri ètu Sasuri Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci, peka na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lula Abraham parcaya Ama Lamatua,<bt>&lt;&lt;Because Abraham believed God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nèti èèna ka, Lamatua peka na, Abraham ne dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Nèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>that's why God2 said Abraham was a straight insides (=righteous) person who is in a reciprocally right relationship with Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What does the Scripture say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What does the Scripture say? "Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 15:6, Galati 3:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dhèu sab'a, tatu abhu gaji. Èèna na doi iia d'ara boe, te ngaa doi dhu lamatua na b'ae ne gati rui-j'aj'èra. Te sèra sa hak nèti dhèu sab'a.<bt>A person who works, surely receives (his/her) wages. That is not free gift money, but money which his boss pays to replace/reciprocate that person tiredness/ effort (doublet). Cuz (elaboration) that is the right of a worker.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who works is paid."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who works is paid. His wages are not regarded as a gift, but as something he has earned.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Lamatua ka dhu unu hak, ho peka na, dhèu cee dhu parcaya Yesus Kristus bisa pabe'a hari dènge Ne, masi ka uru èèna, dhèu ne tao sala aa pahae boe Lamatua. Abhu boe j'ara èci sa, dhu dhèu bisa ad'u-ue, ho pabe'a ngi'u nèngu dènge Lamatua. Te dhèu hud'i parcaya uuru ku Yesus Kristus, heka Lamatua peka na, nèngu dhèu d'ara mola, aa Lamatua sèmi nare ne.<bt>God2 is the one who has the right to say, that whoever believes in Yesus Kristus can be in a reciprocally good relationship again (=reconciled) with Him, even though previously that person did wrong and did not care at all about God2. There is not a single thing a person can do (doublet), so.that s/he can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. Cuz (elaboration) a person must first believe in Yesus Kristus, only.then God2 says s/he is a straight insides (righteous) person and God2 accepts/receives him/ her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But to him who believes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But to him who believes in the one who justifies the ungodly, and does not work, his faith is credited to him as righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dhèu aae Daud peka kahèi, na, d'ara dhèu karèj'e-karae, ropa Ama Lamatua peka na, dhèu se dhu d'ara mola, masi ka rèngu tao boe ngaa-ngaa. Te Daud suri, na,<bt>King Daud also told, saying, person/people's insides were joyful (doublet) when God said they were straight insides (=righteous) people, even.though they didn't do anything. Cuz (elaboration) Daud wrote, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: David also describes the happiness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: David also describes the happiness of the person to whom God [gives/credits] righteousness apart from works,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />&lt;&lt;Masi ka dhèu se sisu Atora Lamatua,<bt>&lt;&lt;Even.though these people had violated God2's Law,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa Na saku eele sasala-sasigo si.<bt>nevertheless He wiped away their wrongs (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Nèti èèna ka, rèngu oto titu kèna!<bt>That's why they are most fortunate!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dhèu dhu tao bhabhelu,<bt>People/Person who did/do evil,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lamatua pabhèlu eele sasala si.<bt>God2 has completely forgotten their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarioi: fortunate, in a good state"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">makarioi: fortunate, in a good state of affairs/position/situation (carries through several verses); often badly translated as "happiness"--whereas the element of "happy" is not really part of the meaning of the word, but perhaps a result LITERALLY: How fortunate are those whose lawlessnesses are forgiven, and whose sins are covered up.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Te ladhe Lamatua pa'iga heka sasala dhèu,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if/when God2 no longer counts a person's wrongs, [EXEG: NLT uses “no longer” rather than “not” to be consistent with the higher level argument.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, dhèu sèra oto tare'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>na, those people are truly fortunate!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: How fortunate is the person"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: How fortunate is the person to whom God will not keep account of their sin.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 32:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />De ele boe miu pangee, na, dhodhoka dhèu Yahudi dhu suna di, dhu bisa oto, ho ra pabe'a dènge Lamatua, si? Aa dhèu suku leo dhu suna boe, bisa boe, si? Aad'o! Ngangee sèmi sèra sala! Nèti èèna ka, ji'i dhu peka mema-mema le, lula Abraham parcaya Lamatua, ka Lamatua cap ne, dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Nèngu.<bt>So (consequently) perhaps/probably you-pl are thinking that, only Yahudi people who are circumcised, are the ones who can be fortunate/lucky enough to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, right? And people of other ethnic groups who are not circumcised, can't, right? No! Thinking like that is wrong! That is why we-exc have reminded you-pl before, that, because Abraham believed in God2, God2 stamped/marked him as a straight insides (=righteous) person who is in a reciprocally good relationship with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Does this happiness come only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Does this happiness come only to the circumcised, or to the uncircumcised also? For we say that faith was credited to Abraham as righteousness.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Lod'o mia Lamatua cap Abraham sèmi èèna? Lod'o dhu na suna le, do dhae? Dhu mola-mola, nuka lèke lod'o dhu na suna mèka.<bt>When did God2 stamp/mark Abraham like that? [Was it] when he was already circumcised, or not yet? What is correct, is before he had been circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lèke boe lod'o na suna le,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lèke boe lod'o na suna le, te ngaa lod'o dhu na suna mèka.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then how was it credited?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then how was it credited? When he was circumcised, or uncircumcised? Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tare'a! Lod'o Abraham suna mèka, Ama Lamatua cap nare le nèngu dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Lamatua. Nèbhu ku, heka na suna kèna, ho j'aj'i tadha, na, nèngu j'aj'i le dhèu dhu lèka Lamatua. Dènge sèmi èèna ka, Abraham j'aj'i dhèu oti j'ara hia dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Lamatua. Te Lamatua sèmi nare dhèu dhu parcaya, ho ra pabe'a dènge Lamatua, masi ka ra suna, do aad'o.<bt>Really! When Abraham was not yet circumcised, God had already stamped/marked him, a straight insides (=righteous) person who was in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. Eventually, only.then did he get circumcised as a sign that he was a person who believed in God2. In that way, Abraham was the person who opened the way for all people who believe in God2. Cuz (elaboration) God2 accepts people who believe in Him, so that they (can be) in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, whether they are circumcised, or not.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oti j'ara = rintis jalan (the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">oti j'ara = rintis jalan (the first one to cut a path through the virgin forest)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He received the sign of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He received the sign of circumcision [later], a proof of the righteousness by faith which he had before he was circumcised, that he might be the father of all who believe, even though uncircumcised, and are accepted as righteous.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 17:10</note><v n="12" />Abraham bhoke j'ara kahèi hia èdhi dhèu Yahudi dhu suna le. Lula boe nèti èdhi suna, te ngaa lula èdhi parcaya Kristus sama sèmi Abraham parcaya Lamatua lod'o dhu na suna mèka.<bt>Abraham also opened the way for us-exc Yahudi people who are circumcised. Not <span class="Italic">because</span> we are circumcised, but because we believe in Kristus the same as Abraham believed in God2 when he was not yet circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the father of circumcision"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the father of circumcision to them who are not of the circumcision only, but who walk in the steps of that faith of our father Abraham, which he had when he was still uncircumcised.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe èdhi lèka Ama Lamatua, èdhi sèmi tare ngaa dhu Na pajaji<bt>If we-inc believe in God, we receive what He promises</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ama Lamatua dhu pa'èki pajaji dènge Abraham, dènge ana-èpu na, peka na, nèbhu-nèbhu rai-haha kateme j'aj'i mi pusaka rèngu. Lamatua pajaji sèmi èèna, lula Abraham parcaya Ne, aa Lamatua cap ne dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Ne. Te ngaa Lamatua pajaji boe sèmi èèna, ladhe dhoka Abraham tao madhutu Atora Lamatua.<bt>God had bound a promise with Abraham and his descendants, saying, eventually the whole world would become their inheritance. God2 promised like that, because Abraham believed in Him, and/so God2 stamped/branded/categorised him, as a *righteous person who was in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. But God2 didn't promise like that, because Abraham was doing according to/obeying God2's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the promise that he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the promise that he would be the heir of the world was to Abraham, and his [offspring/children], not through the Law, but through the righteousness of faith.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 17:4-6, 22:17-18, Galati 3:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Te ladhe dhèu dhu madhutu dhoka Atora Lamatua di, bisa sèmi rare pusaka dhu Lamatua moa, sasoa na, parcaya mi Lamatua parcuma di. Aa lii pajaji Lamatua èèna guna boe ngaa-ngaa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if a person who only follows God2's Law can receive the inheritance which God promised, that means that, belief in God2 is just pointless/ineffectual. And that aforementioned promise of God2's, doesn't have any use/worth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if they who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if they who are of the Law be heirs, faith is made [void/no good], and the promise made worthless.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galati 3:18</note><v n="15" />Ètu era mia abhu Atora Lamatua, ètu èèna kahèi dhèu sisu Atora èèna. Aa ladhe dhèu sisu Atora Lamatua, na, Lamatua nasa, hèia Na huku si. Aa ladhe Atora Lamatua aad'o, tatu dhèu sisu boe.<bt>Wherever God2's Law exists, there also people violate that Law. And if people violate His Law, na, God2 gets angry, and then He punishes them. And2 if God2's Law doesn't exist, (then) surely no person violates (it).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** ètu èèna kahèi dhèu aa'i-aa'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">*** ètu èèna kahèi dhèu aa'i-aa'i sisu Atora èèna</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the Law produces wrath,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the Law produces wrath, for where there is no law, there is no [disobeying of the Law / transgression / sin].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Nèti èèna ka, èdhi hud'i parcaya ku Lamatua. Èèna ka dhu risi eele nèti aa'i-aa'i. Te Lamatua d'èi pad'elo dènge mola-mola d'ara hua iia Na mi dhèu dhu parcaya Ne. Aa ladhe èdhi lèka Ne, sama sèmi Abraham, tatu èdhi abhu ngaa dhu Na moa, masi ka èdhi dhèu Yahudi dhu tao madhutu Atora Na, do aad'o. De èdhi aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Ne, sama sèmi ana-èpu Abraham.<bt>That's why we-inc must believe in God2. That is more important than everything. Cuz (elaboration) God2 likes to show His good insides (=grace) freely/ straight/without.embellishment to people who believe in Him. [CHECK adverbial phrase] And if/when we-inc believe in Him like Abraham [did], surely we will receive what He promised, whether we are Yahudi people who follow His Law/Regulations, or not. So (consequently), all of us who believe in Him, are like Abraham's descendants (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dènge mola-mola = dengan tulus, ikhlas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dènge mola-mola = dengan tulus, ikhlas, tidak sembunyi2</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="monos: we assume talks of Jews"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">monos: we assume talks of Jews with two options: be of the Law only, or also believe. It does not contrast two groups, one who is of the Law and rejects faith, and one who accepts both. If it were the latter, if would contradict verse 14. LITERALLY: Therefore it is of faith, that it might be by grace, so that the promise might be certain to all the offspring, not the one who is of the Law only, but also of the faith of Abraham, who is the father of us all.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galati 3:7</note><v n="17" />Lamatua dhu peka tèke le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a ad'u-ue sèna ka èu j'aj'i bèi-baki nèti suku ae-ae.&gt;&gt; Abraham parcaya Ama Lamatua. Nèbhu-nèbhu ka Ama Lamatua tao paj'aj'i lii moa Na. Nèngu kahèi dhu pamamuri hari dhèu madhe. Lamatua dhoka padhai lii di, ka ngaa-ngaa dhu aad'o, j'aj'i dènge.<bt>God2 has said beforehand in His Clean/Holy Writings, saying, &lt;&lt;I will do/arrange.things so.that you-sg become the ancestor of many ethnic groups.&gt;&gt; Abraham believed God. Eventually God made His promise happen/fulfilled. He also was the one who made dead people live again. God2 only needs to just speak, and/so things which don't exist, happen/come into being straightaway.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao paj'aj'i lii pajaji Na."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tao paj'aj'i lii pajaji Na.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "I have made you a father of many nations." Before him whom he believed, God, who makes the dead live, and calls those things which are not as though they were.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 17:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Masi ka Abraham dènge mèka ana, te ngaa na lèka Ama Lamatua, aa tatae Lamatua tao madhutu lii pajaji Na. Nèti parcaya èèna ka, Lamatua tao ne j'aj'i mi &lt;&lt;bèi-baki nèti suku ae-ae.&gt;&gt; Èèna nuka sèmi dhu suri ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, na, &lt;&lt;Ana-èpu ae-ae bèli-camèd'a mai nèti èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even though Abraham himself did not yet have a child, nevertheless he believed (in) God1, and waited (doublet--expectantly or continually-reduplication can signal either) for God2 to do according to His promise, Because of his belief, God2 made him become &lt;&lt;many ethnic groups' ancestor.&gt;&gt; That is the same as what is written in the Holy/Clean Writings, saying, &lt;&lt;Many descendants will later come from you-sg.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ca nau-ca nadha ; Q: dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ca nau-ca nadha ; Q: dhèu ae, do? A: oo. Dhèu ae aae. (sangat banyak orang/orang banyak batúl)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who against hope believed in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who against hope believed in hope, that he might become the father of many nations, according to that which was spoken, "So shall your offspring be."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 15:5</note><v n="19" />Abraham lèka èra Lamatua, masi ka ne'a nèngu dhu heka bhora le, umur dhu cangasu tèu kèna. Era ana nèti Sara dhu bèdho mèno le, aa na heka d'ai seli le.<bt>Abraham believed2 strongly in God2, even.though he knew he was old and wrinkled, already one hundred years (old). And Sara's child place (=womb) was closed up dry (=she was barren), and she also was terribly old. [NOTE for daughter translations: she was always barren, so avoid impression that she simply became barren due to old age. See NLT. CHECK collocations: e.g. Gk “womb is dead”; KM “womb is dry”; BI “womb is closed”; Dhao “womb is closed tight”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèdho mèno = (UNS mandul) tutup"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">bèdho mèno = (UNS mandul) tutup mati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was not weak in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was not weak in faith, he did not consider his own body, now [like] dead, because he was about a hundred years old, nor even the deadness of Sarah's womb.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 17:17</note><v n="20" />Te ngaa lalèka Abraham kura boe, ho pangee na, Lamatua bisa boe tao madhutu lii padadha Na. Parcaya na asa tabha èra mi Lamatua, aa na ded'e padedha kolongara Lamatua.<bt>But Abraham's faith2 was not lacking [CHECK lex], to think that God2 could not do according to His promise. His faith/belief in God2 continued to increase and/as he lifted up high (=*glorified) God2's name/reputation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hali = kurang (kuno)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">hali = kurang (kuno)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did not stagger at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did not stagger at God's promise through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Abraham lèka tare'a-re'a, ngaa dhu Lamatua padhadha le, Nèngu bisa tao.<bt>Abraham was really certain that, what God2 had promised, He was capable of doing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was fully persuaded that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was fully persuaded that what he had promised he was also able to do.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua cap Abraham, peka na, dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Nèngu.<bt>That's why God stamped/marked Abraham, a straight insides (=righteous) person who was in a reciprocally good.relationship with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And therefore it was credited"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And therefore it was credited to him as righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua peka na, Lamatua ige boe sèmi èèna hia Abraham mesa na,<bt>But God2's Holy/Clean Writings say, God2 doesn't/didn't count like just for Abraham, [NOTE to daughter translations: /itong/ works in KM for moral reckoning, but CHECK that it's equivalent in the vernacular also has that secondary use.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now it was not recorded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now it was not recorded for his sake alone that it was credited to him,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />te ngaa mi èdhi kahèi! Te ladhe èdhi parcaya Lamatua, Na cap èdhi kahèi dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Ne. Lamatua ka dhu pamamuri hari Kètu èdhi, Yesus nèti mamadhe Na.<bt>but for us-inc also! Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc believe in God2, He also stamps/marks us straight insides (=righteous) persons who are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. God2 is the one who brought back to life our-inc Head/Leader Yesus from His death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but for us also, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but for us also, to whom it shall be credited, if we believe in the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Yesus madhe, lula èdhi ad'u-ue sasala-sasigo. Hèia Na mamuri hari, ho bhoke j'ara, sèna ka èdhi bisa pabe'a hari dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>Yesus died, because of our-inc doing (doublet) wrong/sin (doublet). Then (seq) He lived again to open the way/path for us-inc to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who was delivered [to die]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who was delivered [to die] for our [offences/ wrongdoings/ sins], and was raised again for our justification.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu bisa pabe'a hari dènge Ama Lamatua sad'i dhoka ra parcaya Yesus Kristus<bt>People can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God as long as they believe in Yesus Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />De, lula èdhi parcaya Ama Lamatua, nèti èèna ka Na cap èdhi dhèu d'ara mola. Hèia d'ara èdhi j'aj'i mola-mèci hia Lamatua, lula Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, dhu Lamatua pua mai, bhoke j'ara ho èdhi bisa padame dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently), because we-inc believe in God, that's why He stamps/brands us as people with straight (righteous) insides. Then our insides are/become clean/holy (doublet) toward God2, because our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent, has opened the path/way so.that we-inc could be in a reciprocally peaceful/restored relationship with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireeneen ekhomen pros ton theon: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">eireeneen ekhomen pros ton theon: the idea of a pono relationship, everything just as it should be. Like Hebrew shalom. LITERALLY: Therefore since we are justified by faith, we have peace [with/toward] God through our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kristus pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi, lula èdhi parcaya le Nèngu. Nèti èèna ka, d'ara èdhi j'aj'i èra. Aa d'ara èdhi karae kahèi, lula te'a, na, bèli-camèd'a Lamatua neo ded'e èdhi, sèna ka te'a mèu dadedha Na.<bt>Kristus showed us-inc his good insides (grace), because we have believed in Him. That's why our-inc insides are/become strong. And we also have joyful/happy insides, because we know that, later God2 wants to lift us up to know/experience His high-ness/glory. [EXEG: Gk genitive here famous for its complexity. See Fee &amp; Strauss 2007.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By whom [Christ] also we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By whom [Christ] also we have access by faith into this grace in which we stand, and rejoice in hope of the glory of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Masi ka èdhi abhu rupa-rupa sasusa, te ngaa d'ara èdhi karej'e-karae taruu. Te èdhi te'a, na, j'èra uuru ku heka bisa taha dènge èra risi hari.<bt>Even though we-inc get/experience all.sorts.of difficulties, nevertheless our-inc insides are happy/rejoicing (doublet) continually. Cuz (elaboration) we know that, there is suffering first, before we can endure/persevere even more strongly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And not only that, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And not only that, but we glory in troubles also, knowing that troubles produce patience,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ladhe èdhi èra ka ètu d'ara j'aj'èra, èèna ka dhu tao èdhi manahu boe, aa mamuri èdhi pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua. Ladhe èdhi mamuri sèmi èèna, èèna ka dhu pa'èra parcaya èdhi, peka na, pe Lamatua neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi.<bt>If we-inc endure in difficulty/suffering, that makes us not fall (morally), and our lives please God2's insides. If we live like that, it makes us believe more strongly, that, later God2 will show his good insides (=grace) to us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and patience, experience, and experience,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and patience, experience, and experience, hope,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ladhe lalèka èdhi asa èra sèmi èèna, èdhi makae boe. Te Lamatua dhu bagi le hia èdhi, Roh Na dhu Mola-Mèci, sèna ka èdhi te'a mèu, na, Nèngu dhu sue èdhi titu kèna.<bt>If we our-inc faith2 becomes increasingly stronger like that, we are not embarrased/ashamed. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has already given us His Holy Spirit, so.that we can know clearly, that, He has lots of love for us. [EXEG: kataischunei: put to shame, but SSA "has more the sense of ‘be disappointed’ than ‘be put to shame’ (BAGD, p. 410.3a), but specifically it means to be humiliated because the source of one’s faith has been shown to be inadequate"][NOTE to daughter translations: if “know in our hearts” is heavy as a Hebraism, just use “know well/understand deeply”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and hope does not disappoint"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and hope does not disappoint us, because God has poured out his love into our hearts by the Holy Spirit, who is given to us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Nèngu pad'elo sasue Na sèmi ne'e ka: ropa èdhi mampu boe pabe'a dènge Lamatua, te'a boe, na, Lamatua dhu pua Kristus madhe pala èdhi. Te ngaa èdhi dhu mamuri pusi-pahae boe Lamatua. Lamatua pili lod'o dhu lèke sèna ka tao aa'i-aa'i sèra.<bt>He shows/ed His love like this: when we-inc still were not capable of making ourselves in right.relationship with God2 [SSA, high level], contrary-to-expectation, God2 sent Kristus to die for us. But we were living without caring.about/ paying.attention.to (doublet) God2. God2 chose the appropriate time to do all those things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aseboon: ungodly LITERALLY: For when we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">aseboon: ungodly LITERALLY: For when we were still without strength, at the right time Christ died for the ungodly.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Pangee paie-iie ku! Te cadhui ku abhu dhèu dhu sadia madhe hia angalai na dhu d'ara mola. Ele boe abhu dhèu cahag'e dhu sadia madhe, ho soru dhèu d'ara be'a.<bt>Think carefully! Cuz (elaboration) it is difficult for there to be a person who is prepared to die for his straight insides (=righteous) friend/companion. Maybe there are some people who are prepared to die to help people/person who has a good insides. [EXEG: Note the progression is downward to show the exceptional nature of God's love. 7a “righteous person”, 7b “good person”, 8 “still full-blown sinners”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cadhui = sulit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">cadhui = sulit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because a person will hardly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because a person will hardly die for a righteous person. But maybe some would even dare to die for a good person.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te ngaa Ama Lamatua pad'elo le sasue Na ae-ae mi dedha èdhi. Lula, lod'o èdhi mamuri ètu d'ara sasala era, Kristus madhe le gati èdhi.<bt>But God has shown His abundant love for us-inc. Because, when we-inc were still living doing wrong/sin, Kristus died in our place/to exchange us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But God has shown how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But God has shown how much he loves us, in that, while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ama Lamatua cap èdhi, dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Ne, lula Kristus pasuti raa Na, sèna ka madhe gati èdhi. Aa te ngaa, ladhe dhèu ue sasala, Lamatua nasa. Te ngaa nèti mamadhe Kristus, èdhi dhu tao sala abhu heka huku.<bt>God stamped/marked us as straight insides (=righteous) people who are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, because Kristus spilled His blood (for a purpose) to die for us. However/Whereas.in.actual.fact, if a person does wrong/sins, God gets angry. But with the death of Kristus', we who do wrong do not get punished anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since we are now justified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since we are now justified by his blood, we will much more be saved from wrath through him.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2011-12-15 12:04:25Z">lula</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Uru èèna, èdhi pamusu dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa Ana Ama Lamatua mesa Na madhe, ho cuhi d'ara Lamatua, sèna ka èdhi bisa padame dènge Lamatua. De limuri ne, èdhi pamusu heka, te ngaa pabe'a hari le. Risi-risi hari, Kristus dhu mamuri hari le, pe d'ai lod'o èle rai-haha ne, Na hia èdhi mamuri, sèna ka èdhi baku lèke hahuku.<bt>Previously, we were in an enemy relationship with God2. But, God's own Child died to cool God2's insides (idiom: remove reason for anger and damaged relationship), so that we can be restored/peaceful relationship with God2. So (consequently), now, we-inc are not in an enemy relationship anymore, but restored to a right relationship. Even more so, because Kristus came back to life, later at the end of the world He will also save/deliver us to not get/experience punishment anymore. [EXEG: NLT, SSA, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if, when we were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, much more, being reconciled, we will be saved by his life.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Mesa boe èèna di! D'ara èdhi bisa karae, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua ne, dedha risi eele!&gt;&gt; lula èdhi pa'èki dènge Ne. Èdhi bisa j'aj'i dhèu unu Na, lula Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, madhe le pala èdhi, sèna ka èdhi padame dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>Not just that! Our-inc insides can rejoice, saying, &lt;&lt;God2, is above all/highest/glorious!&gt;&gt; because we-inc are bound/linked with Him. We can become His people, because Yesus Kristus, our Head/Leader has died for us, to make us in a peace.relationship with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katallagee: reconciliation, be one of his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">katallagee: reconciliation, be one of his guys LITERALLY: And not only that, but we also rejoice/boast in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom we have now received the atonement.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe èdhi pasoro Adam dènge Kristus, abhu dhu sama, aa abhu dhu sama boe<bt>If/When we-inc compare Adam and Kristus, there are similarities, and there are differences</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />De karèi nèti uuru èèna ka, Adam ka dhu tao uru sasala-sasigo. Nèti èèna ka, Ama Lamatua hia boe ne mamuri taruu. Hèia karèi nèti lod'o èèna ka, dhèu aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne madhutu ad'u-ue sasala kahèi, èci èèna ka dènge nèngu. Aa, lula rèngu tao sala sama sèmi Adam, ka rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra hud'i madhe ku nuka sèmi nèngu kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), beginning from long ago, Adam was the first one who did wrong/sin (doublet). That's why God didn't allow him to keep living continually. So starting from that time, all people in this world also follow doing wrong, the same as him. And because they do wrong the same as Adam, they all also must die the same as him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because sin came into the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because sin came into the world by one man [Adam], and death by sin, and so death passed to all men, because all have sinned. dià tóuto: therefore. It's not clear if it refers to Verses 1-11, or just to Verse 11, or to everything from 1:17 up to 5:11<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>hoósper: Everybody since Adam has made the same kind of bad choice Adam made, back at the beginning. They all ended up sinning by just the same process as Adam ended up sinning hoútoos: in this way, as a result<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>diéelthen: spread throughout the human race -- not genetically, just because we are human and the first real human somehow screwed up our genes, or let loose some kind of moral virus, but because practically speaking, all the rest of us have fallen into the same trap as Adam, of not wanting to do things God's way</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 3:6</note><v n="13" />Uru-uru sèra, lod'o Ama Lamatua papuru mèka Atora Na, dhèu tao le sasala dhu pale-lème le rai-haha ne. Te ngaa, lula dènge mèka Atora, ka abhu boe dhu ige sasala-sasigo dhèu sèra.<bt>Long ago, when God had not yet handed down His Laws, people already did/doing wrongs throughout this entire world. But because there was not yet (the) Law, there was no one who counts/keeps track of people's wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For until the Law, sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For until the Law, sin was in the world. But sin is not kept account of when there is no Law. ellogéitai: it is not the practice to keep account; a bookkeeping term. God is the one who keeps track of such things, if we need to provide a subject<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Mulai nèti Adam toke d'ai Musa sèmi rare Atora Lamatua èèna, dhèu aa'i-aa'i tatu madhe. Masi ka rèngu sisu boe paredha Lamatua dhu pangèd'u mi Adam, te ngaa ra tao rupa-rupa sasala. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu hud'i madhe ku, nuka sèmi Adam.<bt>Beginning from Adam until Musa received God2's Law, all people surely died. Even.if they didn't violate God2's command(s) which He gave/entrusted to Adam, nevertheless they did various sorts of wrongs. That's why they must die, the same as Adam.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ladhe èdhi pasoro Adam dènge Lamatua Yesus, abhu dhu sama, aa abhu dhu sama boe. Te Adam èci èèna ka dènge rupa dhu paj'uj'u asa raropa Yesus, dhu bèli-camèd'a èèna cèu mai.<bt>So then! If we-inc compare Adam with the Lord Yesus, there are similarities, and there are differences. Cuz (elaboration) Adam was also like a form/picture which showed Yesus's model/form/ type, which would appear later on.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="potoree = photo ; raropa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">potoree = photo ; raropa = model, type, form, (UNS: citra, duplikat)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But death reigned from Adam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But death reigned from Adam to Moses, even over those who did not sin like Adam by disobeying God's command, who is a picture of the one who is to come. allà: in contrast what you might expect from a case where no records were kept of wrongdoing, everybody died anyway<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>ebasíleusen: death ruled; there was no way to escape it</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Te ngaa sasala Adam, sama boe dènge babe'a dhu Yesus hia èdhi. Te dhèu èci, nuka Adam, sisu paredha Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra hud'i madhe ku. Te ngaa Dhèu èci hari, nuka Yesus Kristus, tao rupa-rupa babe'a hia mi èdhi, aa pamata boe dhèu b'ala babe'a Na. Nèti tatao ca Dhèu ne'e ka, pad'ai mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra, te Ama Lamatua d'èi tao be'a hia èdhi.<bt>But Adam's wrong, were not the same as Yesus's goodness for/toward us-inc. Cuz (elaboration) the one person, that is Adam, was violating God2's command(s). That's why all people must die. But the other Person, that is Yesus Kristus, did all sorts of good deeds for us, and didn't keep waiting for people to reciprocate His goodness. From this one Person's deeds, were sufficient for all people, cuz (elaboration) God2 likes to do deeds which are good toward/for us-inc. [NOTE to daughter translations: if 1st sentence “not the same as” doesn't fly in your RL, try “different from”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pamata = tunggu ; padai ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pamata = tunggu ; padai = bekin cukup (mencukupkan)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the offense is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the offense is not the same as the free gift. For if by the offense of one, many have died, much more the grace of God, and the gift by grace, which is by one man, Jesus Christ, has been more than enough for many. paráptooma: the result of getting out of line<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>chárisma: the result of God treating us graciously dooreà: for free, no charge, not asking for anything in return<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>eperisseusen: abound, have more than enough for, sufficient</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Dhu Ama Lamatua pangèd'u mi èdhi, sama boe dènge sasala dhu Adam tao èèna. Ropa Adam tao sasala, Ama Lamatua pama'ète lii langu, peka na &lt;&lt;Èu sala. De èu hud'i abhu huku!&gt;&gt; Te ngaa masi ka dhèu ue sasala ae titu kèna, Ama Lamatua, dhu parisa mamuri dhèu aa'i-aa'i, neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na era, aa pama'ète, na, &lt;&lt;Èu sala boe. De èu bebas le, aa mu abhu heka huku. Mai, sèna ka pabe'a hari dènge Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>The things which God gives/entrusts to us-inc, are not the same as that sin which Adam did. When Adam did wrong, God decided/handed down (legal) decision, saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg are wrong/guilty. So (consequently) you must be punished!&gt;&gt; But, even.though people had already done a lot of wrongs, God, who examines all people's lives, still wants to show His good insides (*grace/goodness/ kindness/generosity), and decide, saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg are not wrong/guilty/you are innocent. So (consequently), now you are free and do not get/experience your punishment anymore. Come [+invite] be in a reciprocally good relationship again with Me!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And there is a difference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And there is a difference between God's gift and the sin of one person. After the one sin came the judgment of 'Guilty'. But after so many sins comes the undeserved judgment of 'Not Guilty'.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />De ca dhèu nuka Adam dhu tao sala, aa sisu paredha Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, limuri ne dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i madhe ku. Te ngaa Dhèu èci hari, nuka Yesus Kristus dhu tao be'a. Lula tatao Na dhu be'a èèna ka, èdhi bisa pabe'a hari dènge Lamatua. Èèna nuka sèmi mèdha èci dhu Na hia iia d'ara mi èdhi. Na neo hia èdhi mamuri dhu lèke, sama sèmi èdhi j'aj'i angalai Dhèu Aae.<bt>So (consequently), one person, that is Adam, did wrong deed/s, and violated God's command. That's why, now, all people must die. But, one other Person, who was Yesus Kristus, did good. Because of those good deed/s of His, we can be (restored to) a reciprocally good relationship with God2. That is like a thing which he gives.freely to us. He wants to give us true life, as if we are the Raja's friends. [NOTE: don't force Gk. word play on “rule/reign”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if by one man's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if by one man's offense, death ruled by one [Adam], much more they who receive abundance of grace and of the gift of righteousness, shall reign in life by one, Jesus Christ. paraptoómati: not the usual word for doing wrong, but for breaking the rules or getting out of line<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />De nèti ca dhèu dhu ad'u-ue sasala, na bhoke j'ara ho Ama Lamatua babège eele dhèu aa'i-aa'i nèti madha Na. Aa nèti ca Dhèu leo hari dhu tao j'ara dhu lèke, Na bhoke j'ara ho dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa pabe'a hari dènge Lamatua, sèna ka mamuri mola dènge Ne.<bt>So (consequently), one person doing wrong, opened the way/path for God to evict all people from His face/presence. And yet with another Person's right.correct deed/s, He opened the way/path so that all people could be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2, in.order.to have true life with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="De, ca dhèu dhu ad'u sasala,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">De, ca dhèu dhu ad'u sasala, na bhoke j'ara ho dhèu aa'i-aa'i lèke babèga eele nèti madha Lamatua.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, as the sin of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, as the sin of one condemned all people, in the same way, the one righteous act sets all people free and gives them life. ára óun: this wraps up the line of thought Paul started in Verse 12<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Madhutu a'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e: Adam ne, ca dhèu dhu d'èi boe nanene Lamatua, ka sisu paredha Lamatua. Aa dhèu ae kahèi madhutu tao sasala, sama sèmi Adam. Aa Yesus ne, ca Dhèu dhu nanene Lamatua, ka tao madhutu dad'èi Lamatua. Nèngu ka dhu bhoke j'ara, sèna ka dhèu ae bisa pabe'a hari dènge Lamatua.<bt>My thinking is like this: that Adam was a person who did not want to listen to/obey God2, so he violated God2's command. And many people have also followed doing wrong, the same as Adam. And this Yesus, was a Person who listened to/obeyed God2, and so did according to God2's will. He is the one who opened the path/way so.that many people can be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as by one person's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as by one person's disobedience, many have been made sinners, so by the obedience of one, many will be made righteous. gàr: further explanation<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>hoósper ... hoútos: just as one thing happened ... in a similar way another thing happened. See note in vs.12 katestátheesan: were put in a position, were made to be something that they weren't before (Acts 7:27 "who made you the ruler and judge?")<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ama Lamatua papuru Atora Na re Musa, ho dhèu aa'i-aa'i re'a mèu, mia dhu sala. Te ngaa ètu mia-mia sasala dhèu asa tabha ae. Ètu èèna kahèi, Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na ae risi hari.<bt>God handed down His Law via Musa, so that all people could know clearly which (of options) are wrong [implied by construction--and which are right]. But people's wrongs increased everywhere. There also God showed His good insides (grace, etc.) even more. [NOTE to daughter translations: if the /di mana ... di situ/ construction is difficult for your RL, try /Ma biar orang pung bekin sala batamba banya, ju Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae lebe banya./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Law was introduced that the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Law was introduced that the wrongdoing might be emphasized. But where sin increased, grace increased more. pareiséelthen: entered in as a factor<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Uru èèna, bhabhelu ètu d'ara dhèu abhu koasa dhu uri rèngu, toke ra tao sasala dhu nèti mamadhe. Te ngaa limuri ne, j'ara be'a dhu Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus tao èèna, Ama Lamatua pake ho pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi. Aa j'ara be'a ne dènge koasa sèna ka ator èdhi kahèi, hèia èdhi bisa pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, aa mamuri mola taruu dènge Ne.<bt>Previously, evil that is/was in a person's insides had power/authority to manage/direct/control them, to the point that they did wrong/sin which carried/brought death (indirect causality). But now, those good thing/s which Yesus Kristus, our Head/Leader has done, God uses to show His good insides (grace) to us. And those good thing/s also have power to arrange/ control us, so we can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God, and have true life with Him forever. [NOTE: “evil in their livers” also sets the stage for ch.7]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That as sin rules by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That as sin rules by death, even so might grace rule by righteousness, [for/leading us to] eternal life by Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi hud'i tèke eele sasala-sasigo, ho mamuri madhutu dad'èi Lamatua<bt>We-inc must leave behind our wrongs, to live according to God2's will</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />De èdhi peka ngaa hari? Ele boe miu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Ama Lamatua pabhèlu eele le sasala èdhi, lula d'ara hua iia Na. Nèti èèna ka, hud'i laa èdhi tino tao sala, sèna ka Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na risi hari mi èdhi.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), what else can we-inc say? You-pl are probably thinking, saying, &lt;&lt;God has completely forgotten our wrongs, because of his goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. That's why just let us-inc keep on doing wrongs/sin, so.that God2 will show His goodness/grace/ kindness/ generosity even more to us.&gt;&gt; [CHECK /tino/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tino = terus-menerus (Lena not know)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tino = terus-menerus (Lena not know) (UNSs OK, Paulina said ‘tambah meningkat’)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What will we say then?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What will we say then? We will continue in sin, that [grace/favor] may increase?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Aad'o sèmi èèna! Lèke boe ladhe èdhi tao sala taruu. Te èdhi dhu pama'ète tare le, peka na, èdhi tèke eele aa'i le sasala-sasigo èdhi. Lula èdhi pa'èki heka dènge bhabhelu-katub'a, èèna nuka sèmi èdhi dhu madhe le! Te dhèu dhu madhe le bisa heka tao sala, si? Ladhe èdhi madhe le, tasamia hari èdhi bisa mamuri ad'u-ue sasala? Bisa boe, sina ma?<bt>No way! It is not appropriate for us to keep doing wrong. Cuz (elaboration) we-inc have decided, that, we already have left behind (abandoned) our wrongs. Because we are no longer bound/linked with/by evil (doublet), that's the same as if we've already died! Cuz (elaboration) people who already dead can't do wrongs anymore, right? If we have already died, how is it that we-inc can live doing wrong? Can't be done, right? [NOTE: explicating ‘death’ required from UNS responses (in Belu). Guided by consultant.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Certainly not! How shall we,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Certainly not! How shall we, who are dead to sin, live any longer in it?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ele boe miu me'a boe, na, ropa sarani èdhi, èèna j'aj'i tadha, na, èdhi tèke eele le mamuri dhui, ho abhu mamuri hiu, nuka dhu pa'èki dènge Yesus Kristus. Èèna sama sèmi èdhi madhe le palere-lere dènge Ne.<bt>Perhaps you don't understand, that, when we-inc were *baptised, it was a sign that we have left behind/abandoned our old/former life, to get new life, that is one who is bound/linked to Yesus Kristus. That is like/as if we have died together with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that “new person” doesn't actually mean “guest who has just arrived”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhèu hiu = (orang baru) tamu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dhèu hiu = (orang baru) tamu yg baru datang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do you not know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do you not know that as many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Lod'o Kristus madhe, ra padhane Ne. Aa lod'o ra sarani èdhi, èèna nuka sèmi èdhi madhe kahèi, tèke eele mamuri dhui, hèia ra padhane èdhi. De Ama Lamatua pake koasa Na dhu kapai aae èèna, ho pamamuri hari Kristus nèti mamadhe Na. Ama Lamatua d'èi ladhe èdhi sèmi tare koasa Na kahèi, ho mamuri hari j'aj'i dhèu dhu hiu.<bt>When Kristus died, they buried Him. And when we were baptized, that was like we also died, leaving behind the old life, and then they (non-referential) buried us. So (consequently) God used His great power to bring Kristus back to life from His death. God also wants us to receive that power of His, to live again as a new person. [EXEG: glory = power here, see NLT, Harrison, Calvin, etc.] [NOTE: This is a "safe" compromise approach to vs. 3-4 that focuses on the symbolism and result of baptism, avoiding the method quagmire that has no consensus among commentators and is bound to generate unhelpful disputes among readers.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore we are buried with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death. That just as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 2:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te èèna sama sèmi èdhi madhe palere dènge Yesus. De èdhi dhu pa'èki dènge Ne, tatu bèli-camèd'a èdhi mamuri hari nèti mamadhe, sama sèmi Nèngu mamuri hari.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that is like we-inc died together with Yesus. So (consequently), we who are bound/linked to Him, surely we-inc also later will live again from death, just like He also came back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei: could be translated &quot;if&quot;, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">ei: could be translated "if", but here it's more like "since this is the way it is" sýmphytoi: grown together, come into a close relationship<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: For if we have been united with him in his death, we will certainly also be united with him in his resurrection.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Uru èèna, èdhi j'aj'i dhèu dhu tao rupa-rupa sasala. Te ngaa mamuri èdhi dhu dhui èèna, madhe le, èci èèna ka dènge paku pamadhe èdhi ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha palere-lere dènge Kristus. Limuri ne, bhabhelu ètu d'ara èdhi dènge heka koasa ho uri èdhi. Limuri ne, èdhi aad'o heka ètu d'ara a'èki sèna ka tao hari sasala. Te èdhi sèmi heka ènu dhu dènge boe hak ho pili neo tao ngaa.<bt>Formerly, we were people who did all.sorts.of wrongs. But our former lives, have died, the same as if they had been nailed killing us on the cross (doublet) together with Kristus. Now, evil in our insides doesn't have any power/authority to manage/control us anymore. Now, we-inc aren't bound to do wrong anymore. Cuz (elaboration) we are no longer like a slave who doesn't have the right to choose what s/he wants to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="a'èki = ikatan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">a'èki = ikatan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that our old"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that our old self was crucified with him, so that the [body of sin/power of the sinful self] might be made powerless, that we should no longer be slaves to sin.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ladhe dhèu dhu madhe le, nèngu bebas le, si? Abhu heka ngaa èci sa laka-seti ne, ho ad'u-ue hari sasala.<bt>If a person is already dead, s/he is already free, right? There is nothing that can force him/her to do (doublet) wrong again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ae nare dara na = su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ae nare dara na = su istirahat ; CHECK all laka-seti (following recent books)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he that is dead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he that is dead is freed from sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />De, lula èèna nuka sèmi èdhi madhe le palere-lere dènge Kristus, na, èdhi parcaya, peka na, bèli-camèd'a èdhi mamuri taruu dènge Ne kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), because that is like we already died together with Kristus, na, we believe that we will also live continually with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lere = antar, ikut dari belakang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lere = antar, ikut dari belakang ; palere = bersama ; palere-lere = padhutu-dhutu (John Baun)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èdhi parcaya, peka na, ladhe èèna"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">èdhi parcaya, peka na, ladhe èèna na èdhi nuka sèmi dhu madhe le palere-lere dènge Kristus, na, èdhi kahèi mamuri taruu dènge Ne.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now if we are dead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now if we are dead with Christ, we believe that we will also live with him.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Èdhi te'a, na, lula Yesus Kristus mamuri hari le nèti mamadhe Na, de Nèngu bisa heka madhe hari. Te abhu boe èci sa dhu dènge koasa ho pamadhe hari Ne.<bt>We know that, because Yesus Kristus has lived again from His death, consequently He will not die again. Cuz (elaboration) there is nothing which has the power to make Him die again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that since Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that since Christ was raised from the dead, he cannot die again. Death has no [control/power] over him.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Na madhe ca tèka èèna ka, ho segi koasa nèti sasala. Te ngaa limuri ne Na mamuri ho pakab'ua Ama Lamatua.<bt>He died one time, to win/overcome the power/authority of wrong/sin. But now, He lives to show honor to God. [NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The death he died, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The death he died, he died to sin once for all. But the life he lives, he lives to God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Miu hud'i tao ku iisi sèmi èèna. Nuka sèmi miu dhu madhe le, nèti èèna ka sasala dènge heka koasa mi dedha miu. De limuri ne, miu hud'i mamuri ku ho pakab'ua Ama Lamatua, lula miu dhu pa'èki le dènge Yesus Kristus.<bt>You-pl also must make/consider yourselves like.that. It's as if you-pl are already dead, that's why wrong doesn't have power over you anymore. So (consequently) now, you must live to show honor to God, because you are bound/linked together with Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the same way, count"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the same way, count yourselves dead to sin but alive to God in Christ Jesus. hoútoos: in the same way as happened with Christ<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bhabhelu ètu d'ara èu dhu dènge koasa. Baku soro tèke bhabhelu èèna ator èu, ka èu dhoka madhutu dad'èi ngi'u aae sèna ka èu tao bhabhelu-katub'a. Te èèna na ngi'u aae èu madhe.<bt>The evil in your insides has power/authority. Don't allow that evil to manage/control you-sg, so you-sg only follow your-sg body's desires to do evil (doublet). Cuz (elaboration) your body will die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not let sin take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not let sin take control of your [earthly/mortal] bodies, that you should obey it and its evil desires. thneetóoi: subject to death<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>soómati: body, but from the Jewish framework Paul writes in he's including the mind, not just biological urges -- "your natural self", "da way you stay", "how you feel"</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Aa baku soro isi èu sèna ka tao j'ara dhu lèke boe, te èèna sala kahèi. Te ngaa pangèd'u mamuri èu mi Ama Lamatua di, sèna ka Nèngu ka dhu uri mamuri èu. Sama sèmi èu dhu madhe le, ka mamuri hari. De pake la mamuri èu kateme aa'i, sèna ka tao j'ara dhu lèke sèra, hia mi Lamatua.<bt>And don't hand.over1 your-sg self to do things which are not right/correct, cuz (elaboration) that also is wrong. But just hand.over2 your self to God, so that He is the one who manages/controls your-sg life. It's as if you had already died, then come back to life. So (consequently) use your entire/whole (focus on effort, not duration) life to do things which are right/correct, for (the benefit of) God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kateme aai (hati) = anteru-anteru ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kateme aai (hati) = anteru-anteru = kateme iisi (diri)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nor surrender any part of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nor surrender any part of your bodies as instruments of unrighteousness for sin; but surrender yourselves to God, as those that are alive from the dead, and the parts of your bodies as instruments of righteousness for God. mélee: individual parts of the body. He's focusing on the different parts because he's really talking about our entire personality, body included<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Baku soro tèke sèna ka sasala ator miu, sama sèmi sasala ka dhu j'aj'i lamatua miu. De limuri ne miu hud'i mamuri madhutu ia ka atora Musa, sèna ka pabe'a hari dènge Ama Lamatua. Te miu dhu mamuri mola le, lula Lamatua dhu pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na mi miu. De limuri ne d'ara hua iia Lamatua ka dhu uri mamuri miu.<bt>Don't allow for wrong/sin to manage/control you-pl, as if wrong/sin had became your-pl boss/master. So (consequently) now, you-pl no longer need to live following/obeying Musa's law to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl are living straightly (=righteously), because God2 has shown His good insides to you-pl. So (consequently) now, that good insides of God2's is what controls/manages your life. [EXEG: SSA, TB. Specify Moses' law, so we're not saying you don't have to follow God's law anymore.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For sin shall not have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For sin shall not have [control/power] over you; for you are not under the law, but under grace. ou kyrieúsei: in the context the future tense has the force of an imperative<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>hypò: dominated by. "because you do not live by what the law tells you you must do, but by the goodness which God has shown you"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi nuka sèmi ènu dhu sab'a madhutu dad'èi Lamatua<bt>We are like a slave who works according to God2's will</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />De tasamia? Ele boe miu ngee, na, &lt;&lt;Èdhi madhutu ia ka atora Musa, ho pabe'a hari dènge Ama Lamatua. De hud'i laa èdhi tao sala taruu di. Te Lamatua neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na era mi èdhi!&gt;&gt; Miu pangee sèmi èèna ka, si? Ja'a pasanèd'e, èèna na sale!<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Perhaps you-pl are thinking, saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc we no longer need to live following/ obeying Moses' law, in.order.to be in a reciprocally good.relationship with God. So (consequently) let's just continue to do wrong/sin. Cuz (elaboration) God2 still wants to show His good liver/heart to us!&gt;&gt; You are thinking like that, right? I'm telling [you], that is wrong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then? Shall we sin,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then? Shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? Certainly not!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ja'a kore upama nèti ènu dènge lamatua na. Ladhe miu soro ngi'u mi ho sab'a hia dhèu èci, na, miu hud'i nanene, aa sab'a madhutu dad'èi na. Te nèngu èèna kètu miu, aa miu j'aj'i ènu na. Sèmi èèna kahèi, miu bisa pili neo madhutu mia. Te miu bisa pili, sèna ka ad'u-ue sasala, hèia miu j'aj'i mi ènu nèti sasala ne. Te ngaa ladhe miu pili sèmi èèna, miu tao iisi mi pacèri nèti Ama Lamatua. Do, miu bisa pili tao dhu lèke, dènge j'aj'i ènu dhu tao madhutu ngaa dhu Lamatua pua mi. Ladhe pili sèmi èèna, miu bisa pabe'a dènge Ne!<bt>I'll take the example of a slave and his/her boss/master. If you-pl hand.over your-pl selves to work for a person, you must listen to/obey (him), and work according to his desires. Cuz (elaboration) s/he is your-pl head/leader. And you-pl, are his/her slave. In the same way also, you can choose which (among choices) you want to follow/obey. Cuz (elaboration) you can choose to do wrong, so you become a slave to that sin. But if you choose like.that, you make yourselves separated apart from God. Or, you can choose to do what is right/true/correct, and become a slave to do what God2 orders you. If you choose like that, you can be/become in a reciprocally good relationship with Him!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Don't you know that whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Don't you know that whoever you surrender yourself to, as servants to obey, you are his servants to obey, whether of sin that leads to death, or obedience that leads to righteousness? eétoi: a pick one or the other choice<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Uru èèna, miu soro tèke sèna ka sasala uri miu, te ngaa limuri ne miu nanene d'ara iiki miu, sèna ka tao madhutu ngaa dhu dhèu sarani aj'a-nori miu. Nèti èèna ka ja'a manèngi makasi mi Lamatua.<bt>Formerly, you allowed wrongs to be what controlled/managed you, but now you are hearing/ listening.to your inner insides (=conscience), to do according to what the sarani (=Christian) people teach you. That's why I give thanks to God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thank God that you were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thank God that you were servants of sin, but you have obeyed from the heart that form of teaching which was given to you. eis hòn paredótheete: you started to obey the kind of teaching that was passed on to you<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te Lamatua dhu patalale le miu nèti koasa sasala, toke sasala sèra uri heka miu. De limuri ne, j'ara dhu lèke ka dhu uri miu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who has freed you-pl from the power of wrong/sin, to.the point that wrong/sin no longer manages/controls you-pl. So (consequently) now, right/correct things are what controls/ manages you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have been set free"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have been set free from sin and have become servants to righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ja'a peka ne'e, pake conto dhu j'aj'i bèli-bèli, nèti lamatua dènge ènu, sèna ka miu me'a malai ngaa dhu ja'a peka-padhai. Uru èèna, miu hia ngi'u miu j'aj'i ènu sèna ka tao sala, dhu pakaj'alu miu madhutu atora Musa. Te ngaa limuri ne, miu hud'i hia ngi'u miu j'aj'i ènu dhu me'a dhoka tao dhu be'a di, dhu hia miu j'aj'i dhèu mola-mèci ètu madha Ama Lamatua.<bt>I am speaking here, using an everyday example from/about a boss/master and slave, so.that you can quickly/easily understand what I am saying. Formerly, you-pl handed.over your selves to be/ become slaves to do wrong, which made you dirty/defiled according to Moses' law. But now, you must hand.over your selves to become slaves who only know how to do what is right/correct/true, which brings/leads you to become clean/holy (doublet) people in God2's face (=view). [NLT + HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarkos: &quot;make yoaself be da kine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">sarkos: "make yoaself be da kine peopo dat ..." may be another solution for the "body" metonymy. LITERALLY: I speak in human terms because of the weakness of your natural selves. Because just as you surrendered the parts of your bodies as servants for uncleanness that leads to sin after sin, so now surrender the parts of your bodies as servants to righteousness that leads to holiness.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>sarkòs: your human nature, your natural selves eis: the expected goal<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Uru èèna, ropa miu dhoka nanene aa tao madhutu dad'èi sasala, miu mo'o boe nanene aa tao dhu lèke.<bt>Previously, when you only heard/obeyed and did according to the desires of sin/wrong, you didn't want to hear and do what was right/correct/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when you were servants"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when you were servants of sin, you were free from righteousness.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: Miu abhu ngaa dhu be'a nèti tatao miu sèra? Aad'o, sina ma? Aa te ngaa, ngaa dhu miu abhu sèra tao miu mi'e makae di. Lula miu tao sala sèmi èèna, ka dhu miu abhu, nuka Lamatua soro kabodho mi miu.<bt>So (consequently) I want to ask like this: What good results have you gotten from those deeds of yours? There's nothing, right? In.actual.fact, what you got, just makes you eat embarrassment/shame. Because of your doing wrong like that, what you get, is that God2 turns his back on you. [NOTE to daughter translations: Make sure it is clear that /bosong pung bekin-bekin/ in KM is strongly s.t. that is socially or morally wrong. MTT's only partly proficient in KM may not pick this up.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ka dhu miu unu, = what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ka dhu miu unu, = what you get</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What [fruit/good] did you have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What [fruit/good] did you have then from the things you are ashamed of now? Because the end of those things is death.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Te ngaa limuri ne, Ama Lamatua patalale eele le miu nèti lamatua uru èèna, de miu parluu ia ka tao sasala. De ne'e ne miu hud'i j'aj'i ku dhèu sab'a nèti Ama Lamatua. Lèpa lod'o limuri, pe miu j'aj'i mola-mèci hia Ne, aa abhu mamuri mola-mèci dhu d'ai mia-mia.<bt>But now, God has freed you from your former boss/ master, so you no longer need to do wrong. So (consequently) now you must become God's working people (=workers). In the end, you will be/become clean/holy (doublet) for (the benefit of) Him, and have true life which goes on forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now you have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now you have been made free from sin, and have become servants of God, you have your fruit that leads to holiness, and the end eternal life.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Te ropa èdhi tao sasala, Lamatua tule eele èdhi toke d'ai mia-mia. Èèna ka dhu èdhi abhu. Èdhi madhe kèna! Te ngaa Ama Lamatua bhoke le j'ara èci hia èdhi. Te Na neo hia iia èdhi mamuri mola dhu ma'ète boe. Èdhi abhu mamuri èèna, ladhe èdhi j'aj'i dhèu unu Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when we do/did wrong, God2 rejects us forever. That's what we get. We're dead [+idiomatic, emphatic]! But God has opened a way for us. Cuz (elaboration) He wants to freely give us true life which doesn't ever end. We get that life, if/when we become our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus' person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the wages of sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the wages of sin is death. But the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe dhèu madhe le, atora huku dènge heka hak<bt>If a person has died, legal regulations no longer have rights/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a neo padhai lii dènge miu dhu me'a mèu atora huku sèra. Sèmi ne'e ka: ladhe miu mamuri era, atora huku dènge hak ho ator miu. Te ngaa ladhe miu madhe le, atora huku dènge heka hak mi miu.<bt>Siblings! I want to speak to you-pl who clearly understand Moses' legal regulations. It's like this: if/when you-pl are still alive, legal regulations have the right to control/manage you. But if you are already dead, legal regulations no longer have the right to control you. [NOTE to daughter translations: Personification “regs controlling us” works in KM, and should be adjusted in Daughter Translations only if personification doesn't work. Not simply because they are personification.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, I am speaking to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, I am speaking to those who know (the) law. Don't you know that the law has authority over a person as long as he lives? èe agnoéite ... ginoóskousin: I am assuming you know how laws in general work -- they apply to living people, not dead people<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nómon: law in general, not specifically Jewish or Roman</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ja'a kore pakasame nèti atora dhèu èmu-kamali. Ladhe dhèu bhèni èci leo le èmu dènge mone èci, na, madhutu atora huku, dua ra j'aj'i dhèu èmu-kamali toke madhe. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu mone madhe uuru, bhèni balu ne pa'èki heka dènge atora deo na. Nèngu bisa hari leo-èmu.<bt>I'll take an example from husband-wife regulations. If a woman has married with a husband, na, according to legal regulations, the two of them are husband-wife until death. But if her husband dies first, that widow is no longer bound/tied to that just-mentioned regulation/law. She may marry again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leo èmu = kawin (leo le"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">leo èmu = kawin (leo le èmu) ; ladhe ka = andaikata</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the woman who has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the woman who has a husband is bound to the living husband by law. But if the husband dies, she is released from the law concerning the husband.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te ngaa ladhe bhèni ne leo hari èmu lod'o dhèu èmu na mamuri era, nèngu bersina. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu èmu na madhe le, atora nèti laleo èmu lèke heka nèngu. Bhèni ne j'aj'i dhèu kalora iisi. De ladhe na madhèdi hari dènge dhèu leo, madhutu atora, nèngu bersina boe.<bt>But if this woman marries with another/different person when her husband is still living, na, she is committing adultery. But if her husband is already dead, the marriage regulations don't affect her anymore. That woman is a free person. So (consequently) if she marrys2 another person, na, according to the regulation/law, she is not committing adultery.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="laleo èmu = perkawinan ; kalora"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">laleo èmu = perkawinan ; kalora iisi = sendiri (bebas in this context)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then, if she marries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then, if she marries another man while her husband is living, she will be called an adulteress. But if her husband is dead, she is free from the law, and if she marries another man, she is not an adulteress. géneetai andrì hetérooi: can be applied to marriage, as it is later in this verse, but in the first part it implies the woman leaving her husband and shacking up with somebody else<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>chreemaatísei: she is acting like an adulteress, is recognized as one</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge miu dhèu parcaya! Sèmi ne'e: Kristus madhe le. Èèna nuka sèmi miu madhutu madhe dènge Ne kahèi, hèia tèke eele mamuri miu dhu dhui. Ka atora huku lèke heka mi miu. Limuri ne atora huku lèke heka miu, te ngaa mamuri miu pa'èki dènge Kristus, dhu mamuri hari nèti mamadhe Na. Èèna cakaraa dènge bhèni balu dhu leo hari èmu. Ngaa-ngaa tao boe. De limuri ne aa'i-aa'i dhu miu ad'u-ue sèra, hia mi Lamatua.<bt>It's like that also with you believers! Like this: Kristus died. That is like you also have died together with Him, and have left behind your old/former lives. And/So the legal regulations no longer affect/apply.to you. Now they no longer effect you, Law, [contrary to expectation] your lives are tied/bound together with Kristus, who has already come back to life again from His death. [CHECK this previous sentence. It comes across to me as almost non-sensical.] That is the same as a widow who marries again. There's no problem. So (consequently) now, everything which you do, is for God2. [CHECK /cakaraa/] [EXEG: some commentators see this as applying broader than just to Jewish law so don't restrict vs.4-6.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, my brothers, you also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, my brothers, you also have become dead to the law by the body of Christ, that you should belong to another, to the one who is raised from the dead, that we should produce fruit for God. tóoi nómooi: as far as the law is concerned -- again, not just the Jewish law, but whatever cultural rules you live under<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te uru èèna, èdhi tao dhoka madhutu dad'èi ngi'u aae èdhi di. Lula èdhi te'a atora, èèna ka dhu hia èdhi sisu atora sèra, ho tao j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke boe. De sasala èdhi sèra ka dhu tao Ama Lamatua soro kabodho mi èdhi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) formerly, we-inc only just did according to our-inc own desires/passions. Because we know the regulation/s, that makes us (weak causation) like to violate those regulations, to do things which are not right/correct. So (consequently) those wrongs of ours, are what causes God turn his back on us. [SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when we were [in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when we were [in the flesh/controlled by our sinful nature], the sinful passions, which were by the law, worked in our [members/bodies] to produce fruit for death. dià tóu nómou: the law made us want to do bad things, and this determined what we did with our bodies<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Uru èèna, èdhi hud'i tao madhutu ku atora. Te ngaa limuri ne, atora ne lèke heka èdhi, dhu tèke eele le mamuri dhu dhui. Madhutu dad'èi j'ara dhui, na, Atora Musa dhu suri ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci èèna, dhu èki tèke èdhi. Te ngaa madhutu dad'èi j'ara hiu, na, èdhi pa'èki heka dènge atora èèna. Te Roh Lamatua ka dhu uri èdhi! Nèti èèna ka, limuri ne èdhi sab'a dhoka hia Lamatua.<bt>Formerly, we had to do according to the regulation/s. But now the regulation/s doesn't apply to us anymore, who have left behind/abandoned our old lives. Following the desires of the old way, na, Moses' Law/Regulation(s) which are written in the Clean/Holy Writings have bound/tied us. But following the desires/requirements of the new way, na, we are no longer bound with those regulation/s. Cuz (elaboration) God2's Spirit is what controls us [emphatic]! That's why, now, we just work for God2. [CHECK sariha-sanoro] [EXEG: SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sariha-sanoro = menolong, memelihara, bimbing, ator,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sariha-sanoro = menolong, memelihara, bimbing, ator, rangkulan (embrace) (probably not widely known, CHECK; young UNS “sudah membesarkan”)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now, by dying to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now, by dying to what once bound us, we have been released from the law, so that we serve in the new way of the Spirit, and not in the old way of the written law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Atora Musa paj'uj'u bhabhelu ètu d'ara èdhi<bt>Moses' law show the evil that is in our-inc insides [SSA]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />De èdhi neo peka ngaa? Neo peka, na, &lt;&lt;Atora dhu Lamatua hia re Musa ne, sala!&gt;&gt; Aad'o! Te ladhe ja'a ke'a mèu boe atora ne, tatu ja'a bisa boe ke'a j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke boe ètu d'ara ja'a. Nuka sèmi, abhu atora dhu peka na, &lt;&lt;Mage d'ara neo mere mèdha-panyau dhèu.&gt;&gt; Te ngaa dènge j'ara tasamia ka, ja'a bisa ke'a, na, d'ara neo sèmi èèna, sala, ladhe ke'a boe atora èèna? Bisa boe!<bt>So (consequently), what do we-inc want to say? Do [we] want to say, &lt;&lt;God2's Law via Musa, is wrong!&gt;&gt; No! Cuz (elaboration) if I don't really understand that law, surely I will not be able to understand the things which are not right/correct in my insides. For example, there is a regulation which says, &lt;&lt;Don't desire to take (other) people's possessions (doublet).&gt;&gt; But how can I know that a desire like that is wrong, if I don't know that regulation? (I) can't! [EXEG: SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tí óun eróumen: starts a new"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Tí óun eróumen: starts a new section, with a different philosophical argument LITERALLY: What shall we say then? That the law itself is sinful? Certainly not! But I would not have known sin except through the law. I would not have known what it is to covet if the law had not said, "You shall not covet."<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="7:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 20:17, Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 5:21</note><v n="8" />Te ngaa lula abhu atora dhu peka sèmi èèna, èèna nuka sèmi j'ara-j'ara bhelu ètu d'ara ja'a, sèna ka ja'a neo kore rupa-rupa mèdha-panyau dhèu. Ladhe dènge boe atora dhu kai, sasala na abhu boe koasa ho ator dhèu.<bt>But, because there is a regulation which says like that, it is as if the evil things in my insides are making me disire to take all.sorts of possessions of (other) people. If there aren't regulation/s/law that forbid it, its wrong/sin also doesn't have power to control/steer people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But sin, taking the opportunity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But sin, taking the opportunity given by the commandment, produced in me every kind of covetous desire. For apart from law, sin is dead.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ètu mamuri ja'a uru èèna, ja'a ke'a mèu mèka dad'èi nèti Atora Lamatua. Nèbhu-nèbhu ku, heka ke'a kèna. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a mulai mase'a, na, ja'a sisu le Atora sèra ka ad'u-ue sasala. De hua nèti sasala èèna ka, ja'a hud'i madhe ku.<bt>In my former life, I didn't yet truly understand the requirements of God2's Law. Eventually, only then did I understand. That's why I began to become aware that I had violated/transgressed thsoe Laws and done (doublet) wrong. And the fruit/consequence of that wrong, is I had to die. [EXEG: NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ètu mamuri ja'a uru èèna, ja'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Ètu mamuri ja'a uru èèna, ja'a tadhe boe Atora Lamatua. Nèbhu-nèbhu ku, ke'a na Atora Lamatua nèti j'ara-j'ara dhu lèke-lèke boe. Hèia j'ara-j'ara bhelu-katub'a nèti dara ja'a cèu sahèka sa li'u mai, ka ja'a sisu atora sèra ka ad'u-ue sasala.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Once I was alive apart"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Once I was alive apart from the law. But when the commandment came, sin sprang to life,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Hèia d'ara ja'a roe bhilu, te ke'a na, ja'a mesa ku bisa boe pabe'a ja'a dènge Lamatua, ladhe tao madhutu dhoka Atora Na. De pantas ladhe ja'a abhu nanasa nèti Lamatua, nuka huku madhe èèna, lula ja'a sisu le Atora Na. Aa te ngaa Lamatua hia atora ne, sèna ka dhèu bisa mamuri dhu lèke. Te ngaa bagi ja'a, Atora ne ka dhu pa'ele iie ja'a, ka Lamatua soro kabodho mi ja'a.<bt>So, my insides was weak (discouraged, disappointed) cuz (elaboration) I knew/came to realise that I myself couldn't be recip.good with God2, only because of obeying His Law. So (consequently) it is appropriate that I get/experience God2's anger, that is the punishment of death, because I have violated His Law. Where.in.actual.fact, God gave His Law, so that people could live right/correctly. But for me, it was that Law which ruined me, and so God2 turned his back on me. [EXEG: See SSA, Moo. Something along the lines of “I came to realize that my assumption that I could obtain eternal life by actually keeping the law was wrong. In fact, obeying the law made me come to realize I was separated from God.” In the context, he's talking about keeping the law, not about his inadequate attempts of “trying” to keep it. It is a massively profound theological watershed for Paul.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and I died. And the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and I died. And the commandment, which was meant to bring life, in my case brought death.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Atora ne mema pad'elo j'ara mamuri dhu mola. Te ngaa abhu bhabhelu dhu sub'u ètu d'ara ja'a. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a tipu hari ngi'u ja'a mesa ku, ho pangee na, ja'a bisa pabe'a ja'a dènge Ama Lamatua, sad'i ja'a tao madhutu Atora Na. Hèia èèna nuka sèmi Atora mesa èèna ka dhu tao toke Lamatua mad'enge dènge ja'a.<bt>That Law, really does show the path of life which is straight/correct. But there is evil which appears/shows up in my insides, I have deceived myself to think that I can be in a right.relationship with God, as long as I do according to His Law. Then, it's as if it's the Law itself which makes God2 to the point that He is disgusted/revolted with me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="check all mad'enge &gt; mad'enge AND"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">check all mad'enge &gt; mad'enge AND sorga &gt; surga ; sub'u = tumbuh subur</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For sin, taking the opportunity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For sin, taking the opportunity given by the commandment, deceived me, and by it killed me.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />De ladhe deo na dhèu peka na, &lt;&lt;Atora dhu Lamatua hia re Musa èèna, sala,&gt;&gt; na, ja'a dhaa na, &lt;&lt;Aad'o! Atora Lamatua ne, mola-mèci!&gt;&gt; Aa paredha aa'i-aa'i ètu d'ara Atora ne mola-mèci, lèke, aa be'a kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), if those recent people (=earlier in the text) say, &lt;&lt;The Law that God gave via Moses, is wrong,&gt;&gt; I respond, saying, &lt;&lt;No! God2's Law, is clean/holy/pure!&gt;&gt; And all the commands in that Law are also clean/holy, and1 right/correct, and2 also good. [NOTE: responding to v.7, SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then, the law is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then, the law is holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good. nómos: by now it's more specifically the revealed law, as well as cultural rules<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ele boe miu pangee, na, Atora ne ka dhu tao Lamatua soro kabodho mi ja'a, do? Aad'o! Te masi ka ja'a ke'a Atora sèra, te ngaa ja'a nanene taruu bhabhelu ètu d'ara ja'a, nèti èèna ka ja'a tao sala. De nèti sasala ja'a èèna ka Lamatua soro kabodho mi ja'a. Atora ne mema be'a, te èèna ka dhu pad'elo j'ara-j'ara bhelu-katub'a dhu tao èdhi pacèri nèti Ama Lamatua. De ropa Lamatua pad'elo j'ara mamuri dhu lèke, Atora èèna ka dhu peka paled'a, na, bhabhelu ètu d'ara èdhi èèna, be'a boe.<bt>Perhaps/probably you are also thinking, saying, it's the Law which made God2 turn his back on me, right? No! Cuz (elaboration) even though I know that Law/Regulation, nevertheless I still keep listening to/obeying that evil which is in my liver/heart, that is why I do wrong/sin. So (consequently) it is my doing wrong that makes God2 turn his back/reject on me. The Law itself is certainly good, cuz (elaboration) it shows/reveals things which are evil (doublet), which cause us-inc to be cut off/separated away from God. So (consequently), when God2 shows the path of life which is right/correct, that Law is what makes clear/explains, that, those evil things in our liver/hearts, are not good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Did that which is good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Did that which is good become death to me? Certainly not! But so that sin might be seen as sin, it produced death in me through what was good, so that through the commandment sin might become completely sinful.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Babe'a dènge bhabhelu patula-pajuku ètu d'ara èdhi<bt>Good and evil push and pull (struggle with each other) in our-inc insides</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Èdhi te'a, na, Atora dhu Lamatua pangèd'u re Musa, puru mai nèti Roh Lamatua. Te ngaa ja'a ne dhoka dhèu rai-haha biasa di, dhu dènge d'ara dhu èra boe. Hèia ja'a nanene j'ara-j'ara bhelu ètu d'ara ja'a, toke ja'a manahu asa d'ara sasala. Èèna nuka sèmi sasala dhu j'aj'i lamatua ja'a, aa ja'a j'aj'i mi ènu nèti sasala.<bt>We-inc know that the Law which God2 handed over via Musa, came down from God2's Spirit. But I am only an ordinary human whose insides (character, seat of emotions) is not strong. So I listen.to/obey the evil things which are in my insides, to the point that I fall into wrong [common phrasing]. That is as if wrong/sin has become my boss/master, and I have became a slave to sin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that the law is spiritual. But I am [unspiritual/carnal/worldly], sold as a slave to sin.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Pamalaa ja'a. Ja'a ke'a boe ngaa ka dhu ja'a tao. Te ja'a tao boe madhutu ngaa dhu ja'a neo tao. Te ngaa ja'a tao madhutu ngaa dhu ja'a d'èi boe tao.<bt>It makes me confused. I don't understand what it is I am doing. Cuz (elaboration) I don't do according to what I want to do. But I do according to what I don't want to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pamalaa ja'a = I'm confused, It"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Pamalaa ja'a = I'm confused, It makes me confused.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not know what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not know what I am doing. Because what I want to do, I do not do. But what I hate, I do.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galati 5:17</note><v n="16" />Ladhe ja'a tao ngaa dhu ja'a neo boe tao, ja'a mangaku, na, Atora Lamatua ne lèke.<bt>If I do according to what I don't want to do, I acknowledge/confess that, that Law of God2's, is right/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I do what I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I do what I do not want to do, I agree that the law is good.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />De ja'a boe ka dhu uri ngi'u ja'a. Te bhabhelu dhu muri ètu d'ara ja'a ka dhu uli ja'a!<bt>So (consequently), it's not me who controls/manages/steers myself. Cuz (elaboration) it's the evil which lives in my insides that controls me [+speaker emphasis]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then it is not me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then it is not me that does it, but sin that lives in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ja'a ke'a le, na, abhu boe j'ara dhu be'a muri ètu d'ara ja'a. Te ja'a ne dhèu rai-haha dhu d'ara karehe. D'èi do d'èi boe, ja'a bisa boe pakaseti iisi sèna ka tao dhu lèke. Ja'a d'èi tao dhu be'a, te ngaa j'aj'i boe!<bt>I know that there is no good thing which lives in my insides. Cuz (elaboration) I here, am a human who has a rotten/evil2 insides. Want to or not, I cannot force myself to do what is right/correct. I want to do what is good, but it doesn't happen/eventuate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dèi do dèi boe = ko'o"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Dèi do dèi boe = ko'o do ko'o boe ; ko'o2 = tofa (rumput) but does not inflect for person and number ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I know that nothing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I know that nothing good lives in me, that is in my sinful nature. Because the good desire is with me, but I do not find how to do that which is good.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Te ja'a d'èi tao dhu be'a, te ngaa j'aj'i boe tao. Aa ko'o boe tao dhu bhelu, te ngaa cèku tao!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I desire to do what is good, but it doesn't happen. And I don't want to do what is evil, but I do it!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cèku (ALT cuku)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">cèku (ALT cuku)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the good that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the good that I would like to do, I do not do. But the evil that I do not want to do, that I do.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />De ladhe ja'a ad'u-ue ngaa dhu ko'o boe tao, èèna mai boe nèti ja'a mesa ku, te ngaa lula sasala dhu muri ètu d'ara ja'a.<bt>So (consequently) if I do what I don't want to do, that does not come from me myself, but because of the evil which is living in my insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now, if I do what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now, if I do what I would not like to do, it is not me that is doing it, but sin that lives in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ne'e ne j'aj'i mi tate'a èci, sèmi ne'e ka: masi ka ja'a neo tao dhu be'a, te ngaa abhu bhabhelu dhu palab'a ètu d'ara ja'a.<bt>This is a principle, like this: even.if/though I want to do what is good, nevertheless there is evil which opposes/rebels/fights in my insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So I find a principle,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So I find a principle, that when I want to do good, evil is present with me.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Aa te ngaa madhutu iia-iia ètu d'ara ja'a karej'e titu kèna, ladhe ja'a pangee Atora Lamatua.<bt>However, in actual fact, my insides are very happy, if/when I am thinking about God2's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I delight in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I delight in the law of God in my inner being.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Te ngaa nuka sèmi abhu koasa ètu d'ara ja'a dhu pa'ele iie ja'a. Te ja'a neo tao dhu be'a, te ngaa j'aj'i boe. Èèna nuka sèmi koasa bhabhelu ètu d'ara ja'a dhu kèpe nare ja'a, ho laka-seti madhutu ne.<bt>But, it.is.as.if there is a power/authority in my insides which ruins/destroys me. [NOTE: kuasa 'power' here intended as sense #2 authority/law/principle, not sense #1, power. Kuasa's can be in opposition, but atoran and prinsip can't.] Cuz (elaboration) I desire to do what is good, but it just doesn't happen/eventuate. It.is.as.if the evil force/power which is in my insides has captured/arrested me, to force me to only follow him (personification).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I see another principle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I see another principle in my body, fighting against the principle of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the principle of sin, which is in my body.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ira ii, kasian, ee! Ja'a ne dhèu j'èra! Dhèu cee ka dhu bisa patabuli ja'a nèti koasa bhabhelu dhu muri ètu d'ara ja'a ne, dhu tao Lamatua mad'enge dènge ja'a?<bt>Ira ii [+regret, grief]! I am a person in difficulty! Who can save/release me from this evil power which lives in my insides, which makes God2 detest/abhor me?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dale ; Ira ii, kasian, ee!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dale ; Ira ii, kasian, ee! = UNSs say bawa unsur keluhan, duka, menyesal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What a miserable person I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What a miserable person I am! Who will rescue me from this body of death?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Te ngaa malo-malo ka! Ama Lamatua unu Na ka dhu bhoke j'ara ho patabuli eele ja'a! Ja'a manèngi makasi ae-ae mi Lamatua, lula Kètu èdhi Yesus Kristus bisa hia mamuri mi ja'a! De ladhe ja'a mamuri maena dhoka mi ngi'u ja'a di, na, ja'a j'èra. Masi ka ja'a neo tao madhutu Atora Lamatua, te ngaa abhu koasa bhabhelu ètu d'ara ja'a, dadugu ja'a, sèna ka tao taruu dhoka bhabhelu-katub'a di.<bt>But wow [+positive, hopeful]! God himself has opened the way to set me free! I give many thanks to God2, because our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus can save2 me! So (consequently), if I live hoping/leaning on my own self, I am miserable/in torment. Even.if I wants to do according to God2's Law, nevertheless there is an evil power in my insides cajoles/tempts me to keep doing evil (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bhabhae = manghalangi ; malo-malo ka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">bhabhae = manghalangi ; malo-malo ka = UNSs say bawa rasa untung, harapan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thanks to God through Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thanks to God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, with the mind I myself serve God's law, but with the body the [law/principle] of sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èdhi bisa mamuri mola, ladhe pa'èki dènge Roh Lamatua<bt>We-inc can truly live/live straight/righteous, if we are bound/linked with God2's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />De Ama Lamatua huku boe dhèu dhu pa'èki dènge Yesus Kristus!<bt>So (consequently), God doesn't punish people who are bound/linked with Yesus Kristus!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, there is now no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus, ára: this wraps up what Paul has said before. It's like getting back to the main point<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nýn: in contrast to the impasse he was talking about in the last chapter. It's talking about logic, not time -- "the way things really are" sárka: probably copied from Verse 4 to make clear what "stay tight" is referring to. It's in a few important manuscripts but not in all<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te abhu dua lii tate'a dhu lèke: ka èci peka na, ladhe èdhi pa'èki dènge Yesus Kristus, Roh Lamatua hia koasa mi èdhi ho bisa mamuri mola. Ka dua peka na, abhu bhabhelu ètu d'ara èdhi dhu kakèj'i èdhi ho tao sala. Aa ladhe èdhi tao sala, Ama Lamatua mad'enge dènge èdhi. Aa ladhe èdhi abhu Roh Lamatua, Na patalale èdhi nèti koasa sasala.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are two principles which are right/true: the first says, if we-inc are bound/linked with Yesus Kristus, God2's Spirit gives us power/authority to be able to live straight/right/ correctly. The second says, there is evil in our insides that cajoles/coaxes/tempts/persuades us to do wrong/sin. And if/when we-inc do wrong, God is disgusted/abhorred with us. And if/when we get/have God2's Spirit, He frees/releases us from the power of wrong/sin. [EXEG: “/nomos/ of the Spirit” is widely argued that it has to be taken in the sense of “principle” and not “law” in this context. See Morris, Moo, SSA, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the principle of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the principle of the Spirit bringing life in Christ Jesus has set me free from the principle of sin and death.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Masi ka èdhi tao madhutu atora Musa, èèna bisa boe patabuli èdhi nèti koasa sasala, lula èdhi se dhoka dhèu rai-haha biasa di dhu tao bhabhelu katub'a taruu. Te ngaa Lamatua ka dhu bhoke j'ara. Te Nèngu pua Ana Mone mesa Na mai, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu rai-haha biasa, sama sèmi èdhi kahèi. Masi ka èdhi dhèu rai-haha biasa tao rupa-rupa sasala, te ngaa Yesus mesa-mesa Na dhu tao nèdhi boe sasala ngaa-ngaa. Ngaa hari, Nèngu j'aj'i korban, ho saku eele sasala-sasigo dhèu.<bt>Even if we do according to Moses' Law, that cannot release/save us from the power of wrong/sin, because we-inc are only just ordinary humans who keep doing wrong. But God2 is the one who opened a way (out). Cuz (elaboration) He sent His own Son [marked] to become an ordinary human like us. Even though we-inc normal humans do all sorts of wrong, nevertheless Yesus himself never did any wrong. In addition, He became a *sacrifice to erase/wipe away people's wrongs/sins (doublet). [EXEG: SSA, NLT, CEV, TB, Morris, Moo. It is not about the effort in trying to do it (whether it succeeds or not), but that even if we could do it successfully, Paul has come to realise that still wouldn't make the grade.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mesa-mesa = uniquely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">mesa-mesa = uniquely</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For what the law could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For what the law could not do, in that it was weakened by our sinful nature, God did by sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful man [and for sin/ to be a sin offering]. And so he condemned sin in sinful man,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ama Lamatua hia Kristus mai, sèna ka Na madhe, ho hud'i laa èdhi bisa tao j'ara aa'i-aa'i dhu lèke, madhutu Atora Lamatua. Ka limuri ne, èdhi tao j'ara-j'ara dhu mola madhutu dad'èi Roh Lamatua, aa tao heka madhutu dad'èi d'ara unu ti.<bt>God sent Kristus in.order.that He die, so that we-inc can do according to all the things that are right/correct/true, according to God2's Law. So now, we are doing straight/right/correct things, according to God2's Spirit's desire/will, and no longer following our own desires/passions. [EXEG: Not Moses law here (Moo, SSA). Don't follow TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: in order that the righteous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: in order that the righteous requirements of the law might be fully met in us, who do not live according to the sinful nature, but according to the Spirit. katà sárka: same idea as in 3 -- human nature is driven by how we feel, and it motivates the way our bodies behave<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Dhèu dhu mamuri madhutu dad'èi d'ara unu ra, tao sèmi èèna lula ra pangee dhoka j'ara bhabhelu di. Te ngaa dhèu dhu mamuri madhutu dad'èi Roh Lamatua, rèngu dhoka pangee j'ara-j'ara dhu pakarej'e d'ara Roh Lamatua di.<bt>Those people who live according to their own desires/passions, do like.that because they are thinking only evil things. But people who live according to God2's Spirit's desires/will, they are only thinking about things which make God2's Spirit happy. [NOTE to daughter translations: wording resonates with Gen. 6:5--compare phrasing.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those who live according to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those who live according to their sinful nature have their minds set on what the sinful nature wants; but those who live according to the Spirit have their minds set on what the Spirit wants.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Dhèu dhu soro tèke bhabhelu ator ngangee na, sama sèmi dhèu dhu nanene boe Roh Lamatua, nuka sèmi d'ara nèngu aad'o heka dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa dhèu dhu soro tèke Roh Lamatua ator ngangee na, mamuri na mola, aa d'ara na mera-milu.<bt>A person who allows evil to control/arrange his thinking, is the same as a person who doesn't know how/isn't able to listen to/obey God's Spirit, that is his/her insides toward God2 no longer exist. But a person who allows God2's Spirit to control/ arrange that thinking of his, his life is straight/true/real, and his insides are at peace. [HCE: EXEG: SSA seems to be incorrect here in pushing death &amp; life here = eternal damnation &amp; eternal life; mind, controlled by, life &amp; peace all seem to indicate he is talking about here on earth; “death” is structurally juxtaposed to “life &amp; peace”, hence rendering here as “death in his liver” Morris rejects the idea of “consequences, results in, brings”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thanatos: mahke inside, as in 1"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">thanatos: mahke inside, as in 1 Timothy 5:6 LITERALLY: The mind of the sinful nature is death, but the mind controlled by the Spirit is life and peace,<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dad'èi èdhi dhèu rai-haha ne, palab'a bia dènge dad'èi Lamatua. Hèia èdhi to'o boe pahaha iisi ho nanene Lamatua, lula èdhi mesa ti bisa boe.<bt>The desires/passions of we'inc humans is heavily opposed to God2's will/desires. So, we don't humble ourselves/bow (=symbol of respect) to listen to/obey God2, because we (by) ourselves can't.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because the mind of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because the mind of the sinful nature is hostile to God. It does not submit to God's law, nor can it do so.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te dhèu dhu soro tèke dad'èi ra ator rèngu, d'èi do d'èi boe, èèna bisa boe pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) people who allow their own desires/passions to control/manage them, want-to-or-not, that cannot make.happy(=please) God2's insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those controlled by their sinful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those controlled by their sinful nature cannot please God. arésai: do something that God will be happy about. It's like everything they do is polluted and they don't know it, but God knows<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Te ngaa miu se, dhèu dhu mamuri bhelu heka, madhutu dad'èi d'ara mi. Te ladhe abhu Roh Lamatua dhu mamuri ètu d'ara miu, miu tao j'ara-j'ara dhu pakarej'e d'ara Nèngu. (Te ngaa ladhe abhu dhèu dhu Roh Kristus pea boe ètu d'ara na, nèngu j'aj'i boe dhèu unu Lamatua.)<bt>But as for you-pl, no longer live evil according to your own desires/ passions. Cuz (elaboration) if God2's Spirit is living in your insides, you do things that please Him. (But if there is a person who Kristus' Spirit doesn't live in his insides, he also has not become God2's possession.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you are not controlled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you are not controlled by your sinful nature, but by the Spirit, if the Spirit of God lives in you. But if any person does not have the Spirit of Christ, he is not his.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ngi'u aae miu bèli-camèd'a madhe, lula sasala dhu miu tao uru sèra. Te ngaa, lula limuri ne Kristus mamuri ètu d'ara miu, roh miu mamuri taruu, lula Ama Lamatua cap le miu dhèu d'ara mola, hèia miu pabe'a hari le dènge Ne.<bt>Your-pl bodies later will die, because you previously did wrong/sin. But, because now Kristus lives in your insides, your spirits will live continually, because God has stamped/categorised you as straight insides (righteous) people, so you are already in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: if bodies don't die, but people die, don't feel you have to retain the image. “You will die...” But discuss it in the full framework of vs.10-11, where there is death:life and body:spirit. So don't force the language, but make sure the contrasts come through.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if Christ is in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if Christ is in you, your body is dead because of sin, but your spirit is alive because of [righteousness / justification].</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Te Ama Lamatua ka dhu pamamuri hari Yesus Kristus nèti mamadhe Na. De masi ka èdhi madhe, te ngaa ladhe Roh Lamatua dhu mamuri ètu d'ara èdhi, pe Nèngu pamamuri hari èdhi kahèi. Sasoa na, Na pamamuri èdhi sama sèmi Na pamamuri hari Kristus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God is the one who caused Yesus to live again from His death. So (consequently), even if/though we die, nevertheless if God2's Spirit is living in us, He also later will make us live again/come back to life. That means, He will make us live, the same as He caused Kristus to live again. [DISCOURSE: shift to 1pi from Gk 2p for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And if the Spirit of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And if the Spirit of the one who raised Jesus from the dead is living in you, he who raised Christ from the dead will also give life to your [mortal / dying] bodies through his Spirit who lives in you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 3:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Roh Lamatua peka na, èdhi j'aj'i ana-ana Ama Lamatua<bt>God2's Spirit tells/makes known, that, we-inc have become God's children</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />De sèmi ne'e a'ari aa'i-aa'i! Èdhi dhu dènge kèlu-g'ètu. Mage nèti kèlu-g'ètu ne, ho mamuri èdhi madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha di, te ngaa èdhi hud'i mamuri madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently) it's like this, siblings! We-inc have a debt (doublet). It is not a debt for us-inc to live following our human desires/passions, but we must live according to the will of God. [EXEG: last clause implicit to explicit--from Helong check.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kèlu-gètu = utang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kèlu-gètu = utang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then brothers, we have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then brothers, we have an obligation, but it is not to our sinful nature, to live according to that.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te ladhe èdhi mamuri madhutu dhoka bhabhelu ètu d'ara èdhi di, tatu Lamatua soro kabodho mi èdhi, aa èdhi pasae tare huku madhe! Te ngaa ladhe èdhi soro tèke Roh Lamatua palaho koasa sasala ètu d'ara èdhi, èèna na èdhi heka bisa mamuri dhu mola kèna.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we just live following/obeying the evil that is in our insides, surely God2 will turn His back on us, and we will bear the punishment of death! But, if we allow God2's Spirit to destroy the power from the wrong/sin that is in our insides, only.then will we be able to live straight/right/ true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if you live according"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if you live according to the sinful nature, you will surely die! But if, by the Spirit, you [put to death / kill] the deeds of the body, you will live.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dhèu dhu nanene Roh Lamatua, sèna ka Na ator si, na, dhèu se'e ka dhu j'aj'i ana-ana Ama Lamatua.<bt>People who listen to/obey God2's Spirit so.that He controls/manages them, na, these are the people who are God's children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those who are led by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those who are led by the Spirit of God are the sons of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ladhe èdhi soro tèke Roh Lamatua ator èdhi, Na tao boe èdhi sèmi ènu dhu mamuri dhoka dènge d'ara madha'u di. Uru èèna, èdhi mamuri sèmi èèna ka. Te ngaa, lula èdhi sèmi tare le Roh Lamatua ho uri èdhi, èdhi te'a le, na, èdhi j'aj'i le ana-ana Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, Nèngu d'èi tadèngi, ladhe èdhi paroa Ne, &lt;&lt;Ama Pasue!&gt;&gt;<bt>If we-inc allow God2's Spirit to control/manage us, He doesn't make us like a slave that lives only with fearful insides. Formerly, we lived like.that. But, because we have already received God2's Spirit to control/manage us, we know that we have already become God's children. That's why He will listen, if/when we call Him, saying, &lt;&lt;Dear Father!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: shift to 1pi from Gk 2p for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For you did not receive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For you did not receive a spirit [of slavery to fear / that makes you slaves to fear] again, but you received a Spirit [of sonship / who makes you sons]. And by him we cry out, "Abba [Papa/ Daddy], Father".</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 14:36, Galati 4:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />D'ara èdhi unu ti ka dhu peka na, èdhi j'aj'i ana-ana Lamatua. Aa Roh Lamatua kahèi peka sèmi èèna.<bt>Our own insides are what tells/lets us know, that, we have become God2's children. And God2's Spirit also tells/makes known like.that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Spirit himself gives testimony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Spirit himself gives testimony with our spirit that we are God's children.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ladhe èdhi j'aj'i ana-ana Lamatua, èèna sasoa na, bèli-camèd'a èdhi sèmi tare pusaka Na, lula Nèngu j'aj'i Ama èdhi. Aa ladhe Ama hia pusaka mi Ana Na Kristus, èdhi kahèi sèmi palere-lere dènge Ne. Te ngaa abhu ca j'ara era: èdhi hud'i abhu ku j'aj'èra, sama sèmi Kristus kahèi dhu abhu le j'aj'èra, sèna ka bèli-camèd'a Lamatua ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha, nuka sèmi Nèngu ded'e padedha-dedha le Kristus.<bt>If we become/are God2's children, that means that, later we will receive His inheritance, because He is/has become our Father. And if/when Father gives an inheritance to His Child Kristus, we also receive it together with Him. But there is one more thing: we must encounter/experience suffering, just as Kristus also encounter/experienced suffering, so that later God2 can/will lift us up high (=exalt/praise/glorify), the same as He has lifted Kristus up high.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now since we are children,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now since we are children, then we are heirs--heirs indeed of God and co-heirs with Christ, if we [suffer with him / share in his suffering], in order that we may also [be glorified with him / share in his glory]. ei: no doubt about it -- more like "since we are ..."<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>hína: suffering is the prerequisite, and it leads to the payoff, which is glory</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galati 4:5-7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bèli-camèd'a Lamatua ded'e èdhi padedha-dedha<bt>Later God2 will lift us-inc up high (=praise/exalt/glorify)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Te ngaa madhutu a'abhu ja'a, j'aj'èra dhu èdhi pasae ne'e ne, kab'ua na aad'o, ladhe pasoro dènge dadedha dhu Lamatua neo pad'elo mi èdhi.<bt>But according to me, the suffering which we bear/ experience now doesn't have any meaning, if/when compared with the amazing/incredible things which God2 will later show us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokalyftheenai: be revealed (by God) LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">apokalyftheenai: be revealed (by God) LITERALLY: For I consider that the present sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed for us.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Madhutu iia-iia na, aa'i-aa'i dhu Ama Lamatua paj'aj'i ètu dedha-liru dènge rai-haha, dhu mate tatae neo rèdhi Na pad'elo ana-ana Na sèra, nuka cee! Te Na neo pad'elo dènge ra, dènge d'ara karej'e-karae.<bt>In.actual.fact everything which God has created in the sky (doublet) and the earth (doublet), is waiting expectantly wanting to see Him show/reveal who His true children are. Cuz (elaboration) He wants to show/reveal them with a joyful (doublet) insides. [SSA + HCE (larger context)] [NOTE to daughter translations: if the /sapa/ construction makes things difficult, try a statement /ada tunggu-tunggu deng rindu ko mau lia Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung ana-ana deng hati babunga./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokaradokía: eager longing, deep desire, can't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">apokaradokía: eager longing, deep desire, can't wait to find out, itching LITERALLY: The creation waits in eager expectation for the sons of God to be revealed.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te Ama Lamatua paj'aj'i dedha-liru dènge rai-haha, aa dènge isi ra aa'i-aa'i, sèna ka tao madhutu dad'èi Na. Te ngaa ra madhutu boe, lula boe dad'èi rèngu, te ngaa nèti dad'èi Lamatua, te Na huku si sèna ka pa'ele iie si. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa abhu era maena era.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God created the sky (doublet) and the earth (doublet) and all their contents, in.order.to do according to His intent/purpose(s). But they didn't follow (it), not because they didn't want to, but because of following God2's will, cuz (elaboration) He punished them, and allowed them to become rotten/decayed. Even though that's the case, nevertheless there is still hope. [EXEG: SSA; theologically hairy verse; Morris points out arguments in several directions make equal (non)sense.][NOTE to daughter translations: make sure /sonde jadi-jadi/ tracks to /bekin iko Dia pung mau/ not to creation (!) If problem, try /Ma dong sonde mau iko/. Also, if needed, see Helong for alternate organization combining vs.20-21.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the creation was subjected"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the creation was subjected to [worthlessness / futility / purposelessness], not by its own choice, but by the will of the one [God] who subjected it. Yet there was this hope,</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 3:17-19</note><v n="21" />Te limuri ne aa'i-aa'i dhu Lamatua paj'aj'i sèra ele iie, aa abhu boe j'ara kalua. Te ngaa èèna na, Lamatua neo patabuli si, sèna ka ra ele iie heka, te ngaa rèngu bisa j'aj'i kapai titu kèna madhutu dad'èi Na. Lamatua kahèi neo ded'e padedha-dedha ana-ana Na, ho patabuli rèngu nèti dhu ele iie sèra.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now all those aforementioned things which God2 created, are ruined, and there is no way out. But later God2 is going to free/rescue/save them, so.that they aren't in a (morally/socially) ruined state anymore, but they can become amazing/incredible following/ in.accord with His intent/purpose. God2 also is going to lift up high (exalt, glorify) His children, so that they also are freed/rescued/saved from those things that are ruined.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ele = hilang ; ele iie"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ele = hilang ; ele iie = rusak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that the creation itself will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that the creation itself will be freed from its bondage to decay, and brought into the glorious freedom of the children of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Te èdhi te'a le, na, abhu j'aj'èra ae ètu rai-haha ne. Karèi nèti uru ka d'ai doe ne'e, aa'i-aa'i dhu Lamatua paj'aj'i sèra, taraa pèd'a, dhu ra tatae ho Lamatua tao aa'i-aa'i j'aj'i hiu. Èèna nuka sèmi bhèni dhu taraa kabake pèd'a neo nara iisi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we already know there is much trouble and strife in this world. From long ago until now, all the things which God2 created, moan from pain, while waiting for/anticipating God2 making everything become new. That is like a female who is groaning in pain about to give birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taraa = shout, moan, groan (in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">taraa = shout, moan, groan (in pain), complain (can be sound only (as in vs.26), or can also have words)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that the whole"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that the whole creation has been groaning in the pains of childbirth right up to the present time.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Mesa boe rai-haha di dhu tatae, te ngaa èdhi kahèi mate sèmi èèna. Masi ka Lamatua hia uru le Roh Na mi èdhi, èdhi taraa d'ara pèd'a kahèi. Te èdhi dhu tatae mate Ama Lamatua ded'e nare èdhi j'aj'i ana-ana dhu mola, dènge patabuli ngi'u èdhi aa'i-aa'i nèti dhu ele iie.<bt>Not just the world/creation itself which keeps waiting/ anticipating, but we-inc also keep waiting2/ anticipating2 like.that. Even though God2 has given His Spirit to us first, we also are moaning in pain. Cuz (elaboration) we keep waiting (doublet) for God to lift us up/appoint/adopt to become His true children, and to free/rescue/save our bodies from everything that is ruined. [NOTE to daughter translations: a possible way to better reflect the concept of “first fruits” is “God2 has given us His Spirit first, to show that later we will get more than that, we still moan...” But be careful it is not such heavy information load that it skews the focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparkheen: the first installment of what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">aparkheen: the first installment of what he plans to give us eventually. LITERALLY: And not only [them], but we also, who have the Spirit as the [firstfruits /first gift], groan inwardly as we wait eagerly for our adoption as children, the redemption of our bodies.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 5:2-4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Lod'o Lamatua hia èdhi mamuri, Na peka kahèi, bèli-camèd'a Na tao sèmi ngaa. Te ngaa limuri ne, èdhi dhu tatae era lula dhae j'aj'i mèka. Ladhe èdhi tèdhi ka j'ara èci dhu j'aj'i le, èdhi pamata heka neo tèdhi j'ara èèna. Te dhèu parluu heka mate, sèna ka rèdhi j'ara dhu j'aj'i le, sina ma?<bt>When God saved us, He also told/made known, what/how he would want to do later. But now, we are still waiting, because it's not yet happened/ eventuated. If we see a thing has happened, we don't need to wait anymore to want to see that thing. Cuz (elaboration) people don't need to keep waiting anymore to see a thing that has already happened, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we were saved by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we were saved by hope. But hope that is seen is not hope. For who hopes for what he sees?</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Te ngaa ladhe èdhi dhu tatae ho neo tèdhi ca j'ara dhu dhae j'aj'i mèka, èdhi pa'èra d'ara taruu.<bt>But if we are waiting to see something that has not yet happened, we can strengthen our insides continually (patient endurance).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if we hope for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if we hope for what we do not see, we wait for it with patience.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, lod'o èdhi mate tae-tae èèna, Roh Lamatua ka dhu soru-bara èdhi, lula èdhi se dhu roe-bhilu, aa te'a boe sabaj'a dhu lèke. Te ngaa Roh Lamatua unu Na ka dhu sabaj'a gati èdhi, masi ka te'a dhoka taraa di, aa te'a boe sabaj'a peka lii ngaa.<bt>In the same way also, while we keep waiting/ anticipating/hoping2, God2's Spirit is also helping us. because we are weak (doublet), and don't know how to pray right/true/correctly. But God2's Spirit himself is praying replacing us, even though we only just know how to moan, and don't know how to pray using which words. [Morris, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the same way, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the same way, the Spirit helps us in our weakness. We do not know how we should pray, but the Spirit himself [intercedes / pleads] for us with groans that words cannot express.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ama Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu ne'a aa'i mèu-mèu, dhu èdhi neo peka nèti d'ara èdhi. Nèngu ne'a ngangee Roh Na kahèi. Nèti èèna ka, Nèngu ne'a aa'i j'ara-j'ara dhu Roh Na neo peka ho soru-bara èdhi. Te ngangee Roh Lamatua, èci èèna ka dènge ngangee Ama Lamatua mesa Na. Aa Roh Na dhu sabaj'a mi Ama Lamatua, manèngi sèna ka Lamatua soru-bara dhèu parcaya sèra. Te Roh ne sabaj'a madhutu dad'èi Lamatua.<bt>God himself knows everything that we want to say in our insides. He also knows His Spirit's thinking. That's why He knows/understands everything which His Spirit wants to say to help us. Cuz (elaboration) God2's Spirit's thinking, is the same as Father God's own thinking. And His Spirit is praying to Father God, requesting that God2 help (doublet) the believers. Cuz (elaboration) that Spirit prays following/ according to God2's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entynkhanei hyper hagioon: CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">entynkhanei hyper hagioon: CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY: And he who searches hearts knows the mind of the Spirit, because the Spirit intercedes for the saints in accordance with God's will.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />De limuri ne èdhi te'a le sèmi ne'e: Ama Lamatua tao aa'i-aa'i j'aj'i mi be'a hia dhèu dhu sue Nèngu. Te karèi nèti uru ka, Lamatua dhu ator nare le j'ara tasamia dhu Na neo tao hia mi rèngu. Aa Na paroa le rèngu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mai ka! Mai j'aj'i dhèu unu Ja'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) now we already know like this: God makes everything become good on.behalf.of/for the people who love Him. Cuz (elaboration) from long.ago, God2 has arranged ahead.of.time what it is that He wants to/is going to do for them. And He has already called them, saying, &lt;&lt;Come on! Come become My people!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if /su ator memang so'al Dia mau bekin karmana kasi sang dong/ is hard to translate, try /su putus memang, iko Dia pung mau./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For those who love God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For those who love God and are called according to his purpose, he works out everything for good.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Lula uru-uru sèra, Na tadhe le rèngu aa hag'e nare si, sèna ka j'aj'i ca ropa dènge Ana Na, nuka Kristus. Te Kristus ka dhu Ana uuru, aa dhu leo sèra j'aj'i mi ari Na.<bt>Because long ago, He already knew/recognised them, and chose/set apart them to become a model/image like His Child, which is Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) Kristus is the eldest Child, and the others are His younger.siblings. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk “firstborn (of all creation)” is also used in Colossians, where that context makes it clear that sequential order is not in focus, but rather status above all creation. Just keep in mind that you also want status more in focus here, and if possible, minimise temporal order.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For those whom he knew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For those whom he knew beforehand, he also planned beforehand to [become / be made] like his Son, so that he [Christ] might be the first born among many brothers.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dhèu dhu Lamatua tadhe karèi nèti uru sèra, Na paroa nare le, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu unu Na. Aa rèngu kahèi, dhu uru èèna dhèu sala, Na tao si j'aj'i dhèu mola, sèna ka pabe'a hari dènge Ne. Aa Na ded'e si padedha-dedha.<bt>Those people whom God2 already knew from long.ago, He also called them to become His people. And those same people, who formerly were sinful/wrong /guilty people, He has made to become straight insides (righteous) people so.that they are in a reciprocally good relationship again with Him. And He also lifts them up high (=exalt, glorify; different grammar from lift up = appoint, adopt).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And those he knew beforehand,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And those he knew beforehand, he also called. Those he called, he also justified. Those he justified, he also glorified.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua sue èdhi titu kèna<bt>God loves us greatly</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />De èdhi peka ngaa hari nèti j'ara se aa'i-aa'i ra? Ama Lamatua dhu bhiri nare èdhi. Aa ladhe sèmi èèna, dhèu cee dhu bisa lab'a hari èdhi? Abhu boe, sina ma?<bt>So (consequently), what else can we say about all these things? God is supporting/ backing us to the max. And if that the case, who can oppose us anymore? There's nothing/no.one, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what will we say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what will we say about these things? If God is for us, who is against us?</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ama Lamatua taha boe Ana Na. Te ngaa soro Ana Na ho madhe j'aj'i korban, sèna ka soru-bara èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti. Lula Ama Lamatua taha boe Ana Na, èdhi bisa te'a, na, bèli-camèd'a Na hia iia èdhi j'ara aa'i-aa'i dhu be'a. Lèke, si?<bt>God didn't hold back/restrain/withhold His own Child. But He handed.over His Child to die as a sacrifice, in.order.to help us all. Because God didn't withhold His Child, we can know that, later He will also free.gift(verb) to us, all things which are good. That's true, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who did not spare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who did not spare his own Son, but gave him up for us all, how will he not also, with him, freely give us all things?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ele boe miu pangee, na, abhu dhèu dhu bisa pèci sasala asa dhèu dhu Lamatua hag'e nare sèra? Te ngaa aad'o, si? Te Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu cap èdhi j'aj'i dhèu mola dhu dènge heka sasala, ho èdhi pabe'a hari dènge Ne.<bt>Perhaps/probably you-pl think that there still are people who can accuse/cast blame on the people whom God2 has chosen? But there is no one, right? Cuz (elaboration) God2 himself is the one who stamped/ branded/categorised us-inc as straight /righteous people who no longer have any wrong/sin/guilt, so.that we could be in a reciprocally right relationship with Him again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Cee ka dhu neo pèci sasala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Cee ka dhu neo pèci sasala asa dhèu dhu Lamatua hag'e nare sèra? Aad'o, si? Te, Lamatua mesa na ka tao rèngu j'aj'i dhèu mola, ho pabe'a hari dènge Ne.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who will bring any accusation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who will bring any accusation against the ones that God has chosen? It is God who justifies [them].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ele boe miu pangee, na, abhu dhèu era dhu peka na, hud'i Lamatua huku ku dhèu dhu Na hag'e nare sèra. Te ngaa bisa boe! Te Yesus Kristus dhu madhe le. Risi-risi hari, Lamatua ka dhu pamamuri hari Ne nèti mamadhe Na. Hèia Lamatua ded'e Ne, sèna ka pamadhèdi Ne ètu era dhu kab'ua risi re baboa g'ana Na. Aa ètu èèna, Nèngu loe boe sabaj'a hia èdhi.<bt>Perhaps/probably you think that there are still people who say that God2 must punish the people whom He has chosen (collective). But that is not possible/not going to happen! Cuz (elaboration) Yesus Kristus has died. And even more, God2 caused Him to live again from His death. So/Then, God2 elevated/appointed Him up to sit in the place which has the most honor at His right side. And there, He is the one who prays continually on.behalf.of/for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK all sebhe g'ana &gt; baboa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">CHECK all sebhe g'ana &gt; baboa g'ana</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="De, abhu boe dhèu dhu peka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">De, abhu boe dhèu dhu peka na Lamatua hud'i huku ku dhèu dhu Na hag'e nare sèra. Te, Yesus Kristus dhu madhe le. Risi-risi hari Nèngu ka dhu Lamatua pamamuri hari nèti mamadhe Na. Hèia Lamatua ded'e nare Ne, sèna ka padhèdi Ne ètu era dhu kabua risi re baboa g'ana Na. Aa Nèngu ka dhu loe boe sabaj'a hia èdhi.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who is the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who is the one who condemns? Christ Jesus is the one who died, or rather, who was raised to life, who is at the right side of God, who is also [interceding / pleading] for us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ele boe miu pangee, na, abhu dhèu do, j'ara dhu leo, dhu bisa tao Kristus sue heka èdhi, do? Bisa boe! Masi ka èdhi paraga dènge lii langu do, sasusa do, manganga-mad'èu do, unu boe mèdha-papake do, mamadhe-mamopo do, dhèu neo pamadhe do, te ngaa Kristus sue èdhi taruu. Abhu boe èci sa dhu bisa pacèri èdhi nèti sasue Kristus.<bt>Probably/perhaps you think that there is person or, another way/thing/matter, that can make Kristus no longer love us, [tag question]? Impossible/no way! Even if/though we encounter a issue/dispute/ litigation or, difficulty/suffering or, hunger (doublet) or, not having clothes or, having misfortune (doublet) or, people wanting to murder [us] or [whatever], nevertheless Kristus keeps on loving us. There is not one thing that can separate us from the love of Kristus!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who shall separate us from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? Shall trouble, or hardship, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or danger, or sword?</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua suri tèke, peka na,<bt>In God2's Clean/Holy Writings it is written, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dhèu loe boe tenge j'ara neo pamadhe èdhi,<bt>&lt;&lt;People are looking for a way (to try) to murder us-inc,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lula èdhi j'aj'i dhèu unu Lamatua.<bt>because we have.become/are God2's people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Rèngu tao èdhi,<bt>They do to us,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nuka sèmi kalèbho dhu ra neo roro.&gt;&gt;<bt>like a sheep which they want to/are going to slice.it's.throat (the act of the first phase of slaughter [ritual or for meat]).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "For your sake we are in danger of death all the day long. We are treated like sheep that are going to be slaughtered."</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 44:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />De masi ka èdhi paraga dènge sasusa sèmi ngaa èèna ka, te ngaa èdhi segi le, lula Kristus sue èdhi titu kèna!<bt>So (consequently), even though we encounter whatever kind of difficulty, nevertheless we have already won/conquered, because Kristus loves us greatly!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No, in all these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ja'a ke'a mèu le, na, abhu boe j'ara èci sa dhu bisa hag'e eele sasue Lamatua nèti dedha èdhi. Masi ka èdhi mamuri do, èdhi madhe do, abhu ana pajuu nèti sorga do, dhu rèd'u paredha do, abhu koasa do, lii langu dhu j'aj'i limuri do, dhu j'aj'i bèli-camèd'a do,<bt>I know clearly that: there is not one thing that can make God2 set aside/separate2 His love for us. Whether we live or, we die or, there are underlings from heaven (=angels) or, those who hold rule/government or, there is a power/authority or, disputes/issues now or, disputes later or,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I am convinced that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I am convinced that neither death nor life, neither angels nor other rulers or powers, neither the present nor [things to come / the future],</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />koasa ètu dedha-liru do, koasa ètu rai-haha do, mèdha leo dhu Lamatua tao nare le -- abhu boe èci sa dhu bisa pacèri èdhi nèti Ama Lamatua, dhu kai Ne, sèna ka sue ia ka èdhi! Lula èdhi dhu pa'èki le dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, dhu Lamatua pua mai.<bt>powers in the sky (doublet) or, powers on the earth (doublet) or, other things which God2 has made, --- there is not a single thing which can separate us from God, which can prevent Him so that He does not love us anymore! Because we are bound/linked with our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: neither height nor depth, nor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: neither height nor depth, nor anything else in all creation, will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua hag'e nare dhèu Isra'el sèra<bt>God chose/selected out the Isra'el people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Èdhi dhu pa'èki dènge Kristus, padhai lii dhu lèke. De ja'a monya boe miu. D'ara iiki ja'a kahèi, peka na, Roh Lamatua dhu ator d'ara ja'a.<bt>We-inc who are bound/linked with Kristus, speak what is true/correct. So (consequently), I am not speaking emptily (=lying) to you-pl. My small insides (=conscience) also tells me that, God2's Spirit is steering/controlling my insides. [EXEG: on the switch from “I” to “we” in the 1st sentence, note Morris;' discussion about “as a Christian” being background for Paul's assertion; Moo's “as one united with Christ” being “the Christian reality from which he speaks”. The Gk. goes Positive-specific (I), Negative-specific (I). The Kupang deliberately goes Positive-generic principle (we-inc), Negative-specific (I), which is more natural for rephrasing in KM.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if “my conscience tells me” is too heavy, just say /Beta pung dalam hati ju kasi tau, bilang/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I speak the truth in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I speak the truth in Christ--I am not lying, my conscience [confirms/ testifies/ assures me] it to me in the Holy Spirit,</Message></Annotation><v n="2-3" />Ja'a peka sèmi ne'e ka: d'ara ja'a susa. Ja'a rasa bia, lula ja'a ngee kèdhi dhèu-dhèu ja'a mesa ku. Te ja'a neo sèna ka dhèu ja'a, dhèu Yahudi<bt>I'm telling like.this: my insides are distressed. I feel heavy/sad/ discouraged, because I remember my own people. Cuz (elaboration) I want that my own Yahudi people</bt><note reference="9:2-3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dhèu <span class="Italic">Yahudi,</span> èci èèna ka dènge bangsa Isra'el, nuka dhèu Yahudi dhu pea ètu rai Isra'el; aa dhu ètu era-era leo kahèi. Te ngaa suku <span class="Italic">Yahuda</span> sama boe dènge suku Yahudi. Te suku Yahuda, nuka èci nèti canguru dua suku Isra'el.<bt>The <span class="Italic">Yahudi</span> race/people group, is the same as the Isra'el race/people group, that is the Yahudi people who live in the land of Isra'el, and also in other places. But the tribe of <span class="Italic">Yahuda</span> is not the same as the Yahudi race/people group. Cuz (elaboration) the tribe of Yahuda, is one of the twelve tribes of Isra'el.</bt></note>sèra, pa'èki dènge Kristus kahèi, te ngaa ae dhu parcaya boe Nèngu. Ladhe sèmi ja'a dhu bisa bhoke j'ara hia rèngu, ja'a sadia manèngi ho Lamatua huku ja'a, sèna ka gati si. Aa ja'a sadia manèngi kahèi, sèna ka Lamatua hag'e eele ja'a nèti Kristus, ho rèngu bisa pa'èki dènge Ne.<bt>also becomes bound/linked with Kristus, but many don't believe in Him. If perchance [=hypothetical] I could open the path for them, I am prepared to request that God2 punish me, to replace them/in their place. And I am also/would also be prepared to request God2 to separate me from Kristus, so that they can become bound/linked with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: becauseI have great [sorrow /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: becauseI have great [sorrow / sadness / grief] and continual [anguish / sorrow / pain] in my heart. LITERALLY: For I could wish that I myself were cursed and cut off from Christ for the sake of my brothers, my own kinsmen in the flesh,<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>eeuchómeen: hypothetical, not saying that that's how it actually is, but what Paul would be willing to accept if that would help the others katà sárka: natural born relatives<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Aa te ngaa, rèngu se dhèu Isra'el, nuka bangsa èci dhu kalua hua iia titu kèna. Lamatua dhu ded'e le rèngu se, j'aj'i ana-ana Na karèi nèti katanga rai ka. Na pad'elo dadedha Na mi rèngu. Na pa'èki dènge ra rupa-rupa lii pajaji. Na pangèd'u si Atora Na. Rèngu ka dhu re'a mèu pahaha iisi mi Lamatua, aa sab'a hia Ne. Lamatua dhu pamoa le, neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi rèngu.<bt>Whereas in fact, they are the Isra'el people, that is a most fortunate race/people group. God2 has already raised/appointed/adopted them to be His children from long.ago. He showed his high-ness/glory to them. He bound/tied/made all.kinds of promises with them. He handed over His Law to them. They are the ones who know/knew how to worship Him, and serve/work for Him. God2 is the one who already promised that He wants to show His good insides grace/goodness/kindness) to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: who are the Israelites, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: who are the Israelites, who have been made children, and [received] the glory, and the [covenants / agreements], and the Law, and the [worship / spiritual service /religious service], and the promises, dóxa: glory, probably referring to God's awesome appearance in Exodus 14:22<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>diathéekai: not a contract they bargained over, but a mutually acceptable agreement on a take-it-or-leave it basis. The plural reflects the fact that the Israel people agreed to God's proposal three different times, at Sinai, just before they crossed the Jordan River, and again at Gerizim and Ebal, or else it reflects the series of covenants with Adam, Hoah, Abraham, and Moses latreía: the correct forms for public worship of God in the Tent and the Temple<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 4:21, 14:22</note><v n="5" />Dhèu Yahudi j'aj'aj'i ra nèti bèi-baki ji'i, nuka: Abraham, Isak dènge Yakob (dhèu rare ngara &lt;Isra'el&gt; nèti Yakob). Aa Kristus, dhu Lamatua pajaji mema karèi nèti uru-uru ka ho pua mai èèna, j'aj'aj'i Na nèti bèi-baki ji'i dhèu Yahudi kahèi. Kristus ne'e ka, Ama Lamatua kahèi dhu nèd'u paredha mi aa'i-aa'i se. De lèke, ladhe dhèu ded'e koa-kio hia Ne toke d'ai mia-mia. Lèke tare'a!<bt>The Yahudi people originated from our-exc ancestors, who were: Abraham, Isak, and Yakob (people take/got the name &lt;Isra'el&gt; from him). And Kristus, that one whom God2 had promised ahead.of.time long ago to send, also originated from our Yahudi ethnic group's ancestors. This Kristus, is also God who commands/rules/governs everything. So (consequently), it is appropriate if people lift up praises (doublet) to Him forever. Really! [NOTE: names plus Jacob = Isra'el for high-level cohesion setting up following verses &lt; HCE; EXEG: Christ--who is God (theos, not kurios) over all] [NOTE to daughter translations: check if you can streamline /ju turun datang dari botong bangsa Yahudi pung nene-moyang dong./ = /ju turun datang dari dong./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: From them are the [fathers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: From them are the [fathers / patriarchs], and from whom [came / was born] the Christ [according to the flesh / physically]; who is God over all--may he be [spoken well of / praised] forever, Amen! theòs: grammatically this is linked back to Christ, "the God who is in charge of everything, whom we praise from now to eternity". Most translations try to unlink them as "who is in charge of everything -- God be praised for ever", but then we would expect the article "ho" in front of theòs<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 32:22-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Masi ka abhu dhèu Isra'el ae ka dhu sèmi mèka Kristus, te ngaa dhèu bisa boe peka, na, lii pajaji Lamatua èèna j'aj'i boe. Baku ngee, na, dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu j'aj'i nèti bèi-baki Isra'el sèra, j'aj'i bangsa Isra'el dhu Ama Lamatua hag'e nare ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Na.<bt>Even though many Isra'el people have not yet accepted Kristus, nevertheless people cannot say that, that promise of God2's didn't happen/eventuate. Don't think that all people who originate from ancestor (doublet) Isra'el, are the Isra'el ethnic group that God chose to be/become His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is not as though"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is not as though God's Word had failed. For not all who are descended from Israel are Israel.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Nuka sèmi, dhèu ae-ae j'aj'aj'i ra nèti bèi-baki ji'i, Abraham. Te ngaa rèngu aa'i-aa'i j'aj'i boe ana-èpu d'èlu Abraham dhu Ama Lamatua hag'e nare. Te Lamatua dhu peka le dènge Abraham, aku Nèngu na, &lt;&lt;Ana-èpu èu dhu Ja'a tadhe, dhoka rèngu dhu j'aj'i nèti ana mu Isak di.&gt;&gt;<bt>For example, many people descended from our-exc ancestor Abraham. But they are not all Abraham's direct descendants (doublet) whom God2 chose. Cuz (elaboration) God2 had told Abraham, saying, &lt;&lt;Your-sg descendant/s whom I know/recognize, are only just those who descend from your child Isak.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nor are Abraham's descendants all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nor are Abraham's descendants all his children. On the contrary, "Through Isaac your offspring will be called." tékna: children without an article or a possessive (not "his children") in a section like this are more likely God's than Abraham's<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>all': on the contrary, rendered by "ony" inside the quotation</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 21:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sasoa na, karèi nèti uru d'ai sange ne'e, ana-èpu aa'i-aa'i boe nèti baki ji'i Abraham, dhu j'aj'i ana-ana Ama Lamatua. Dhodhoka ana-èpu dhu j'aj'i nèti lii pajaji Lamatua dènge Abraham di, dhu Lamatua tadhe. Rèngu ka di dhu j'aj'i ana-ana Lamatua dhu lèke.<bt>It means that, from previous.times until now, not all descendants (doublet) who come from grandfather Abraham, are the ones who are/become God's children. Only just the descendants (doublet) who were born/originated from God2's promise to Abraham, are the ones who God2 recognises/acknowledges.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That is, it is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That is, it is not the physical children that are God's children, but the children of the promise are [considered / counted] to be the offspring.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te Lamatua pa'èki lii pajaji dènge Abraham, peka na, &lt;&lt;Pe d'ai tèu mai nèi, Ja'a lèpa hari mai. Lod'o èèna dhèu èmu èu Sara nara iisi le ana mone ca dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 bound/tied a promise with Abraham, saying, &lt;&lt;Around next year, I will return. At that time, your wife Sara will already have given birth to a male child.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your wording in Gen. 18:10]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this was how the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this was how the promise was stated: "At this time I will come back, and Sarah will have a son."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 18:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Mesa boe èèna di. Te Isak dènge dhèu èmu na Ribka, nara iisi ana kajari dua.<bt>Not just that. Cuz (elaboration) Isak and his wife Ribka gave birth to twin children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana kajari dua = twins"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ana kajari dua = twins</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Not only that, but Rebecca's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Not only that, but Rebecca's children had one and the same father, our ancestor Isaac.</Message></Annotation><v n="11-12" />Lod'o Ribka nara iisi mèka ana na si, rèngu se dhae tao mèka j'ara dhu mola, do dhu bhelu. Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Lamatua peka uuru le dènge Ribka lula-nèti ana kajari dhu kalua uuru, peka na, &lt;&lt;Bèli-camèd'a a'a ne sab'a hia ari na.&gt;&gt; Lamatua peka sèmi èèna ho pad'elo, na, ladhe Nèngu hag'e nare le dhèu èci, Nèngu dhu ne'a le, neo pake dhèu ne sèna ka tao tasa mera mia. Hèia Lamatua pili ari na, j'aj'i dhèu unu Na. Lamatua parluu heka pamata, ho laladhe ari ne neo tao ngaa, lula Lamatua dhu ne'a mema le.<bt>When Ribka had not yet given birth to them, they had not yet done straight/good things or evil things. Even though that was the case, nevertheless God2 had already told ahead of time to Ribka about the twin child which came out first, saying, &lt;&lt;Later the elder.sibling will work for his younger.sibling.&gt;&gt; God2 told like.that, to show that, if He had already chosen a person, He already knew how/what He wanted to use that person to do. So, God2 chose that younger sibling to become His person. He didn't need to wait to see what that younger sibling was going to do, because God2 already knew ahead.of.time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Yet, before the twins were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Yet, before the twins were born or had done anything good or bad, in order that God's purpose in choosing might stand, not by works but by him who calls. She was told, "The older one will serve the younger one." the order of the parts in 11 and 12 in Pidgin makes it better to put them together, because there isn't a logical break at the same place there is in Greek<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 25:23</note><v n="13" />Te Lamatua dhu peka le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na, aku Nèngu na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 wrote in His Clean/Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ja'a pili kore le Yakob,<bt>&lt;&lt;I have chosen Yakob,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa Ja'a tule eele Esau.&gt;&gt;<bt>but I rejected Esau.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as it is written,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as it is written, "Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Meliaki 1:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />De èdhi peka tasamia? Ele boe cahag'e peka na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua pama'ète lii langu, bia cabèka, do?&gt;&gt; Bisa boe!<bt>So (consequently), what can we-inc say? Perhaps some say, &lt;&lt;God2 decides/judges cases/disputes heavy on one side (=biased/prejudiced)?&gt;&gt; Impossible/no way!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then shall we say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then shall we say? Is God unjust? Not at all!</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Te uru èèna, Ama Lamatua dhu peka le dènge Musa, na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) long ago God told Musa, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu paraga dènge sasusa,<bt>&lt;&lt;If there are people who encounter trouble/difficulty, [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure merciful actions are coming through in this verse, not just feelings of pity/compassion.] [implicit from meaning of “mercy” in Dhao (you have to have something going wrong before the idea of “mercy” can come into play)]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ja'a ka dhu pili neo pad'elo rasa kasia mi cee, aa Ja'a ka dhu pili neo bhoke d'ara Ja'a mi dhèu dhu Ja'a paj'uj'u unu Ku.&gt;&gt;<bt>I am the one who chooses to show pity/mercy toward whoever it is that I choose wanting to open My insides to the people that I myself have designated&gt;&gt;. [CHECK /dara mèke boe/ “mercy” “pity”?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara mèke boe = sonde sampe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dara mèke boe = sonde sampe hati, (Lit: sonde kuat pikul) (UNS berat hati, hati berat), rasa tertuduh jika tidak menolong ;bhoke dara = buka hati, hati tergugah (aroused)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dara Ja'a mèke boe dènge dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Dara Ja'a mèke boe dènge dhèu dhu Ja'a hag'e kore sèra.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he says to Moses,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he says to Moses, "I will have mercy on whom I have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 33:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />De dhèu ne'e rasa boe d'ara taleo Lamatua, lula dad'èi nèngu unu na, do, lula tatao unu na. Te ngaa lula Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu neo pad'elo d'ara taleo Na mi dhèu ne'e.<bt>So (consequently), that person doesn't feel/experience God2's patience/pity/mercy because of that person's own will, or because of his own deeds. But because its God2 himself who wants to show His patience/mercy/pity to that person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, it does not depend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, it does not depend on a person's desire or effort, but on God's mercy.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, Lamatua padhai lii dènge dhèu aae Masir, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a ded'e kore èu j'aj'i dhèu aae, lula Ja'a neo pake èu ho pad'elo koasa Ja'a mi dhèu ae-ae. Dènge sèmi èèna, dhèu dhu pale-lème rai-haha ne, bisa koa-kio kolongara Ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Clean/Holy Writings, God2 spoke to the king of Masir (Egypt), saying, &lt;&lt;I lift you-sg up/appointed to be king, because I want to use you to show My power to many people. In that way, people throughout the entire world can praise (doublet) My name/reputation.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Scripture says to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Scripture says to Pharoah, "I raised you up for this very purpose, that I might show my power in you, and that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 9:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />De ladhe Lamatua neo pad'elo rasa kasia Na mi dhèu èci, na, Nèngu tao. Aa ladhe Na neo tao d'ara ca dhèu adhu sèmi hadhu, na, Nèngu tao sèmi èèna kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), if God2 wants to show His mercy/pity to a person, na, He does so. And if he wants to make a person's insides hard like rock (unbending, unyielding--negatively valued), na, He just does that too.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, God has mercy on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, God has mercy on those whom he wants to have mercy, and he hardens those whom he wants to harden.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:16-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 7:7-9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua bisa pad'elo rasa kasia Na, te ngaa Na sèmi nare boe bhabhelu<bt>God2 can show His mercy/pity, but He also doesn't accept/put up with evil</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ladhe sèmi abhu dhèu dhu sisu ja'a, peka na, &lt;&lt;Kèri sèmi èèna, ladhe Lamatua neo ad'u j'ara èci, cee ka dhu bisa lab'a Ne? Aad'o, sina ma? De nga tao ka Nèngu neo pèci sasala mi dedha èdhi? Èèna adil boe!&gt;&gt;<bt>If perchance [hypothetical] there is a person who protests/argues with me, saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, if God2 wants to do something, who can oppose Him? No one, right? So (consequently), why does He want to accuse/blame us of wrong/sin? That's not just/fair (loan)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then will you say to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then will you say to me, "Why does God still blame us? For who can resist his will?" mémphetai: find fault, complain, blame<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ladhe abhu dhu pangee sèmi èèna, ja'a dhaa sèmi ne'e ka: &lt;&lt;Èu pangee na, èu ne cee?! Èu neo padhai lii lab'a Lamatua, do?&gt;&gt; Baku sèmi èèna! Te ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, abhu dhu suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe dhèu tao mèdha èci, abhu ètu mia mèdha ne karèi hari dhèu dhu tao ne peka na, &lt;Nga tao ka èu tao ja'a sèmi ne'e!?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>If there is someone thinking like that, I respond like this: &lt;&lt;Who do you-sg think you are?! You want to speak opposing God, huh?&gt;&gt; Don't (be/do/think) like that! Cuz (elaboration) in the Clean/Holy Writings it is written, saying, &lt;&lt;If a person makes a thing, how can that thing later ask in return to that person who made it, saying, &lt;&lt;Why did you-sg make me like this [+challenge]!?&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But who are you, O"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But who are you, O man, to talk back to God? "Shall what is [formed/ made] say to the one who formed it, 'Why have you made me like this?'" menóunge: used to answer a question when you have to correct the person asking the question -- he doesn't understand the situation<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:16, 45:9</note><v n="21" />Nuka sèmi dhèu tao èru rai. Nèti rai mea ca kahore, nèngu dènge hak tao g'ala dhu kale'e cue, sèna ka dhèu koa ne. Dhèu ne dènge hak kahèi, pake rai mea ca kahore ne tao era kaboko maruru èci, madhutu dad'èi na.<bt>For example, a clay pot maker. From one glump of clay, he has the right to make a shiny/fancy basin/jug for people to praise him/it. He also has the right to use that glump of clay to just make a place for collecting rubbish (=rubbish bin), according to his will/desire. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /hak/ doesn't collocate here, try /dia pili ko .../ (x2)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èru rai = thin, small, used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">èru rai = thin, small, used to cook, breaks easily ; g'ala = thick, larger, used to store sugar, lasts longer (can be years) ; ca kahore = a glump of (clay)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phyrámatos: a mixed quantity of something."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">phyrámatos: a mixed quantity of something. Here, it's clay and water mixed together until it is just gooey enough to work with smoothly. Also used of mixing ingredients for medicine, the mix beer is brewed from, and mixed wine. If they had made poi, they would have used this word timeén: to be honored, usually in public. In this case, a vessel that is honored by the use to which it is put<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>atimían: shame, disgrace, humiliation, dishonorable use. UBS suggests that it means 'everyday use', but that comes in only as one possibility with the adjective átimos 'dishonored, insignificant'. In the papyri all uses of the words in this family are pretty strong, including association with 'being reviled', 'confiscation and public shame', 'shame of prostitution' 'accursed', 'denied the right to vote' LITERALLY: Doesn't the potter have the right to make out of the same lump of clay one pot for special purposes and another for common use?<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge Ama Lamatua. Nèngu dènge hak ho tao madhutu dad'èi Na. Nèngu neo pad'elo mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i, na, Nèngu nasa, aa tule eele bhabhelu-katub'a dhu dhèu tao. Nèngu neo ho dhèu re'a kahèi, na, Nèngu unu koasa ae-ae. Sèna ka dhèu bisa re'a, Nèngu taha d'ara dènge dhèu dhu tao rupa-rupa bhabhelu-katub'a. Te ngaa mi dhèu bhelu-katub'a, dhoka mate lod'o di, ho ra ele iie aa'i.<bt>It's like that also with God. He has the right to do according to what He wants. He wants2 to show all people that, He is/gets angry, and rejects the evil (doublet) that people do. He also wants people to know that, He has a lot of power. So.that people can know, He restrains himself/shows patience with people who do all sorts of evil (doublet). But toward evil people, they are only waiting for the right time for them to be completely destroyed. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since God, wanting to show"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since God, wanting to show his wrath, and to make his power known, endured with much patience the objects of his wrath, which are prepared for destruction? skeúee: pots, same word as in the preceding verse. It shifts to a wider meaning here, "objects of wrath", but keeps the connection clear<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Lamatua ad'u-ue j'ara ne, ho paj'uj'u mi dhèu ae, na, Nèngu neo pad'elo rasa kasia Na mi dhèu cahag'e. Rèngu se'e ka dhu Na hag'e nare mema le, sèna ka ded'e si padedha-dedha. Aa Na neo sèna ka dhèu re'a, na, Nèngu mesa Na ka dhu dedha risi aa'i.<bt>God2 did like that, to show many people that, He wants to show His mercy/pity to some people. They are the ones whom He chose ahead of time to lift up high (exalt, glorify). And He wants people to know that, He himself is above all (highest/greatest/most glorious).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did this to make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did this to make the riches of his glory known on the objects of his mercy, whom he prepared in advance for glory. skeúee: just as in Verse 22, he continues the "pot" figure of speech to refer to people who were made with a certain purpose in mind. This time it's a good purpose<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>proeetoímasen: parallel to Verse 22, "ready", but with a twist -- God is the one who made them ready ahead of time eis dóxan: parallel to Verse 22's "ready fo get wipe out", but these other people are ready to be made glorious<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te èdhi se dhu Na pili nare le, ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Na. Èdhi se, cahag'e nèti dhèu Yahudi, aa cahag'e hari nèti dhèu leo rai kara.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc here, are the ones whom He chose ahead.of.time to become/be His people. We here, some are from the Yahudi people, and some from other ethnic.groups. [CHECK /kabhili/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabhili = (kuno) pisahkan, pilih (yg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kabhili = (kuno) pisahkan, pilih (yg terbaik dari yang baik, hini (seed)) (UNS not know)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we are the ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we are the ones whom he called, not only from the Jews, but also from the Gentiles. ex ethnóon: from various ethnic groups (not Jewish)<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Uru èèna, Lamatua pake dhèu nèti lii padhai Na, ngara na Hosea, ho suri dhèu leo rai kara sèra, peka na,<bt>Long ago, God2 used his spokesperson named Hosea, to write about other ethnic groups, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Abhu dhèu dhu uru èèna, unu boe Ja'a,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who were previously not My people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa Ja'a neo paroa kore si, na,<bt>but I am going to/want to call/summon them, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Miu se, dhèu Ja'a.&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are My people&gt;.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa abhu suku dhu uru èèna, Ja'a sue boe,<bt>And there are ethnic.groups which previously I didn't love,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ca nau-ca nadha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ca nau-ca nadha</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa Ja'a neo paroa kore si, na,<bt>but I am going to call/summon them, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Miu se, suku dhu Ja'a sue.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are ethnic.groups whom I love.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="laos: nation, people, crowd, commoners LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">laos: nation, people, crowd, commoners LITERALLY: As he says in Hosea, "I will call them 'my people' who are not my people, and 'my loved one' who is not my loved one"<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 2:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Hosea suri kahèi, na,<bt>Hosea also wrote, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ètu èèna,<bt>&lt;&lt;There,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ètu era dhu Lamatua peka dènge si, na,<bt>in the place that God2 has told them about, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Miu se, j'aj'i boe dhèu Ja'a!&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are not My people!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Pe Lamatua dhu Mamuri èèna, neo peka dènge si, aku Nèngu na,<bt>Later the God2 who Lives will tell them, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Limuri ne, miu j'aj'i le ana-ana Ja'a!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;Now, you have become My children!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 1:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Na peka sèmi èèna, lula Na kasia mi dhèu Yahudi boe sèra.<bt>He spoke like.that, because He pitied/had compassion on the non-Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And, &quot;It will happen that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And, "It will happen that in the place where it was said to them, 'You are not my people' they will be called 'children of the living God.'" erréthee autóis: it was said to them = God said to them, said in a respectful form that did not actually name God because that was kapu if you didn't have to name him<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Dhèu nèti lii padhai Lamatua èci hari, nuka Yesaya, peka nèdhi le lula-nèti suku Isra'el, na,<bt>Another spokesperson of God2's, that is Yesaya, once spoke about the Israel ethnic group, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Masi ka dhèu Isra'el ca nau-ca nadha,<bt>&lt;&lt;Even though the Isra'el people have become one heap/pile of alot [of people] (doublet),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nuka sèmi salae dhasi,<bt>like the sand on the sea shore,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">te ngaa bèli-camèd'a Ama Lamatua patabuli rèngu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra,<bt>nevertheless later God will save/rescue only just a few of them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhoka dhèu ciki di.<bt>from their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Isaiah crys out about Israel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Isaiah crys out about Israel, "Though the number of the Israelites is like the sand by the sea, only a small number will be saved. hypóleimma: a small number of survivors<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="28" />Te èèna d'ai lod'o na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the time is coming,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ho Ama Lamatua pama'ète lii langu nèti dhèu aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne,<bt>for God to decide the cases for every person in the whole world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama sèmi dhu Na peka mema le.<bt>just as He has made known beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te ngaa Na pamata heka,<bt>But He doesn't wait around/drag His heels,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te Na pamèci nare lai-lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) He brings it to completion quickly!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Lord will quickly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Lord will quickly carry out and finish his word in the world."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:27-28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 10:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Lod'o uru èèna, Yesaya peka le lula-nèti dhèu Yahudi sèra, aku nèngu na,<bt>Long ago, Yesaya also told about the Yahudi people, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Èdhi oto,<bt>&lt;&lt;We-inc are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lula Ama Lamatua dhu Koasa Risi Aa'i èèna,<bt>because God who is Most Powerful,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">soro tèke sèna ka ana-èpu èdhi cahag'e abhu sod'a.<bt>allowed/permitted some of our descendants (doublet) to live.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sod'a = mamuri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sod'a = mamuri</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ladhe aad'o sèmi èèna,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if it wasn't like that, well,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, èdhi se aad'o heka le,<bt>we would be completely annihilated,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nuka sèmi dhèu kota Sodom dènge kota Gomora sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>just like the people of Sodom city and Gomora city.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is just as Isaiah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is just as Isaiah said before, "If the Almighty Lord had not left us descendants, we would have become like Sodom, and we would have been like Gomorrah." sabaoòth: a Hebrew word for large numbers of people, used in the Old Testament for the heavenly armies of angels or the armies formed on earth when God's people had to fight, and carried over into Greek in this quotation<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>spérma: seed, used here of descendants who can carry on the family line</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 1:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii Lolo Be'a hia suku Isra'el dhu ro'o boe nanene Lamatua<bt>Good News for the Isra'el ethnic.group that doesn't want to listen to/obey God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />De èdhi neo peka ngaa? Èdhi neo peka, na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu Yahudi boe sèra mai nèti mia-mia. Uru èèna rèngu tenge boe j'ara ho pabe'a rèngu dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa limuri ne, ra pabe'a le dènge Ne, lula parcaya Yesus Kristus.<bt>So (consequently), what can we-inc say? Do we want to say, &lt;&lt;The non Yahudi people come from all over the place. Previously they didn't try to find a way to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. But now they are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, because they believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what shall we say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what shall we say? That the Gentiles, who did not go after righteousness, have obtained it, a righteousness which is by faith,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Te ngaa dhèu Isra'el sèra, neo ae le tenge j'ara sèna ka tao madhutu atora Musa, ho pabe'a rèngu dènge Lamatua, te ngaa j'aj'i boe.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the Isra'el people, already tried (hard) to do according to Moses' law, so that they could be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, but it didn't happen/eventuate/become reality. [EXEG: SSA, Moo, Morris]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Israel, who followed a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Israel, who followed a law of righteousness, has not obtained it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32-33" />Nga tao ka rèngu bisa boe pabe'a dènge Lamatua? Lula rèngu dhodhoka neo tao madhutu atora di, sèna ka Na sèmi nare si nuka sèmi dhèu dhu d'ara mola, te ngaa rèngu parcaya boe Yesus Kristus. Hèia rèngu oe sèmi kadhunu sa, lèke &lt;&lt;hadhu kadhunu&gt;&gt; cue. Ne'e ne ka naneo nèti Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, dhu peka na,<bt>Why couldn't they be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2? Because they only wanted to follow the law, so that He would accept them as a straight insides (righteous) person, but they didn't believe in Yesus Kristus. So, it's as if they stumbled on a &lt;&lt;stumbling stone&gt;&gt;. This is what is meant in God2's Clean/Holy Writings, saying, [SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kadhunu = terantuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kadhunu = terantuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ladhe ku sa ne'e!<bt>&lt;&lt;Look over here!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Ja'a pamadhèdi le ca Dhèu<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have placed a Person</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ètu ledhe Sion, nuka kota Yerusalem.<bt>on/at mount Sion, that is Yerusalem city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dhèu ne nuka sèmi hadhu cue,<bt>That Person is like a stone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhu dhèu kadhunu lèke Ne.<bt>that people stumble on/over.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ngaa cee dhu parcaya Ne,<bt>But whoever believes in Him, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nèngu parluu boe makae.&gt;&gt;<bt>[they] don't need to be ashamed.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hadhu ne, nuka Yesus. Te ngaa dhèu Isra'el tule eele Ne. Èèna na sama sèmi rèngu kadhunu, ka bèbha lula hadhu deo na.<bt>That aforementioned stone, is Yesus. But the Isra'el people rejected Him. That is like they stumbled, and then they fell (can be physical, moral, or social) because of that stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Why not? Because they did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Why not? Because they did not go after it by faith, but by works. They stumbled over "the stumbling stone". LITERALLY: As it is written, "Look! I lay in Zion a stumblingstone and a rock to make them fall. And the one who trusts in him will never be [ashamed / disappointed]."<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a neo dhèu Isra'el abhu ngaa? Ja'a sabaj'a ho hud'i laa Lamatua patalale rèngu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra. Ladhe j'aj'i ka sèmi èèna, d'ara ja'a heka karej'e kèna!<bt>Siblings! What do I desire for the Isra'el people? I pray may it be that God2 saves/rescues them from their wrongs (doublet). If that would happen, only.then my insides would be happy!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, my heart's desire and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, my heart's desire and prayer to God for them [the Israelites] is that they might be saved. eudokía: wish<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ja'a bisa peka j'ara-j'ara nèti tatao dhèu se'e: rèngu se maj'èni neo madhutu Ama Lamatua. Masi ka ra maj'èni sèmi èèna, te ngaa re'a mèu boe j'ara dhu lèke.<bt>I can tell about these people's ways/characteristics: they are diligent in wanting to follow/obey God. Even though they are diligent like that, nevertheless they don't really understand the true/right/correct way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I can testify about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I can testify about them that they are zealous for God, but their zeal is not based on knowledge. epígnoosin: not based on true knowledge, their understanding of how to serve God is not right<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Lula rèngu re'a boe j'ara mamuri dhu mola, dhu bisa pabe'a dhèu dènge Lamatua, nèti èèna ka dhèu se bhoke j'ara unu ra, ho neo sèku pabe'a dènge Lamatua. Dènge sèmi èèna, rèngu ro'o boe nanene Ne.<bt>Because they don't understand the life path that is straight/right/correct, which enables people to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, that is why they forge their own path trying to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. In that way, they don't want to listen to/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since thy were ignorant of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since thy were ignorant of the righteousness that comes from God, and going around to establish their own, they did not submit to God's righteousness. ouch hypetágeesan: they refused to submit<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ladhe dhèu madhutu dhoka atora di, sèna ka Lamatua sèmi nare si, na, èèna d'ai mèka. Nèti èèna ka, Kristus pamèci nare aa'i mèu-mèu le, sèna ka èdhi bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua. Ka limuri ne dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Kristus bisa pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua.<bt>If a person/someone only just follows/obeys the law, so that God2 will accept them, na, that's not enough. That's why Kristus has made everything complete/ whole, so that we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. So now, all people who believe in Kristus can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God. [EXEG: lots of debate in commentaries about scope of “law” in this verse. We go with “law of Moses” following SSA, Moo, Morris, TB, and context of vs.5, but leave it vague in same ways as Gk.][DISCOURSE: 1. Problem, 2. Solution. 3. General principle or state of affairs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Christ has brought the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Christ has brought the law to an end, so that there may be righteousness for everyone who believes. télos: the Law has no more value. Could also be that the goal that the Law was supposed to accomplish, Christ achieved for us; but in this chapter the emphasis is that just keeping the rules doesn't hack it<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua neo patabuli dhèu aa'i-aa'i nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra<bt>God2 wants to save all people from their wrongs (doublet)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Uru èèna, Musa pad'elo le j'ara ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, sèna ka dhèu bisa pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua, sad'i ra tao madhutu aa'i mèu-mèu Atora Lamatua. Nèngu suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu cee dhu tao madhutu aa'i Atora ne, bèli-camèd'a rèngu abhu mamuri mola.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then, long ago Musa already showed the way in the Clean/Holy Writings, so.that people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God, as.long.as they do according to absolutely every one of God2's Regulations. He wrote, saying, &lt;&lt;The person/whoever does according to all of these Regulations, later will obtain true life.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: here retain “God's Regs” because of how it's set up in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For Moses describes the righteousness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For Moses describes the righteousness which is from the law, that "the person who does these things will live by them."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 18:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Te ngaa Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua pad'elo j'ara leo, peka na, dhèu bisa pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua sad'i rèngu parcaya Yesus Kristus. Dhu suri tèke, na, &lt;&lt;Mage karèi, peka na, &lt;Cee ka dhu bisa ca'e asa sorga?&gt;&gt;&gt; (Èèna, nuka sèmi dhèu neo ca'e la'e peka dènge Kristus, na, èdhi dhèu rai-haha d'èi ladhe Nèngu puru mai sèna ka hia mamuri mi èdhi.)<bt>But God2's Clean/Holy Writings also shows another way, saying, people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God as.long.as they believe in Yesus Kristus. It is written, saying, &lt;&lt;Don't (weak prohibitive) ask, saying, &lt;So who will be able to go up to heaven?&gt;&gt;&gt; (That is as if people/person/someone wants to go up to tell Kristus, saying, we-inc humans are desiring that He comes down to save us/give us life.) [EXEG: clarify from high level context. NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the righteousness that is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the righteousness that is from faith says, "Do not say in your heart, 'Who will ascend into heaven?'" (that is, to bring Christ down),</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Sasuri Mola-Mèci suri kahèi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mage karèi, na &lt;Cee ka dhu neo puru la'e asa d'ara naraka, ètu era dhèu madhe sèra?&gt;&gt;&gt; (Èèna, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu puru la'e ho paca'e Kristus nèti era mamadhe Na, sèna ka hia mamuri mi èdhi.)<bt>The Holy Writings also writes, saying, &lt;&lt;Don't ask, saying, &lt;So who wants to/is going to go down into hell, to the place of dead people?&gt;&gt;&gt; (That is as if someone wants to go down to bring Kristus back up from His death to save us/give us life.) [EXEG: SSA; Problem: this is a misquote of Deut 30:13 (vs. 6 is from 30:12). Rather than say this is not quoting scripture (remove Barisi from the KM), which would skew the focus and raise unhelpful questions, note the following: In the grammar of the Gk, Paul is clearly including/subsuming the contents of vs.7 under his quote margin in vs.5, so the idea of a misquote of Deut 30:13 is both misrepresenting Paul and covering up or correcting his apparent ‘mistake’. What Paul has done here is a very common rabbinic thing to do. Moo points out that it is not as sloppy a misquote as it first appears in English, and that there are Aramaic paraphrases and other sources that do about the same thing, equating and substituting ‘abyss’ with ‘sea’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abysson: the Abyss of Hell LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">abysson: the Abyss of Hell LITERALLY: Or, "'Who will descend into the deep?'" (That is to bring Christ up from the dead).<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Baku sèmi èèna! Te ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci suri, na, &lt;&lt;Lii moa nèti Lamatua ètu katanga madha èu! Te lii moa èèna abhu le ètu hèb'a dènge d'ara èu.&gt;&gt; Lii moa ne dhu èdhi peka-padhai dènge dhèu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe èu neo abhu mamuri, na, hud'i parcaya ku Kristus!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's not necessary! Cuz (elaboration: grounds) in the Holy Writings it is written, saying, &lt;&lt;God's message/ instructions is right in front of our face! Cuz (elaboration) that message is already in your-sg mouth and in your insides.&gt;&gt; That is the message which we have told people, saying, “If you want to be saved, na, you-sg must believe in Kristus!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rheema: (specific) word, message, instructions LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">rheema: (specific) word, message, instructions LITERALLY: But what does it say? "The [word / message] is near you; it is in your mouth and in your heart", that is, the [word / message] of faith which we are proclaiming.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 30:12-14</note><v n="9" />Ladhe èu mangaku dènge hèb'a mu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Kristus èèna, Kètu ja'a,&gt;&gt; aa parcaya ètu d'ara èu, na, Ama Lamatua pamamuri hari le Yesus Kristus nèti mamadhe Na, ka Ama Lamatua patabuli èu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo èu.<bt>If you-sg acknowledge/confess using your own mouth, saying, &lt;&lt;That [known info] Yesus, is my Head/Leader,&gt;&gt; and you believe in your insides that, God has caused Yesus Kristus to live again from His death, then (loose ‘then’, not necessarily as consequence) God2 will save/rescue/release you from your wrongs/sins (doublet). [NOTE to daughter translations: Collocation: Some languages can only confess wrong [negative], not use this word to affirm s.t. positive (e.g. not confess that Jesus is Lord, but profess/declare...) So CHECK.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homologeesees: show yourself in agreement with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">homologeesees: show yourself in agreement with an idea. CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY: That if you [confess / profess] with your mouth "Jesus is Lord", and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te ladhe èu parcaya Kristus dènge d'ara kateme, Ama Lamatua cap èu, peka na, èu dhèu d'ara mola dhu pabe'a dènge Ne. Aa ladhe èu mangaku dènge hèb'a mu, peka na, Yesus j'aj'i Kètu èu, Ama Lamatua patabuli èu nèti koasa sasala-sasigo èu kahèi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if you-sg believe in Kristus with your whole insides (~wholeheartedly), God stamps/brands/ categorises you as a straight/*righteous person who is in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. And if you profess with your mouth, saying, Yesus is your Head/ Leader, God will save/rescue you from your wrongs (doublet). [NOTE to daughter translations: vs.9-10 retain chiasmus structure from Gk A B B A, Check if your lg needs to make it A B A B, or A A B B, but not lose the force of it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For it is with your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For it is with your heart that you believe and are justified, and it is with your mouth that you confess and are saved.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, dhu suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Cee dhu parcaya Ama Lamatua, bèli-camèd'a, na'e boe makae, lula Lamatua neo tao j'aj'i aa'i mèu-mèu, ngaa dhu Na peka nare le.&gt;&gt;<bt>In God2's Holy Writings it is written, saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever believes in God, later will not eat shame, because God2 wants to make happen everything which He has said.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: Last clause necessary for making sense in context, higher level; also HCE; SSA notes “In some languages a statement of the reason for or reference of the disappointment may be needed.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As the Scripture says, &quot;Whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As the Scripture says, "Whoever believes in him [God] will not be [put to shame / disappointed]." ou kataischyntheésetai: will not be put to shame<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:16</note><v n="12" />Dhèu Yahudi dènge dhèu Yahudi boe, èci èèna ka. Beda boe. Abhu dhoka Kètu èci di, aa Nèngu ka Kètu nèti suku aa'i-aa'i. Nèngu neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na ae-ae mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu manèngi bara nèti Nèngu.<bt>The Yahudi people, and the non Yahudi people, are the same. There is no difference. Cuz (elaboration) there is only one Head/Leader, and He is Head/Leader for all ethnic.groups. He wants to show His good insides (=grace, etc.) abundantly to all people who request help from Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For there is no difference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For there is no difference between Jew and Gentile. The same Lord is Lord of all, and richly blesses all who call on him.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci dhu suri, na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu manèngi Lamatua soru-bara si, pe Nèngu patabuli si nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the Holy Writings it is written, saying, &lt;&lt;All people who request help (doublet) from God2, later He will save/rescue them from their wrongs (doublet).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For &quot;Everyone who calls on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For "Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved." ónoma: name, the Lord himself, in Jewish usage it focusses on his essential character -- the name means something, and a well-applied name tells you what a person is like<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Te ngaa tasamia dhèu bisa manèngi bara nèti ca dhèu, ladhe rèngu dhae parcaya mèka ne? Aa tasamia rèngu bisa parcaya ne, ladhe rèngu dhae tadèngi mèka j'ara mamuri dhèu ne? Tasamia rèngu bisa tadèngi lula-nèti nèngu ne, ladhe abhu boe dhèu dhu lole dènge ra?<bt>But how can people request help from a person, if they don't yet believe in/trust him? And how can they believe in him, if they have not yet heard about his life (can include teachings as well as deeds)? How can they hear about him, if there is no one who tells them?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then how will they call"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then how will they call on the one they have not believed in? And how can they believe in the one they have not heard of. And how can they hear without someone preaching to them?</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Aa tasamia rèngu bisa lole dènge dhèu, ladhe abhu boe dhu pua-paleha si? Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe dhèu rèti mai Lii Lolo Be'a, mamai dhèu se'e se be'a titu kèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>How can they tell people, if there is no one who commissions them/sends them (out on a task) (doublet)? In the Holy Writings it says, &lt;&lt;If people bring the good news, their arrival/coming is exceedingly good!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: feet &gt; arrival, see Morris, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And how can they preach"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And how can they preach unless they are sent? As it is written, "How beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news!"</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Te ngaa miu kahèi me'a, na, abhu dhèu Isra'el cahag'e ro'o boe nanene Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua. Te Yesaya, ca dhèu dhu nèti lii padhai Lamatua, suri peka na,<bt>But you-pl already know that, there are some Isra'el people who don't want to listen to/obey God2's Good News. Cuz (elaboration) God2's spokesperson Yesaya writes, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lamatua!<bt>&lt;&lt;Lord/God2!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dhèu se'e ro'o boe lèka lii moa<bt>These people don't want to believe the message/instructions</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dhu rèngu tadèngi le nèti ji'i!&gt;&gt;<bt>which they have heard from us-exc!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But not all the Israelites"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But not all the Israelites responded to the good news. For Isaiah says, "Lord, who has believed our message?" hypeékousan: obeyed<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />De ladhe neo parcaya Ama Lamatua, na, hud'i nanene uuru ku Lii Holo-Nori Na. Aa neo me'a lii moa Na, hud'i tadèngi uuru ku lula-nèti Kristus.<bt>So (consequently), if [a person/you] want to believe in God, na, [he/she/you] must first hear His Words/ Teachings/Advice. And if they want to know His message/instructions, [they] must hear first about Kristus. [CHECK: would /lai lula/ work here?] [NOTE to daughter translations: experiment to see which sequencing works best for your RL/UNS's. /Orang musti dengar so'al Kristus dolo, baru dong bisa parcaya sang Dia. Ma musti ada yang kasi tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata dolu, baru dong bisa dengar./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lai lula = tentang (but many"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lai lula = tentang (but many younger UNS's not like it.)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then faith comes by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of Christ. ára: back to the main point<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>Christóu: UBS takes it as "the message about Christ" or "preaching about Christ", not "checking out what Christ actually said"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ja'a karèi sèku, sèmi ne'e: ele boe miu pangee, na, dhèu Isra'el sèra tadèngi rèdhi mèka lula-nèti Kristus, do? Tatu ra tadèngi le! Nuka sèmi dhèu dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, peka na,<bt>I want to ask like this: perhaps/probably you-pl are thinking that, the Isra'el people have never heard about Kristus, right? Of course they've already heard! Just like what is written in God2's Holy Writings from long ago, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dhèu rèti lii padhai Lamatua, dhu palolo lula-nèti Lamatua ne<bt>&lt;&lt;God2's spokespeople have told about God2 [EXEG: Gk “their voice” Is this to be taken in the context of Ps. 19 where it is the message of creation, or in the context of vs.14-17 above, where it is the msg of salvation brought by those who bring God's msg? Grammatically in the context of Romans, “their voice” goes back to the bringers of God's message of salvation in vs.14-17, irrespective of how it's used in Psalms. Moo points out “The implied object of the verb “heard” in Paul’s question must be “the word of Christ”; “their voice” and “their words” in the Psalm verse must then refer to the voices and words of Christian preachers (see vv. 14-16). Paul is not, then, simply using the text according to its original meaning. Note also TB “the voices of the bringers of the message…” The context in the Psalms doesn't trump the context in Romans in this instance. I (CEG) think the NLT solution disrupts and misses the flow of the argument in chapters 7-8.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pale-palème le rai-haha;<bt>has spread around the entire world;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lii rèngu<bt>Their words</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">d'ai aa'i le palème rai-haha toke d'ai suu-suu rai.&gt;&gt;<bt>have arrived at the world's corners (=farthest reaches).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I ask, &quot;Didn't they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I ask, "Didn't they hear?" Yes, of course! "Their voice has gone out into all the earth; their words to the ends of the world." oikouménees: inhabited world, not just the physical world<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 19:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ja'a neo karèi hari ca j'ara, &lt;&lt;Dhèu Isra'el sèra dhane rare mèka j'ara Ama Lamatua, do?&gt;&gt; Musa ka, dhèu uru j'ara dhu suri peka na, Lamatua peka mi dhèu Isra'el sèmi ne'e:<bt>I want to ask more thing, saying, &lt;&lt;The Isra'el people don't yet understand God's path/way, right?&gt;&gt; Musa, was the first person who wrote about that matter, saying, God2 told the people of Isra'el like this: [SSA, Morris, Moo]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dhane = mangarti, paham"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dhane = mangarti, paham</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ja'a neo tao j'ara èci<bt>&lt;&lt;I want to do one thing</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">hia dhèu nèti suku leo sèra.<bt>for people of other ethnic.groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">J'ara ne tao miu tèka d'ara.<bt>That thing will make your-pl insides jealous/ annoyed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa Ja'a neo tao j'ara èci,<bt>And I want to do one thing,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">hia dhèu dhu mi pangee na kahadhu ènyu.<bt>for people whom you consider turtle-brained (=dumb as a turtle/ox).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahadhu ènyu = turtle-brain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kahadhu ènyu = turtle-brain</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">J'ara ne tao miu kadhi ngutu.&gt;&gt;<bt>That thing will make you grind your teeth (=furious).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again I ask, &quot;Didn't Israel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again I ask, "Didn't Israel [know / understand]?" First, Moses says, "I will make you jealous [by / of] those that are not a people, and I will anger you by a foolish nation." asynétooi: who don't understand anything, stupid<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 32:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Limuri hari, Yesaya suri dhu paled'a risi lula-nèti dhèu Yahudi boe, dhu peka na,<bt>Later on, Yesaya wrote in a clear manner/openly about non-Jews, saying, [SSA, Morris, Moo]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Abhu dhèu dhu uru èèna tenge boe Ja'a,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who previously didn't seek Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa rèngu paraga le dènge Ja'a.<bt>but (contrary to expectation) they have been able to meet Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abhu dhèu dhu uru èèna manèngi boe ho rèdhi Ja'a,<bt>There are people who previously didn't request to see Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te ngaa Ja'a pad'elo iisi le mi rèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>but I will nevertheless reveal Myself to them.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Isaiah boldly says, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Isaiah boldly says, "I was found by those who did not seek me; I revealed myself to those who did not ask for me."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 65:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Te ngaa, lula-nèti dhèu Isra'el sèra, Lamatua peka le sèmi ne'e:<bt>But about the Isra'el people, God2 has already told like.this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Mèda-mèu, ai Ja'a dhu pakabhèle tèke,<bt>&lt;&lt;Night-and-day, I open My arms/hands widely,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakabèle tèke = hands facing down"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pakabèle tèke = hands facing down or up ; pakabhèle tèke = open handed (mau terima)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sèna ka tatae mamai dhèu Isra'el asa Ja'a.<bt>waiting eagerly for the Isra'el people to come to Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ngaa ro'o boe nanene Ja'a,<bt>But they don't want to listen to/obey Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa ra d'èi palab'a dènge Ja'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>and they also like to oppose Me.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But about Israel, he says,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But about Israel, he says, "All day long I have held out my hands to a disobedient and obstinate people." antilégonta: more like direct rebellion, not just complaining.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 65:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua rasa kasia mi dhèu Isra'el sèra<bt>God has compassion/pity on the Isra'el people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: ele boe miu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Lula dhèu Isra'el ro'o boe nanene Ama Lamatua, nèti èèna ka Na tule eele le si.&gt;&gt; Sèmi èèna ka, do? Aad'o! Te j'aj'aj'i ja'a nèti rèngu kahèi! Ja'a ne, nèti suku Benyamin. Ama Benyamin, nuka Yakob. Baki na, Isak, Ama Isak, ka Abraham, dhu j'aj'i bèi-baki nèti dhèu Isra'el aa'i-aa'i.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: perhaps/probably you are thinking, “Because the people of Isra'el do not want to listen to/obey God, that is why He has rejected them.” Like that, right? No! Cuz (elaboration) My origins are also from them (=normal way of saying this)! I here, am from the Benyamin tribe. Benyamin's father, was Yakob. His grandfather, was Isak. Isak's father, was Abraham, who is ancestor (doublet) of all the Isra'el people. [EXEG: Gk is Israelite, Abraham, Benjamin. If Israelite is to be taken as a reference to Jacob, RL norms require they be reordered. NLT has attractive solution in taking Israelite = Jew. But just mentioning Abraham and Benjamin in KM &amp; Dhao doesn't work, because the people know just enough to be dangerous. Local cultures around eastern Indonesia revere the ultimate founding father most (and rarely even mention others outside genealogies, unless with reference to some legendary exploit). and Paul clearly ascribes the founding identity of the Jews with Abraham, and sets up numerous arguments in Romans built on that, without mentioning Jacob. So shifting to elevate Jacob as the founding ancestor, rather than Abraham, I think is actually problematic in the context of Romans.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meè apoósato: he didn't push them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">meè apoósato: he didn't push them away, did he? reject, refuse to listen Benjamin was Abraham's great grandson: Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, Benjamin. The blood lines took their traditional names from Benjamin and his brothers<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: I ask, then, has God rejected his people? By no means! I myself am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, a member of the tribe of Benjamin.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Pilipi 3:5</note><v n="2" />Ama Lamatua tule eele nèdhi boe dhèu unu Na sèra. Rèngu se'e ka dhu Na tadhe karèi nèti uru-uru ka. Miu sanèd'e era, ngaa dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci lula-nèti Elia, si? Elia ka'uu-kamuki mi Lamatua lula-nèti dhèu Isra'el sèra, hèia na manèngi, sèna ka Lamatua huku si,<bt>God has never completely rejected his own people. They are the ones He knew/recognized ahead.of.time from long ago. You-pl still remember, what was written in the Holy Writings about Elia, right? He complained/grumbled (doublet) to God2 about the Isra'el people, and he requested that God2 punish them, [HCE, Morris: take action against]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ka'ugu = mengomel di belakang (not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">ka'ugu = mengomel di belakang (not to s.o.) ; ka'uu-kamuki</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: God has not rejected his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: God has not rejected his people whom he foreknew. Do you not know what the scripture says of Elijah, how he pleads with God against Israel?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />peka na,<bt>saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ama! Dhèu se pamadhe dhèu rèti lii padhai,<bt>&lt;&lt;Father! These people kill the spokespersons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhu Ama pua mai.<bt>whom Father (=you) have sent.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ra pa'ele iie le mei korban kahèi,<bt>They also destroy the sacrifice table (=altar),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ètu era dhu dhèu tema pahaha iisi mi Ama.<bt>in the place(s) where people normally worship Father (=you).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèti dhèu rèti lii padhai Lamatua aa'i-aa'i,<bt>From among all of God2's spokespersons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ate dhoka ja'a mesa-mesa ku di dhu mamuri.<bt>only just I alone who still lives.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te ngaa rèngu tenge j'ara,<bt>But they are looking for ways</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ho neo pamadhe ja'a kahèi!&gt;&gt;<bt>to try and kill me too!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “Lord, they have killed your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: “Lord, they have killed your prophets, they have demolished your altars; I alone am left, and they are seeking my life.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Dhèu Aae sèra 19:10, 14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Te ngaa Lamatua dhaa, peka na: &lt;&lt;Lii èu èèna, sala! Te dhèu dhu pahaha iisi mi Ja'a, abhu pidhu riho dhèu era. Rèngu se taha dènge èra, aa sogo-tagu boe Ba'al!&gt;&gt;<bt>But God2 responded/replied saying, &lt;&lt;What you are saying, is wrong! Cuz (elaboration) the people who worship Me, there are still seven thousand people. They endure strongly, and don't [traditional]worship (doublet) Ba'al!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if no /songgo/ word, try /sémba sang Ba'al pung patong/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But what is the divine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: But what is the divine reply to him? “I have kept for myself seven thousand who have not bowed the knee to Baal.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Dhèu Aae sèra 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Sèmi èèna kahèi limuri ne. Te dhèu Yahudi aa'i-aa'i boe dhu soro kabodho mi Ama Lamatua. Abhu ciki nèti ji'i era dhu Lamatua pili nare, sèna ka hia mamuri, lula Na neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ji'i, lula boe nèti tatao ji'i dhu be'a! Te ladhe Nèngu <span class="Italic">hud'i</span> pili nare ku ji'i lula tatao ji'i dhu be'a, sasoa na, Nèngu bisa boe pama'ète sèna ka neo pad'elo, do pad'elo boe, d'ara hua iia Na mi ji'i. Ladhe sèmi èèna, peka iia ka, na, &lt;Nèngu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na&gt;.<bt>It's like that also, now. Cuz (elaboration) not all Yahudi people have turned their backs on God. There are still a few people from us-exc (includes Paul) whom God2 has chosen to save/give life, because He wants to show His good insides (grace, etc) to us, not because we have done good things! Cuz (elaboration) if He <span class="Italic">must</span> choose us because of our good deeds, that means, He can't decide to show, or not show, His good insides (grace) to us. If that's the case, we can no longer say &lt;He shows His good insides (=grace)’.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="léimma: a few people left cháritos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">léimma: a few people left cháritos: just because he wants to, because he feels kindly toward them, acts graciously. Refers to his character, that he is basically for us and wants us to succeed<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: So too at the present time there is a remnant, chosen by grace. khariti: usually "like do good tings fo dem", but here the "give um chance" (mercy) component needs to be foregrounded to fit in with the rest of the context.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: But if it is by grace, it is no longer on the basis of works, otherwise grace would no longer be grace.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 7:7-8</note><v n="7" />De lala'e na sèmi ne'e ka: dhèu Yahudi ae ka dhu tenge-tenge j'ara ho Ama Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi rèngu, sèna ka rèngu bisa pabe'a kahèi dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa abhu boe, lula d'ara rèngu adhu sèmi hadhu, dènge ro'o boe nanene Lamatua. Te ngaa cahag'e nèti dhèu se abhu. Dhèu se'e ka dhu Lamatua hag'e nare si.<bt>So (consequently), in the end (of the journey/result) it's like.this: many Yahudi people keep seeking/trying to find ways for God to show His good insides (=grace) to them, so that they can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. But they don't obtain it/unable to obtain it, because their insides are hard like rock (hard-hearted, stubborn) and the don't want to listen to/obey God2. But there are some who obtain it. These are the ones whom God has chosen [NLT].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lala'e = 1) perjalanan, dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lala'e = 1) perjalanan, dia pung pergi 2) (UNS) tujuan, implikasi (GEN = sasoa) ; laloe1 = urut ; laloe2 = sasoa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What then? Israel failed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: What then? Israel failed to obtain what it was seeking. The elect obtained it, but the rest were hardened,</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, dhu suri lula-nèti dhèu kètu hadhu sèra, peka na,<bt>In God2's Holy Writings is written about those rock heads (=stubborn), saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lamatua hia si,<bt>&lt;&lt;God2 gave them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">musi madha dhu bisa boe ladhe rèdhi,<bt>eyes which cannot see,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ro'a dhilu dhu bisa boe tadèngi,<bt>ears which cannot hear,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa kahadhu dhu bisa boe pangee.<bt>and brains which cannot think.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">De rèngu re'a mèu iia boe,<bt>So (consequently), they don't really understand,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">toke d'ai sange ne'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>even until this day.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katanýxeoos: numbness, insensibility, insensitivity NRSV: as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">katanýxeoos: numbness, insensibility, insensitivity NRSV: as it is written, “God gave them a sluggish spirit, eyes that would not see and ears that would not hear, down to this very day.”<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 29:4, Yesaya 29:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dhèu aae Daud suri le kahèi lula-nèti dhèu Yahudi se, ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, na,<bt>King Daud also wrote about the Yahudi people in the Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Hud'i laa ho ra tao pesta ètu mei unu ra.<bt>&lt;&lt;Just let them [dismissive] feast at their own table.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te tatao rèngu ne'e ka dhu j'aj'i sasii ho sii hari rèngu,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it will be their own feast2 that ensnares them in return,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sasii = jerat ; sii ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sasii = jerat ; sii = hiki</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ka ra ngee na aa'i-aa'i se be'a le.<bt>so that they think everything is good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa nèti mèdha-panyau unu ra, ka dhu pasaleku rèngu.<bt>And their own belongings (doublet) which make them stumble. [NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakadhunu = pasaleku = bekin dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pakadhunu = pasaleku = bekin dong ta'antok</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And David says, “Let their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: And David says, “Let their table become a snare and a trap, a stumbling block and a retribution for them;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Hud'i laa sèna ka musi madha ra maroga,<bt>Just let their [dismissive] eyes become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ho rèdhi boe ngaa-ngaa!<bt>so they don't need to see anything!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Hud'i laa rèngu dui bia taruu,<bt>Just let them carry heavy burdens all the time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sèna ka kabodho ra asa kabhuku!&gt;&gt;<bt>so their back bones become even more bent over!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koe = bent (scoliosis, to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">koe = bent (scoliosis, to the side); kabhuku = bent (over like an old woman)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: let their eyes be darkened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see, and keep their backs forever bent.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 69:23-24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua neo hia mamuri mi dhèu Yahudi boe kahèi<bt>God2 wants to save non Yahudi people also</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: Nga tao ka dhèu Yahudi sèra kadhunu? Ra bèbha le, do? Aad'o! Te ngaa, lula rèngu ro'o boe nanene Ama Lamatua, aa ro'o boe parcaya Kristus, ne'e ne ka dhu bhoke j'ara hia dhèu Yahudi boe, sèna ka ra bisa abhu mamuri, lula Lamatua patabuli si nèti sasala ra. Nèti tatao Lamatua sèmi èèna, Nèngu neo ho dhèu Yahudi sèra tèka d'ara, hèia ra lèpa hari ho madhutu Ne.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like.this: why did the Yahudi people stumble? They've fallen (out of favour, incluence, position), right? No! But because they don't want to listen to/obey God, and don't want to believe in Kristus, that opens the path for non Yahudi people to be able to be saved because God2 rescues/releases them from their wrongs. By doing like that, God2 wants for the Yahudi people to be jealous/envious, and return to follow/obey2 Him again. [NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So I ask, have they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: So I ask, have they stumbled so as to fall? By no means! But through their stumbling salvation has come to the Gentiles, so as to make Israel jealous.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />De dhu mola na kèna, peka na, dhèu Yahudi se sisu ngaa dhu lèke. Nèti èèna ka, dhèu leo nèti palème rai-haha ne bisa rasa kakee-mamènyi d'ara hua iia Lamatua. De dhèu Yahudi rugi kapai. Te ngaa èèna tao dhèu Yahudi boe sèra oto titu kèna. De nèbhu-nèbhu, ladhe dhèu Yahudi aa'i-aa'i ra pabe'a hari dènge Lamatua, èèna be'a risi hari!<bt>So (consequently) it's clear that, the Yahudi people violated what was right/true. That's why other people from the entire world can taste/sense/experience the sweet flavour (doublet-symbolic of rich delicacies) of God2's good insides (=grace). So (consequently), the Yahudi people, lose out in a big way. But that makes the non Yahudi people gain.an.advantage/benefit greatly. So (consequently) eventually, if all the Yahudi people were also to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2, that would be even better!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèle = (lii pacèle) rugi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">mèle = (lii pacèle) rugi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now if their stumbling means"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now if their stumbling means riches for the world, and if their defeat means riches for Gentiles, how much more will their full inclusion mean!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ja'a neo peka j'ara èci dènge miu dhèu Yahudi boe, sèmi ne'e: Lamatua pua ja'a sèna ka, laku peka-padhai dènge miu, lula-nèti Lii Lolo Be'a Na. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a pa'èra ngi'u, sèna ka pakako sasab'a dhu be'a aae ne.<bt>I want to tell something to you-pl who are non Yahudi people, like this: God2 has commissioned/sent me to go tell you about His Good News. That's why I prepare/strengthen myself to carry out this work which is extremely good. [SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now I am speaking to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now I am speaking to you Gentiles. Inasmuch then as I am an apostle to the Gentiles, I glorify my ministry</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te ladhe ja'a pakako sasab'a ne dènge be'a, ja'a sanao sèna ka dhèu Yahudi unu ku tèka d'ara. Dènge j'ara sèmi ne'e, ja'a bisa bara rèngu cahag'e sèna ka abhu mamuri.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if I carry out this work well, I hope I will make my own Yahudi people jealous. In that way, I can help some of them get saved/life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parazeeloósoo: get them so worked up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">parazeeloósoo: get them so worked up they'll start thinking about it NRSV: in order to make my own people jealous, and thus save some of them.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ropa Lamatua tule eele dhèu unu Na, lod'o èèna kahèi Lamatua bhoke j'ara, sèna ka dhèu leo abhu j'ara ho maso j'aj'i dhèu unu Lamatua. Te ngaa èle èèna, ladhe sèmi rèngu padame hari dènge Lamatua, èèna be'a risi. Te èèna sama sèmi rèngu mamuri hari nèti mamadhe ra!<bt>When God2 rejected His own people, that opened the path so.that other people could get the opportunity so.that other people could enter becoming God2's people. But later, if.perchance [+hypothetical] they reconcile with God2, that is sooo good. Cuz (elaboration) that will be as if they have come back to life again from their deaths!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if their rejection is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if their rejection is the reconciliation of the world, what will their acceptance be but life from the dead!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Nuka sèmi dhèu neo tao roti. Ladhe nare tarigu ciki saraka mi Lamatua, èèna na roti se j'aj'i mola-mèci unu Lamatua. Aa ladhe dhèu hia amo aj'u èci, ho j'aj'i bua sulung mi Lamatua, èèna na aj'u ca kapua ne j'aj'i mola-mèci unu Lamatua kahèi.<bt>Take the example of a person wanting to make bread. If s/he takes a bit of flour and hands.it.over to God2, later all the bread [rolls/loaves-implicit: from that dough/flour] will be His possession that is clean/holy (doublet). And if a person gives a tree's root/s to become the first fruits offering (presented in thanksgiving) for God, later that entire tree will aso be His possession that is clean/holy. [CHECK /bua sulung/] [EXEG: SSA; Note: Morris notes that Num. 15:20-21 is talking about ground meal &gt; tarigu, but in the OT it is the bread that is consecrated, not the dough. The NLT seems to be jumping the gun on Paul a bit here. He's working towards that later, but here he's only giving a picture for comparison for starting in that direction.] [NOTE to daughter translations (to help picture context): Gk uses “part of dough” and “whole batch”. Picture a Jewish priest in NYC blessing one ball of uncooked dough, with the result that the whole batch of 600 bagels is blessed (that's what they actually do).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparkhee: first fruits NRSV: If the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">aparkhee: first fruits NRSV: If the part of the dough offered as first fruits is holy, then the whole batch is holy; and if the root is holy, then the branches also are holy.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ja'a neo pakasame dhèu Yahudi dènge aj'u saitun ca kapua dhu ra piara ètu d'ara oka. Ama Lamatua dhu tutu eele le dadana cahag'e nèti aj'u ne. Te ngaa miu dhu Yahudi boe, nuka sèmi saitun j'ami. Hèia, nèti dadana miu cahag'e, Lamatua pare nare ka la'e patapa mi aj'u dhu ètu d'ara oka deo na. Dènge j'ara ne, dadana nèti aj'u dhu ètu li'u oka, sakid'o nare mamuri nèti aj'u ètu d'ara oka deo na. Ne'e ne, èci èèna ka dènge miu dhu Yahudi boe, dhu sèmi mere d'ara hua iia Lamatua kahèi, dhu Na neo hia mi dhèu unu Na, dhèu Yahudi sèra.<bt>I want to compare the Yahudi ethnic.group with an olive (loan) tree that is cared for in a garden. God is the one who already cut and threw away some of that tree's branches. But you who are not Yahudi, are like a wild/jungle olive. So, some of your-pl branches God2 already cut and went patch/attach/fasten [you] on that aforementioned tree in the garden. In that way, the branches from the tree outside the garden, suck their life from the tree inside that garden. That is the same as you who are not Yahudi, who also receive God2's good insides (=grace), which He wants to give to His own people, the Yahudi people. [NLT] [NOTE to daughter translations: this is not like there is a beringin tree that happens to be in your garden, and one in the hutan, but one is deliberately planted and cared for, and the other grows wild. The one has larger and sweeter fruit. If a problem, try “dong piara” rather than “ada idop” in the first sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tutu = cut, slash (off branches),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tutu = cut, slash (off branches), cut firewood into sections ; patapa =tempel ; sakido = isap</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But if some of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: But if some of the branches were broken off, and you, a wild olive shoot, were grafted in their place to share the rich root of the olive tree,</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ngaa baku pamud'e! De mage mi padedha iisi, ho pangee na, miu dhu nèti li'u, be'a risi nèti dadana dhu Lamatua tutu eele sèra! Ladhe èu neo padedha iisi, mage èu bhèlu, te, èu ne dhoka ca dadana di! Èu boe ka dhu pa'èra kapua aj'u ne. Te amo ka dhu pa'èra aj'u ne!<bt>But be careful! Don't elevate yourselves (become arrogant), thinking you who are from outside are better than those branches which God2 has cut &amp; thrown away! If you-sg want to elevate (=praise) yourself up, don't forget, cuz (elaboration) you are only just one branch! It's not you who is making that tree strong. Cuz (elaboration) it's the roots that make that tree strong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bastázeis: provide continued assistance (not just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">bastázeis: provide continued assistance (not just physical support) NRSV: do not boast over the branches. If you do boast, remember that it is not you that support the root, but the root that supports you.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ele boe èu neo peka, na, &lt;&lt;Lamatua pare eele dadana èci nèti aj'u dhu muri ètu d'ara oka Na, sèna ka Na pakaj'èpe ja'a mi era deo na, ho gati dadana deo na.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-sg probably want to say, &lt;&lt;God2 cut &amp; threw away one branch from the tree that lives in His garden, so that He can patch/stick/attach me there in that place, to replace that aforementioned branch.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakaj'èpe = kasi tadempet, melekatkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pakaj'èpe = kasi tadempet, melekatkan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: You will say, “Branches were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: You will say, “Branches were broken off so that I might be grafted in.”</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Mema lèke. Te ngaa baku bhèlu, na, Lamatua tutu eele dadana sèra, lula rèngu parcaya boe Ne. Aa èu gati si, lula èu parcaya Nèngu. De baku padedha iisi! Be'a risi loe aa baku lela dedha!<bt>That's true. But don't forget that, God2 already cut &amp; threw away those branches, because they did not believe in Him. And you replaced them, because you believe in Him. So (consequently), don't elevate yourselves! It's better, you be careful, and don't fly high [+negative value]! [EXEG: SSA, MC; NEB. Gk /phobos/ 1) fear; 2) awe. Note NLT, CEV, TB, and context (the threat of being ‘cut off’) favour going with the primary sense here. Morris accepts the former, but prefers the latter. Moo describes this fear/awe as “and take up an attitude of fear. This basic biblical concept combines reverential respect for the God of majesty and glory with a healthy concern to continue to live out of the grace of God in our lives.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: That is true. They were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: That is true. They were broken off because of their unbelief, but you stand only through faith. So do not become proud, but stand in awe.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te dhèu Yahudi sèra nuka sèmi dadana dhu muri mema, dhu cèu uru tèka. Te ngaa Lamatua tèke eele boe si toke panèbhu ètu èèna. De ladhe èu parcaya boe taruu mi Lamatua, mage èu maena ho Na soro tèke èu taruu ètu èèna!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Yahudi people, are like the original branches which grew first. But God2 did not allow them to endure there long. So (consequently), if you-pl don't continue believing in God2, don't hope He will allow you to remain there continually!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if God did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if God did not spare the natural branches, perhaps he will not spare you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />De miu hud'i pangee pabe'a-be'a ku. Ama Lamatua mema d'ara hua iia. Te ngaa ne'a hia huku dhu bia kahèi. Pe Nèngu huku dhèu dhu manahu le, dhu pabe'a heka dènge Ne. Te ngaa mi miu dhèu Yahudi boe, Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na, sad'i miu pa'èki taruu dènge Ne, aa miu sèmi mere babe'a Na. Te ngaa ladhe miu sèmi mere boe j'ara sèmi èèna, Lamatua pare eele kahèi miu nèti aj'u Na.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must think carefully. God has good insides (=is gracious/kind/generous). But He also knows how to give out heavy/severe punishment. He later will punish the people who have fallen, who are not in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. But for you who are not Yahudi people, God2 shows His good insides to you, as.long.as you remain bound/linked with Him, and accept His goodness. But if you don't allow Him to do like that, God2 also will cut &amp; throw away you from His tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Note then the kindness and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Note then the kindness and the severity of God: severity toward those who have fallen, but God's kindness toward you, provided you continue in his kindness; otherwise you also will be cut off.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Sama sèmi èèna kahèi dènge dhèu Yahudi sèra. Ladhe ra ele-ho'a ka, ho mulai parcaya Kristus, pe Lamatua tape hari rèngu mi aj'u uru èèna. Te Nèngu dènge koasa ho bisa tao j'ara sèmi èèna!<bt>Like that also with the Yahudi people. If they *repent, in.order.to start believing in Kristus, later God2 will patch/attach them back on that original/first tree. Because He obviously has power to do like that! [SSA, MC; see vs. 20.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tape = tempel (earlier patape)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tape = tempel (earlier patape)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And even those of Israel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: And even those of Israel, if they do not persist in unbelief, will be grafted in, for God has the power to graft them in again.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te miu dhu dhèu Yahudi boe, nuka sèmi dadana nèti aj'u saitun hui, dhu muri tab'a ètu li'u oka. Te ngaa Lamatua hag'e nare miu, ka pakaj'èpe laa mi aj'u saitun dhu hua iia, dhu Na sèle ètu d'ara oka Na, sèna ka hud'i laa aj'u hui èèna leko-leo, aa aj'u ètu d'ara oka leko-leo. Te ladhe dhèu Yahudi boe, bisa j'aj'i sèmi sèra, ngaa hari dhèu Yahudi. Rèngu bisa risi eele hari, ladhe Lamatua pakaj'èpe hari si mi laa aj'u rèngu unu ra.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you-pl who are not Yahudi people, are the same as the branch from a jungle/wild olive tree that previously grew wild/on its own outside the garden. But God2 chose you-pl and patch/attach on the good olive tree, which He planted in His garden, even though the wild tree is different, and the inside garden tree is different. Cuz (elaboration) if non Yahudi people can become like that, even.more.so.with Yahudi people. It's even more possible, if God patches/attaches them again onto their own (original) tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tab'a = tumbuh dgn sendiri, tumbuh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tab'a = tumbuh dgn sendiri, tumbuh liar ; leko leo = berbeda, terpisah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if you have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if you have been cut from what is by nature a wild olive tree and grafted, contrary to nature, into a cultivated olive tree, how much more will these natural branches be grafted back into their own olive tree.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bèli-camèd'a dhèu Yahudi pabe'a hari dènge Lamatua<bt>Later the Yahudi people will be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />A'ari ètu Roma! Miu hud'i me'a ku ngaa dhu uru èèna j'aj'i mi rahasia. Te ladhe miu me'a, miu mage pakapai iisi, dhu peka na, miu d'èlu-mèu risi. Te j'ara na sèmi ne'e: limuri ne d'ara dhèu Yahudi, adhu sèmi hadhu, aa ro'o boe parcaya Kristus. Te ngaa rèngu bisa boe sèmi èèna taruu. Te ladhe dhèu Yahudi boe aa'i-aa'i dhu Ama Lamatua pili nare si, parcaya le Kristus, bèli-camèd'a dhèu Yahudi sèra parcaya Ne kahèi.<bt>Siblings in Roma! You-pl must understand this matter which previously was a secret. Cuz (elaboration) if you understand it, you won't elevate yourselves (be arrogant), thinking, that, you are smart/clever/wise/ knowledgable. Cuz (elaboration) it's like this: now, the Yahudi people's insides are hard like rocks (=stubborn), and they don't want to believe in Kristus. But they won't be like that forever. Cuz (elaboration) if/when all the non Yahudi people whom God has chosen have believed in Kristus, later the Yahudi people will also believe in Him. [EXEG: SSA, MC, high-level.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So that you may not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: So that you may not claim to be wiser than you are, brothers and sisters, I want you to understand this mystery: a hardening has come upon part of Israel, until the full number of the Gentiles has come in.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />De ladhe d'ai ka lod'o na, pe Lamatua patalale dhèu Yahudi aa'i-aa'i nèti koasa sasala-sasigo ra. J'ara ne'e j'aj'i, nuka sèmi dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, dhu peka na,<bt>So (consequently), if/when the time comes, later God2 will save/rescue all the Yahudi people from their wrongs (doublet). That is the same as is already written in the Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bèli-camèd'a Dhèu èci mai,<bt>&lt;&lt;Later a Person will come,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dhu patabuli èdhi nèti mamadhe-mamopo.<bt>who saves/rescues us-inc from misfortune (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèngu mai nèti ledhe Sion, nuka kota Yerusalem.<bt>He will come from mount Sion, that is Yerusalem city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èèna na, Nèngu ka dhu tao ho ana-èpu Yakob ele-ho'a.<bt>He is the one who later will make Yakob's descendants (doublet) repent.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te rèngu mamuri pusi-pahae boe Ja'a,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) they are living not caring about (doublet) Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">aa ra soro kabodho mi j'ara mamuri Ja'a dhu mola.<bt>and they have turned their backs on My life path that is straight/correct/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho rhuomenos: the one delivering, rescuing,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">ho rhuomenos: the one delivering, rescuing, with the implication that the danger in question is severe and acute asebeia: godlessness, ungodliness, live in a manner contrary to proper religious beliefs and practice<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>NRSV: And so all Israel will be saved; as it is written, “Out of Zion will come the Deliverer; he will banish ungodliness from Jacob.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 59:20-21</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="27" />Ja'a neo saku eele sasala-sasigo ra.<bt>I want to/am going to wipe/erase away their wrongs (doublet).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Ja'a pa'èki le lii padhadha dènge rèngu sèmi èèna ka.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I have bound/tied a promise with them like.that.&gt;&gt; [NLT -keep a covenant that was established long ago]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “And this is my covenant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: “And this is my covenant with them, when I take away their sins.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yermia 31:33-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Lod'o-lod'o dhèu Yahudi tadèngi Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua, ra tao iisi ra nuka sèmi musu dhu palab'a dènge Ne. Dènge sèmi ne'e ka, rèngu hia j'ara mi miu dhu Yahudi boe! Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa Lamatua sue si era, lula Na sue bèi-baki ra, aa Na hag'e nare si j'aj'i dhèu unu Na.<bt>Every time the Yahudi people hear God2's/Lord's Good News, they make themselves out to be enemies who oppose Him. In that way, they give a way for you who are not Yahudi! Even though that's the case, nevertheless God2 still loves them, because He loved their ancestors, and He chose them to become His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: As regards the gospel they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: As regards the gospel they are enemies of God for your sake; but as regards election they are beloved, for the sake of their ancestors;</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Te ladhe Ama Lamatua hia le mèdha èci, Na nare heka. Aa ladhe Na paroa nare le dhèu, peka na, &lt;&lt;Mai madhutu Ja'a! Mai asa d'ara ho j'aj'i dhèu Ja'a!&gt;&gt; Na babège eele heka si.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if God has given away a thing, He doesn't yank it back. And if He has called/summoned people, saying, &lt;&lt;Come, follow Me! Come inside and become My people!&gt;&gt; He doesn't evict them out anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for the gifts and the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: for the gifts and the calling of God are irrevocable.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Uru èèna, miu dhèu Yahudi boe, mo'o boe nanene Lamatua. Te ngaa limuri ne, miu sèmi mere rasa kasia nèti Lamatua, lula dhèu Yahudi ro'o boe nanene Ne.<bt>Formerly, you who were not Yahudi people did not want to hear/obey God2. But now, you-pl are the ones who have received God2's mercy/pity, because the Yahudi people are the ones who didn't want to listen/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Just as you were once"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Just as you were once disobedient to God but have now received mercy because of their disobedience,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />De rèngu se'e ka dhu limuri ne ro'o boe tao madhutu dad'èi Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, Lamatua neo pad'elo rasa kasia Na mi miu era. Aa bèli-camèd'a Nèngu neo pad'elo rasa kasia Na mi dedha rèngu kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), they are the ones who now don't want to follow God2's will. That's why God2 still wants to show his pity/mercy to you-pl. And later He also wants to show His pity/have compassion on them again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so they have now been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: so they have now been disobedient in order that, by the mercy shown to you, they too may now receive mercy.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Limuri ne, Lamatua tao ai-hèb'a mi dedha dhèu Yahudi, èci èèna ka dènge dhèu Yahudi boe. Te aa'i-aa'i ra tao boe madhutu dad'èi Na, nuka sèmi rèngu ètu d'ara babèdho, aa re'a boe j'ara kalua. Lamatua soro tèke si sèmi èèna, sèna ka Na bisa pad'elo rasa kasia Na mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra.<bt>Now, God2 attends to the Yahudi people the same as non Yahudi people. Cuz (elaboration) they all do not follow His will, just as if they were caged/trapped and don't know the way out (of their troubles/dilemma). God2 allows them to be like that, so He can show His mercy/pity to all people. [SSA + higher level resonance with previous chapters]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao ai-hèb'a = taruh perhatian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">tao ai-hèb'a = taruh perhatian</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For God has imprisoned all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For God has imprisoned all in disobedience so that he may be merciful to all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua ne be'a seli eele!<bt>God2 is so good!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="33" />Ama Lamatua d'èlu-mèu titu kèna!<bt>God is extremely smart/clever/wise!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa Na pake mamèu Na, sèna ka tao j'ara hua iia.<bt>And He uses His smartness/wisdom to do what is good/noble. [explicating ‘wisdom’]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu tadhe mèu Ne.<bt>There is no one who can truly know/be.familiar.with Him. [broad bridge]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abhu boe dhèu èci sa dhu ne'a mèu j'ara-j'ara dhu Lamatua pama'ète lii langu.<bt>There is no one who can truly know about His judging of cases. [specific]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abhu boe ca dhèu sa kahèi dhu ne'a mèu,<bt>There is not a single person either who clearly understands, [specific]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nga tao ka Lamatua ad'u-ue j'ara èci.<bt>why God2 does (doublet) something.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: O the depth of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: O the depth of the riches and wisdom and knowledge of God! How unsearchable are his judgments and how inscrutable his ways!</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="34" />Abhu boe dhèu èci sa dhu ne'a mèu ngangee Ama èdhi.<bt>There is no one who knows precisely our-inc Father's thinking.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu bisa holo Ne.<bt>There is not a single person either who can give advice to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sýmboulos: adviser NRSV: “For who has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">sýmboulos: adviser NRSV: “For who has known the mind of the Lord? Or who has been his counselor?”<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:13</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="35" />Abhu boe dhèu dhu bisa hia iia Lamatua mèdha èci.<bt>There is no one who can free.gift (verb) a thing to God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Abhu boe dhèu èci sa dhu bisa laka-seti Lamatua sèna ka Na b'ala hari!<bt>There is no one who can force God2 so that He [is obliged to] reciprocate back! [CHECK for examples.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proédooken: give somebody something to set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">proédooken: give somebody something to set up an obligation, so they will owe you something NRSV: “Or who has given a gift to him, to receive a gift in return?”<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 41:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="36" />Te aa'i-aa'i kapua ra nèti Ama Lamatua!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) everything is rooted/sourced in God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aa'i-aa'i j'aj'i, lula Nèngu ka!<bt>Everything happens/comes into being, because of Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aa'i-aa'i dhu èdhi tao,<bt>Everything we-inc do,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">èdhi sab'a hia Ne.<bt>we work for Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Èdhi koa-kio Ne,<bt>We praise (doublet) Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">taa-taa toke d'ai mia-mia!<bt>forever (doublet)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Lèke tare'a-re'a!<bt>That's really true!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For from him and through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For from him and through him and to him are all things. To him be the glory forever. Amen.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 8:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ladhe èdhi pa'èki dènge Kristus, mamuri hiu èdhi j'aj'i sèmi ngaa sa?<bt>If we-inc are bound/linked with Kristus, what must our new life like be like?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari dhu pasue! Ama Lamatua pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a manèngi sèna ka saraka mamuri miu kateme mi Lamatua, sama sèmi korban dhu mamuri. J'ara sèmi ne'e ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara Lamatua. Pa'èra ngi'u miu ho madhutu dad'èi Na, aa mamuri mola, te j'ara sèmi èèna ka dhu pad'elo sasue miu aa pakab'ua Ne. Mema lèke, ladhe miu pahaha iisi mi Nèngu sèmi èèna.<bt>Beloved siblings! God has shown his good insides (grace) toward us-inc. That's why I request that you-pl hand.over your whole/entire lives to Him, like a sacrifice that is alive. That is what makes God2's insides happy. Strengthen/prepare yourselves (=strive hard) to follow His will, and live straight/ clean/holy, cuz (elaboration) that shows your love and respect/ honour toward Him. It is really appropriate that you worship Him like that. [EXEG: SSA; see Message for whole chapter; “strive hard” is explication reflecting the force of “I appeal to you therefore…to present yourself…” which is a very strong exhortation to strive to do s.t. To be “holy and acceptable”, means to do things “according to His will” and “please Him”, among other things. They are not additions.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I appeal to you therefore,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: I appeal to you therefore, brothers and sisters, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to God, which is your spiritual worship.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Baku soro tèke ho dhèu rai-haha ne pua miu tao sèmi ne'e, do sèmi èèna, do mamuri sèmi ngaa sa, madhutu dad'èi d'ara ra. Baku sad'i madhutu iia d'ara di, j'ara ngangee ra, j'ara mamuri ra, do ad'a tatao ra. Te ngaa dhu be'a risi eele, ladhe miu soro tèke Lamatua ub'a ngangee miu j'aj'i hiu, sèna ka miu laladhe aa'i-aa'i se, madhutu j'ara hiu. Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu bisa me'a dad'èi Lamatua mi dedha miu. Te dad'èi Lamatua èèna, be'a, pamèci, dènge pakarej'e d'ara Na.<bt>Don't allow the people in the world now.a.days to order/command you-pl to do like this, or like that, or how to live, according to their own desires/passions/requirements. Don't just blindly follow their thinking, their lives, or, their (adat) customs. But it is better, if you allow God2 to change your thinking become new, so that you see everything, according to a new path/way. In that way, you can know/understand what God2's will is for you. Cuz (elaboration) God's will, is good, perfect/complete, and pleases His insides. [EXEG: MESSAGE. Philips. NOTE /suru/ may be a little strong, but we want something that reflects strong social pressure. Keep in mind that “be conformed” has both a weak sense “wind up doing what they do” and a strong sense “allow people to pressure you”. We want to reflect both, if we can.] [NOTE to daughter translations: 1) /sampurna/ can be unpacked as /langkáp/ or /sonde kurang satu apa ju/ (place latter at end). 2) if /bosong bisa tau Tuhan pung mau kasi bosong/ is difficult, try /Deng bagitu, bosong bisa tau apa yang Tuhan mau ko bosong bekin./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not be conformed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your minds, so that you may discern what is the will of God-what is good and acceptable and perfect.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Lula Lamatua pajuu le ja'a, aa pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ja'a, nèti èèna ka, ja'a peka dènge miu sèmi ne'e ka: lee ngi'u miu dènge j'ara dhu lèke! Baku padedha ngi'u risi nèti dhu lèke. Baku pake j'ara dhu dènge boe kolo-kapua. Dhèu èci-èci hud'i tenge j'ara ho ne'a mèu a'èra dènge karunya dhu Lamatua hia le mi nèngu, lula na parcaya Kristus.<bt>Because God2 has commissioned me and shown His good insides (grace) to me, that's why I tell you-pl, like.this: evaluate your own selves in a way that is true/ right/correct! Don't elevate yourselves up more than what is right/correct. Don't use ways/things/means which have no basis/foundation (doublet). Each person must try to understand the ability and special.gifting (loan) God2 has given him/her, because he/she believes in Kristus. [NLT][NOTE to daughter translations: Check carefully if using loan. Some equate /karunya/ with ‘grace’ (=anugerah) rather than ‘special gifting’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lee = nilei (dari introspeksi) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lee = nilei (dari introspeksi) ; a'èra = kekuatan ; koasa = power/authority ; karunya = abhu iia dara (get freely), grace (=anugerah)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="métron písteoos: God helps us trust"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">métron písteoos: God helps us trust him. How far have we gotten in trusting God? That is the measure by which we calibrate our real potential. If you have learned to trust God a lot, then you know what else you can trust him to do. You'll know it's not you that's doing it, so you won't get conceited about it. And you'll be realistic NRSV: For by the grace given to me I say to everyone among you not to think of yourself more highly than you ought to think, but to think with sober judgment, each according to the measure of faith that God has assigned.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tare pakasame dènge ngi'u dhèu. Ètu ngi'u ne, abhu bagian-bagian, dhu dènge sasab'a-la'a baka-leo.<bt>Take an example from a person's body. One body has various parts. And each part has different jobs/ responsibilities.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For as in one body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For as in one body we have many members, and not all the members have the same function,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, èdhi dhu pa'èki dènge Kristus. Èdhi se dhèu ae-ae, te ngaa pa'èki j'aj'i mi ngi'u èci. Aa dhèu èci-èci ka dènge sasab'a-la'a na, nuka sèmi bagian nèti ngi'u ne. Èci parluu èci. Tare conto nèti kacui-aai dhu poro pama'ète nèti ngi'u ne, gaguna na aad'o heka, si?<bt>It's like that also with us-inc who are bound/linked with Kristus. We are many people, but we are bound/linked/tied.together like one body. And each person has a different job/responsibility, just like the body's parts. Each one needs the other. For example, a hand that is cut off (&amp;separated) from the body, doesn't have a use anymore, right? [NOTE: NLT “needs each other”; Message explicates “linked to each other” saying “But as a chopped off finger we wouldn't amount to much, would we.” CHECK with team and UNS's if last sentence (from Message) is required to pull it all together.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so we, who are many,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: so we, who are many, are one body in Christ, and individually we are members one of another.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 12:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />A'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e: Lamatua pangèd'u èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti koasa, sèna ka pakako rupa-rupa sasab'a-la'a Na, lula Na d'èi pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi. Nuka sèmi, ladhe Lamatua hia èu koasa sèna ka èu peka lii moa Na, èu hud'i peka aa'i lii moa deo na. Te ngaa baku peka risi nèti lii moa èèna.<bt>My meaning/intent is like.this: God2 hands over power/authority to us-inc all in.order.to carry out all.sorts.of His jobs/responsibilities/work, because He likes to show His good insides (=grace) to us. For example, if God2 gives power to you-sg to tell His message/instructions, you must tell that entire message. But don't tell more than/beyond that message. [DISCOURSE: intro is discourse driven, shifting from general principle to explanation.] [EXEG: lots of debate re: “in proportion to faith” KM literal /iko lu pung parcaya/ “according to your belief/faith” was too broad/vague. See Morris, Moo, who come down on different sides. SSA gives both, but comes down on same side as Morris, NLT, etc. \cf added to address objections, as explication of “proportion/ analogous”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nuka sèmi, ladhe Lamatua hia èu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Nuka sèmi, ladhe Lamatua hia èu koasa sèna ka èu peka lii moa Na, aa èu parcaya èra Nèngu, na, èu kahèi hud'i peka padhai taruu, lii moa Na deo na.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We have gifts that differ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: We have gifts that differ according to the grace given to us: prophecy, in proportion to faith;</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:11, 24; 1 Korintus 14:29; 1 Yohanis 4:1-6</note><v n="7" />Ladhe Lamatua hia èu a'èra dènge karunya, ho lalau-lalo'o dhèu leo, èu hud'i lalau-lalo'o pake koasa deo na. Ladhe Na pala hia èu a'èra dènge karunya ho aj'a-nori dhèu lula-nèti Nèngu, na, èu hud'i aj'a-nori ku pake koasa deo na.<bt>If God2 gives ability and special gifting (loan--see note at end of verse) to you-sg to serve (doublet) other people, you must serve using that power. If He divides out ability and special gifting to you to teach (doublet) people about Him, na, you must teach using that power. [NOTE: BI word for spiritual.gift has right range of meaning and is widely entrenched, and used when speaking Dhao. we don't use it across the board for /charismata/ but intersperse it with "power" and “ability” to strengthen people's understanding in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="didáskoon: teaching not so much as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">didáskoon: teaching not so much as an occupation, like schoolteacher, but having the ability to teach within the church NRSV: ministry, in ministering; the teacher, in teaching;<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ladhe Na pala hia èu a'èra dènge karunya, ho pa'èra d'ara dhèu, èu hud'i pa'èra si pake koasa deo na. Ladhe Na hia èu koasa ho soru-bara dhèu leo dènge mèdha-panyau dhu èu unu, hia la mèdha-panyau sèra mi dhèu sèna ka èu soru-bara si. Ladhe Na hia èu a'èra dènge karunya ho pad'elo j'ara mi dhèu leo, sèna ka ra pakako sasab'a Lamatua dènge be'a, na, èu hud'i maj'èni ho pimpin si pake koasa deo na. Ladhe Na pala hia èu rasa kasia ho soru-bara dhèu dhu ètu d'ara sasusa, èu hud'i bara si dènge d'ara karej'e-karae.<bt>If He gives an ability and special gifting to you-sg to strengthen people's insides (=encourage), na, you must strengthen them using that power. If He gives power to you so you can help (doublet) other people with possessions/ belongings/wealth (doublet) which you have, na, give those possessions to help (doublet) them. If he gives ability and special gifting to you to show the way for people so that they carry out God2's work in a better manner, na, you must be diligent/industrious to lead (loan) using that power. If He gives you pity/ compassion to help (doublet) people in difficulty, na, you must help them with a joyful (doublet) liver. [CHECK pimpin.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if your lg has a way of saying “give your possessions (generously) to help them”. But be careful not to make it a heavy information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nuni = pull, lead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">nuni = pull, lead</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hilaróteeti: cheerful, happy, feel good about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">hilaróteeti: cheerful, happy, feel good about helping out NRSV: the exhorter, in exhortation; the giver, in generosity; the leader, in diligence; the compassionate, in cheerfulness.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 12:4-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu unu Kristus hud'i mamuri tasamia ku?<bt>How must Kristus' people live?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ladhe miu pad'elo sasue mi dhèu, na, tao dènge d'ara mola; baku peka leo tao leo. Core eele bhelu-katub'a, aa kèpe pa'èra-èra j'ara dhu be'a.<bt>If you-pl show love to people, na, do it with straight insides; don't say different do different (=hypocritical). Get rid of evil (doublet), and hold firmly to all good things/ways.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let love be genuine; hate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let love be genuine; hate what is evil, hold fast to what is good;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Miu dhèu sarani hud'i mamuri pasue ku èci dènge èci. Pa'èra iisi ho pad'elo pakab'ua miu èci dènge èci.<bt>You-pl (sarani) people (=Christians) must live loving each other sweetly/tenderly. Strengthen/prepare yourselves (=strive hard) to show your respect/honour to each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: love one another with mutual"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: love one another with mutual affection; outdo one another in showing honor.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ladhe miu sab'a, sab'a dènge d'ara kateme, baku dènge paloa-pad'ui. Hud'i laa sèna ka d'ara miu karae, lod'o miu ètu d'ara sasab'a-la'a. Aa miu hud'i sab'a hia Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>If you-pl work, work with full insides (wholeheartedly), don't do it half-half (=half heartedly) (doublet). Allow your insides to be happy/joyful while you are working. And you should work for our-inc Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus. [NOTE to daughter translations: depending on RL you might be able to combine last two sentences.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paloa-padui = satu lia satu, karja"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">paloa-padui = satu lia satu, karja ko sonde</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tóoi pneúmati zéontes: with great enthusiasm,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">tóoi pneúmati zéontes: with great enthusiasm, letting your spirit shine out, with an attitude of intense devotion NRSV: Do not lag in zeal, be ardent in spirit, serve the Lord.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />D'ara miu hud'i karej'e mèda-mèu, te miu me'a le, bèli-camèd'a Lamatua neo tao tasamia hia miu. Pa'èra d'ara ladhe abhu sasusa. Baku roca sabaj'a mèda-mèu.<bt>Your-pl insides must be happy day-night, cuz (elaboration) you already know what God2 wants to do for you. Strengthen/prepare yourselve if/when you encounter/experience difficulty. Don't get bored/tired of praying day-night. [EXEG: Gk is present active participle, which is on-going. This is reflected by “day-night” which means “continually” (See article on doublets in NTT). Aspect also supported by context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Like Philippians 4:4 NRSV: Rejoice in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Like Philippians 4:4 NRSV: Rejoice in hope, be patient in suffering, persevere in prayer.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Pake mèdha-panyau miu, ho bara dhèu sarani dhu parluu miu bara si. Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu mai nèti rae leo, hia ra'a-rinu, aa sèmi mere si sèna ka manubha ètu d'ara èmu mi. Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu pad'elo le sasue miu mi dedha rèngu.<bt>Use your possessions (doublet) to help the (sarani) Christian people who need it. If there are people who come from other places, give them food-drink, and receive them to stay.temporarily in your houses. In that way, you will show your love to them. [NLT, Message explicating hospitality]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teèn philoxenían dioókontes: going out of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">teèn philoxenían dioókontes: going out of your way to take care of visitors (may be referring to Christians, or just to strangers in general) NRSV: Contribute to the needs of the saints; extend hospitality to strangers.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ladhe abhu dhèu tino paj'èra miu, manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua hia si mèngi-nale. Tare'a! Baku dhoo si!<bt>If there are people who habitually cause difficulty to you-pl, request that God give them blessings. Really! Don't curse them! [CHECK /tino/ here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Bless those who persecute you;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Bless those who persecute you; bless and do not curse them.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:44, Lukas 6:28</note><v n="15" />Ladhe abhu dhu d'ara karej'e, na, karej'e sama-sama dènge ra. Aa ladhe abhu dhu tangi roma iisi, lula d'ara pèd'a, na, tangi sama-sama dènge ra.<bt>If there is a person whose insides are happy, na, follow.along (participate in) being happy with them. And if there is a person who weeps from sad insides, na, follow.along crying with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Rejoice with those who rejoice,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Rejoice with those who rejoice, weep with those who weep.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Mamuri pasue dènge d'ara èci. Baku padedha iisi. Be'a risi miu pa'angalai dènge dhèu haha. Baku padedha iisi ho pangee, na, dhoka èu di dhu me'a.<bt>Live loving each other with one insides (=in unity, harmony, accord). Don't elevate yourself (=be conceited). It's better, if you-pl be friends with the people who are low-bodies/socially unacceptable. Don't lift yourself up (=praise yourself) thinking, only you-sg yourself is the one who knows/understands. [CHECK dhèu haha vs. dhèu laku-laku boe.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Live in harmony with one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Live in harmony with one another; do not be haughty, but associate with the lowly; do not claim to be wiser than you are.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Hini 3:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu tao bhelu mi dedha èu, na, èu baku b'ala dènge bhabhelu kahèi. Te ngaa èu hud'i tenge j'ara dhu be'a, dhu dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa sèmi rare dènge d'ara karej'e.<bt>If people do evil to you-sg, na, you don't also reciprocate with evil. But you must keep trying to find the best way, which all people can accept/acknowledge happily.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not repay anyone evil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not repay anyone evil for evil, but take thought for what is noble in the sight of all.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ladhe bisa, na, tenge j'ara ho mamuri padame dènge dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra.<bt>If possible, na, look for way/s to live in mutual peace/reconciled with all people. [NOTE to daughter translations: SSA, Moo, Morris, Barth, and others all lean on the side of this being about peace in broken relationships with others. Therefore, be careful that your translations hit the side of /badame/ “restored relationships”, and avoid /damai-sejahtera/ that highlights “stability &amp; well-being (&amp; implying prosperity)”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If it is possible, so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: If it is possible, so far as it depends on you, live peaceably with all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />A'ari dhu pasue! Ladhe dhèu tao sala mi miu, na, baku b'ala ne. Soro tèke, sèna ka Lamatua ka dhu ator. Te Lamatua nasa ladhe dhèu tao bhelu-katub'a sama sèmi dhu suri ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na,<bt>[Note: vocative sets off new paragraph in RL discourse.] Beloved siblings! If someone does wrong to you-pl don't reciprocate (=don't take revenge). Just let it be so that it's God2 who arranges/handles it. Cuz (elaboration) God2 gets angry if people do evil (doublet), just like what is written in the Holy Writings, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mage bala tèka dara dènge tèka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Mage bala tèka dara dènge tèka dara.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ama Lamatua mesa Na ka dhu peka, na,<bt>&lt;&lt;God himself is the one who spoke, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ja'a ka dhu dènge hak ho b'ala sasala dhèu.<bt>I am the one who has the right to take revenge/respond to people's wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Ja'a ka dhu huku bhabhelu dhèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I am the one who punishes people's evils.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekdíkeesis: not God taking vengeance on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">ekdíkeesis: not God taking vengeance on people who hurt him or us, but on people who do bad NRSV: Beloved, never avenge yourselves, but leave room for the wrath of God; for it is written, “Vengeance is mine, I will repay, says the Lord.”<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 32:35</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dhu be'a risi ka, tao madhutu ngaa dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na,<bt>It's better (=polite command), to do according to what has been written (beforehand) in the Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ladhe musu èu manganga, na,<bt>&lt;&lt;If your-sg enemy is hungry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">hia ne na'a.<bt>na, give him/her food.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ladhe musu èu koko-kamango, na,<bt>If your enemy is thirsty,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koko-kamango = thirsty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">koko-kamango = thirsty</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">hia ne ninu.<bt>na, give him/her drink.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te ladhe tao ka sèmi èèna, nèngu makae unu na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if [you] do like.that, s/he will be embarrased/ashamed,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kadhu ai karoo = coals, embers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kadhu ai karoo = coals, embers ; karoo = still burning</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">aa na pakab'ua hari èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>and show respect back to you-sg. [SSA, Morris] [NOTE: some suggest change from singular to plural you--representing benefit to whole community of believers, but we couldn't make it work with several groups].&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Allusion to Psalm 140:10, burning coals?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Allusion to Psalm 140:10, burning coals? NRSV: No, “if your enemies are hungry, feed them; if they are thirsty, give them something to drink; for by doing this you will heap burning coals on their heads.”<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;nuka sèmi tao kadhu ai karoo mi kètu na.&gt;&gt; Madhutu dhèu d'èlu-mèu Alkitab, sasoa na, &lt;&lt;nèngu makae aa pakab'ua hari èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Greek language Alkitab writes, saying, “like you were putting burning coals on his/her head.” People who are knowledgeable about the Alkitab say that means, “he/she is embarrassed and he/she gives respect back to you-sg.”</bt></note><note reference="12:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 140:10, Lii Hini 25:21-22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Baku soro tèke bhabhelu ator èu. Be'a risi ladhe j'ara-j'ara dhu be'a ka dhu uli èu. Dènge j'ara ne'e, èu bisa segi madha j'ara dhu bhelu sèra.<bt>Don't allow evil things to control/manage/have oversight over you-sg. It's better if its just good things that control/steer you. In that way, you-sg can defeat those evil things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not be overcome by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nanene dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha<bt>Listen.to/obey people who hold authority/government/rule</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Dhèu aa'i-aa'i hud'i nanene ku atora nèti dhèu paredha. Te rèngu dènge hak aa koasa ho paredha dhèu. Te ngaa koasa èèna, mai nèti Ama Lamatua. Lula Lamatua ka dhu ded'e si, nèti èèna ka rèngu abhu koasa ho rèd'u paredha.<bt>Each/all person(s) must listen.to/obey the laws/regulations of those in government. Cuz (elaboration) they have the right and the power/ authority to command/govern people. But that power/authority comes from God. Because God2 is the one who has lifted them up (=appointed them), so that is why they have power/authority to hold government/rule.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let every person be subject"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let every person be subject to the governing authorities; for there is no authority except from God, and those authorities that exist have been instituted by God.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />De ladhe dhèu lab'a dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha, èci èèna ka rèngu lab'a dhu Lamatua ded'e nare le. Ladhe ra ad'u-ue j'ara sèmi èèna, bèli-camèd'a abhu huku nèti Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently), if/when people oppose people who hold authority like that, that is the same as if they were opposing what God2 has lifted up/appointed. If they do like that, later they will get punished from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore whoever resists authority resists"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore whoever resists authority resists what God has appointed, and those who resist will incur judgment.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ladhe miu tao j'ara dhu lèke, baku madha'u dènge dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha. Te ngaa ladhe miu ad'u j'ara bhelu, be'a risi miu madha'u dènge ra! De j'aga ngi'u ho tao dhu lèke, sèna ka miu baku madha'u dènge ra. Aa ladhe miu tao ka j'ara sèmi èèna, pe ra koa-kad'iri miu.<bt>If you-pl do what is right/true/correct, don't be afraid of people who hold authority. But if you-pl do evil, it's better you be afraid of them! So (consequently), watch/guard yourselves to do what is right/correct, so you don't need to be afraid of them. And if you do like that, they will praise (doublet) you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For rulers are not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For rulers are not a terror to good conduct, but to bad. Do you wish to have no fear of the authority? Then do what is good, and you will receive its approval;</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha, rèngu sèra ka dhu Lamatua hag'e nare si, ho ladhe-leru miu. Te ngaa ladhe miu loe boe nèti tao sala, be'a risi miu madha'u! Te rèngu dènge hak dhu iia d'ara boe ho huku miu. Rèngu, nuka sèmi ana pua-paleha Lamatua, sèna ka huku dhèu dhu ad'u-ue bhabhelu-katub'a. Te Lamatua sèmi nare boe bhabhelu dhu dhèu tao; Na nasa dènge ra.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the people who hold authority, they are the ones whom God2 chose to serve (doublet) you. But if you do not cease doing wrong, it's better you be fearful! Cuz (elaboration) they are the ones who have the right which isn't pointless/ineffectual to punish you. They are like God2's servants (doublet) (people who carry out orders) to punish people who do (doublet) evil (doublet). Cuz (elaboration) God2 doesn't accept/put up with the evil which people do; He gets angry at them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for it is God's servant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: for it is God's servant for your good. But if you do what is wrong, you should be afraid, for the authority does not bear the sword in vain! It is the servant of God to execute wrath on the wrongdoer.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Nèti èèna ka, miu hud'i nanene ku, mi dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha. Te miu dhu me'a mèu le, èèna ka dhu lèke mola-mola. Aa miu me'a kahèi, na, Lamatua nasa, ladhe èdhi tao boe dhu lèke.<bt>That's why you-pl must listen.to/obey the people who hold authority. Cuz (elaboration) you already know clearly that, that is what is right/correct. And you also know that, God2 get's angry if/when we-inc (general principle) do not do what is right/correct. [NOTE, discourse: vs.5 separate paragraph because of 1) its genre as summary, recapitulation, and 2) the way it relates to both preceding and following verses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore one must be subject,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore one must be subject, not only because of wrath but also because of conscience.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, miu hud'i b'ae bea dhu madhutu atora, lula dhèu dhu rèd'u paredha sèra, pakako sasab'a Lamatua.<bt>In the same way also, you must pay tax which is according to laws/regulations, because the people who hold authority are carrying out God2's work. [NOTE to daughter translations: 1) /pajak/ not same as /bapajak/ “arbitrary financial demands from people in uniform”; avoid sense of have to pay /orang yang bapajak sang lu/. 2) if /sah/ is difficult, try /yang iko atoran/ or /yang batúl/.] [EXEG: Gk is not /doulos/ or other noun for “servant” here, but rather a verb “in close personal attendance”. Avoid “carrying out the will of God”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For the same reason you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For the same reason you also pay taxes, for the authorities are God's servants, busy with this very thing.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />De miu hud'i b'ae aa'i-aa'i dhu lèke madhutu atora. B'ae hia dhèu roro bea sèra, bea aa'i-aa'i dhu miu hud'i b'ae ku. Pakab'ua mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu mema nia sèmi lii pakab'ua. Aa ladhe abhu dhèu dhu tao j'ara be'a taruu, ded'e padedha kolongara si, sèna ka dhèu re'a, na, rèngu tao j'ara dhu be'a.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must pay everything which is right according to the laws/regulations. Pay the tax collectors, all the tax which you must/are required to pay. (Show) respect for all people who are appropriate to receive respect. And if there are people who continually do good things, lift up their name/reputation (=praise them/say good things about them/promote them) so everyone will know they are doing what is good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Pay to all what is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Pay to all what is due them-taxes to whom taxes are due, revenue to whom revenue is due, respect to whom respect is due, honor to whom honor is due.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:21, Markus 12:17, Lukas 20:25</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mamuri pasue èci dènge èci<bt>Live mutually loving each other</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />B'ae pama'ète kèlu èu aa'i-aa'i, sèna ka baku mamuri ètu d'ara kèlu-g'ètu. Te èdhi pakèlu dhoka ètu ca madha j'ara di, nuka pasue. Ladhe miu sue dhèu, miu tao le madhutu Atora-atora nèti Lamatua.<bt>Pay in full all your-sg debts, in.order.to not live in debt. Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are only indebted in just one thing, which is mutual.love. If you love people, na, you are already doing according to God2's laws/regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Owe no one anything, except"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Owe no one anything, except to love one another; for the one who loves another has fulfilled the law.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te Atora sèra peka na, &lt;&lt;Baku tao j'ara makae dènge dhèu dhu j'aj'i boe dhèu èmu-kamali mu; baku pamadhe dhèu; baku mana'u; baku d'èi leli neo unu mèdha-panyau dhèu,&gt;&gt; aa dhu leo hari. Ladhe neo madhutu aa'i Atora se'e, hud'i tao madhutu ku Atora èci ne'e, dhu peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu hud'i sue ku dhèu leo, nuka sèmi èu sue ngi'u èu unu mu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) those Laws/ Regulations say, &lt;&lt;Don't do the shameful way (sexually-euphemism) with a person who is not your spouse; don't kill people; don't steal; don't desire to get other people's things (doublet),&gt;&gt; and other issues as well. If you want to follow all those Regulations, [you] must follow this one Regulation which says, &lt;&lt;You-sg must love other people, the same as you love your own self.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapeeseis ...: Matthew 22:39 NRSV: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">agapeeseis ...: Matthew 22:39 NRSV: The commandments, “You shall not commit adultery; You shall not murder; You shall not steal; You shall not covet”; and any other commandment, are summed up in this word, “Love your neighbor as yourself.”<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 20:13-15, 17, Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 5:17-19, 21, Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 19:18, Mateos 22:39, Markus 12:29-31</note><v n="10" />Te ladhe èdhi pad'elo sasue mi dhèu leo, èdhi tao boe bhelu mi nèngu, si? De ladhe èdhi loe boe pad'elo sasue èdhi, èdhi bisa tao madhutu aa'i Atora Lamatua.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc show love to another person, we don't do evil to him/her, right? So (consequently), if we-inc do not cease showing our love, we can do according to all the Regulations from God2. [NOTE: 1pi for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Love does no wrong to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Love does no wrong to a neighbor; therefore, love is the fulfilling of the law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus nèbhu heka lèpa hari mai<bt>Kristus will soon come back again</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ama Lamatua neo patabuli èdhi nèti bhabhelu-katub'a dhèu rai-haha. Aa limuri ne, lod'o sèna ka dhèu abhu mamuri nèti Lamatua dètu ae le, ladhe èdhi pasoro dènge lod'o dhu èdhi heka parcaya Yesus Kristus. Nèti èèna ka, èdhi hud'i mamuri pasue, lula èdhi te'a le madha j'ara ne'e. Nuka sèmi uru èèna, èdhi dhu bhèj'i era. Te ngaa limuri ne d'ai le lod'o na, ho èdhi kèd'i ka nèti bhabhèj'i èdhi!<bt>God wants to free/deliver/save us from the evil (doublet) of the people in this world. And now, the time for the Lord to save2 people is really close compared to when we-inc had just believed in Yesus Kristus. That's why we-inc [genre] must live mutually loving each other, because we understand this matter. It's as if formerly, we-inc were still sleeping. But now, the time has arrived for us to wake up from our sleep! [EXEG: on “salvation is nearer”, see Uma, and discussion in SSA and Moo.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Besides this, you know what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Besides this, you know what time it is, how it is now the moment for you to wake from sleep. For salvation is nearer to us now than when we became believers;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lod'o ho dhèu abhu mamuri dètu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">lod'o ho dhèu abhu mamuri dètu ae le,</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Nèbhu boe, te mèda oe èle kèna, aa lod'o rea kèna. De be'a risi èdhi ae eele ka nèti bhabhelu-katub'a èdhi. J'ara ne, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu mamuri ètu d'ara maroga, aa ad'u-ue madha j'ara bhabhelu, te rèngu pangee, na, abhu boe dhu ladhe rèdhi tatao rèngu sèra. Te ngaa limuri ne, èdhi hud'i j'aj'i ku sama sèmi sordad'u dhu bori mema mèdha-papake pamusu, ho pa'èra ngi'u sèna ka tao j'ara dhu be'a, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu mamuri ètu d'ara saraa.<bt>Soon the night is nearly ending, and then daylight will have come. So (consequently), it's better/best, if we-inc stop already from our evils (doublet) [+mild (Yiddish) imperative :-)]. It's like people living in the dark and doing evil things, cuz (elaboration) they think there is no one who sees their deeds/behaviour. But now, we must become like soldiers who fasten on the things (doublet) of war, to strengthen/prepare ourselves (=try hard, strive) to do good things, like people who live in the light.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bori = lit. ikat (di pinggang),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">bori = lit. ikat (di pinggang), but here lengkapi diri</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: the night is far gone,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: the night is far gone, the day is near. Let us then lay aside the works of darkness and put on the armor of light;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Èdhi hud'i mamuri mola ku, sèna ka dhèu aa'i-aa'i bisa rèdhi, na, èdhi dhu tao j'ara be'a. Be'a boe ladhe èdhi mamuri dhoka ètu d'ara tao pesta, dènge tinu mahu di. Be'a boe ladhe èdhi tao j'ara makae. Be'a boe ladhe bau lii langu g'ana-kariu. Aa be'a boe ladhe èdhi tèka d'ara, lula èdhi d'èi boe dhèu risi èdhi.<bt>We-inc must live straight/right/correct, so.that all people can see that we are doing good things. It's not good if we live only to have feasts/parties, and just drink getting drunk. It's not good if we do shameful things (sexually). It's not good if we argue/dispute left-right (=with everyone). And it's not good if we are jealous/veangeful because we don't like people to exceed (=be better/higher ranking than) us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: let us live honorably as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: let us live honorably as in the day, not in reveling and drunkenness, not in debauchery and licentiousness, not in quarreling and jealousy.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te ngaa dhu be'a risi ka, miu ub'a d'ara miu, ho j'aj'i sama sèmi Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, dhu Lamatua pua mai. Aa ladhe èu neo ad'u-ue j'ara dhu lèke boe, na, taha d'ara mu! Mage soro tèke ho madhutu dad'èi mu dhu lèke boe j'ara.<bt>But its better/best, if you-pl change your insides to become like our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent. And if you-sg are desiring/longing to do something that is not right/correct, na, restrain yourself! Don't let yourself follow your own desires that are not right/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabèli = balik hati (kurang lazim)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kabèli = balik hati (kurang lazim) ; ALT: baku golo...</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Instead, put on the Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Instead, put on the Lord Jesus Christ, and make no provision for the flesh, to gratify its desires.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Baku kahèti leli a'ari miu dhèu Kristen<bt>Don't thoughtlessly/arbitrarily criticize your Christian siblings [CHECK /kahèti/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK (not used alot)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">CHECK (not used alot)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Abhu dhu parcaya Lamatua, te ngaa parcaya na èra mèka, aa j'ara ae ka dhu ne'a mèka. Pakabhèle ai èu ho sèmi more ne dènge d'ara kateme. Baku sisu ngaa dhu na peka-padhai. Hud'i laa nèngu pa'angalai dènge miu.<bt>There is a person who already believes in God2, but his belief is not yet strong, and s/he does not yet understand many things. Open your-sg arms to receive him/her in with your whole insides (wholeheartedly/sincerely). Don't argue about his/her thinking. Just allow him/her to be mutual friends with you-pl. [NOTE to daughter translations: Evaluate with team a) use /sodara/ throughout this passage to emphasize that the issues are between believers, BUT b) will /sodara/ skew it for some people to think we are only talking about KIN WHO BELIEVE (??), and does not include non-kin?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kahèti = fiti, kuti ; pakabhèle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kahèti = fiti, kuti ; pakabhèle ai = (symbolic action of welcoming) ; kuri-kuri = kurang kuat (young UNS have heard, but not sure of meaning)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proslambánesthe: make him feel welcome as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">proslambánesthe: make him feel welcome as a member of the Christian community NRSV: Welcome those who are weak in faith, but not for the purpose of quarreling over opinions.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Abhu dhu parcaya Lamatua, dhu pangee na, dhèu sarani bisa ra'a ngaa sa, nuka sèmi sisi, do ngaa èèna ka. Te ngaa abhu dhèu sarani leo, dhu parcaya ra èra mèka, dhu ra'a dhoka sayur di. Te ra luri sisi.<bt>There are people who believe in God2, who think that, /sarani/ (=Kristen) people can eat whatever, like meat or, whatever. But there are other Christians, whose belief is not strong, who only want to just eat vegetables (loan to get generic). Cuz (elaboration) they are in a taboo relationship with meat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèu aaj'u = leaves, leafy vegetable"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">rèu aaj'u = leaves, leafy vegetable (AND lii pacele = nidhu)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="láchana: vegetables, vegetarian diet NRSV: Some"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">láchana: vegetables, vegetarian diet NRSV: Some believe in eating anything, while the weak eat only vegetables.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te ngaa nanene, ee! Dhèu sarani dhu bisa ra'a ngaa èèna ka, baku pahahe dhèu dhu neo boe ra'a sisi. Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge dhèu sarani dhu neo boe ra'a sisi, baku peka dènge dhèu dhu bisa ra'a sisi, na, &lt;&lt;Weh! Mu'a sisi, sala!&gt;&gt; Lula Ama Lamatua sèmi nare le dua ra ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Na!<bt>But listen up, ee! A *Christian (lexicalised: baptised person, used primarily used to distinguish from people of other faiths) who feels he/she can eat whatever, should not look down on/despise people who don't want to eat meat. Like that also, Christians who don't want to eat meat, shouldn't tell people who can eat meat, saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+critical] Eating meat, is wrong!&gt;&gt; Because God has already accepted both of them to be His people! [NOTE: /ra'a sisi/ = 1) eat meat, 2) feast]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meè exoutheneítoo: let him not treat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">meè exoutheneítoo: let him not treat the other person like that person is not worth anything. A very strong word meè krinétoo: let him not pass judgment on the other person<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>NRSV: Those who eat must not despise those who abstain, and those who abstain must not pass judgment on those who eat; for God has welcomed them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ladhe èu me'a dhoka karitik a'ari mu dhèu parcaya sèra, te èu ngee na, èu ne cee? Èu dènge hak ngaa, ho pèci sasala mi dhèu leo? Dhèu ne ènu èu boe, si! Aa èu ne, lamatua boe nèngu, si. Te dhodhoka Lamatua nèngu di dhu unu hak, sèna ka peka paled'a, tatao na èèna lèke, do sala. Te ngaa baku bhèlu, bèli-camèd'a Lamatua na sèmi nare dhèu ne'e dènge be'a, lula Lamatua na bisa pa'èra ne, sèna ka na bisa titu èra.<bt>If/when you-sg keep criticising/accusing2 your fellow/sibling believers like that, who do you-sg think you are? Do you have the right to accuse/blame another person? S/He is not your slave! And you, are not his/her master/owner. Cuz (elaboration) it's only his/her Master/Owner, who has the right to tell clearly/boldly/openly, that what s/he does there, is correct/right, or wrong. But don't forget, later his/her Master is the one who will accept/receive that person well, because his/her Master was able to strengthen him/her so that he/she could stand strong/persevere. [EXEG: Morris, SSA] [CHECK understanding of /a'ari/ here. How broad?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kartiik = karitik (both used, latter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kartiik = karitik (both used, latter more) = kahèti</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Who are you to pass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Who are you to pass judgment on servants of another? It is before their own lord that they stand or fall. And they will be upheld, for the Lord is able to make them stand.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Abhu dhèu cahag'e dhu pama'ète rare, peka na, lod'o èci be'a risi nèti lod'o leo. Abhu kahèi cahag'e dhu peka na, lod'o aa'i-aa'i ra èci èèna ka, lod'o èci sa risi boe nèti lod'o leo. Dhèu èci-èci ka pama'ète unu na j'ara ne'e.<bt>There are some people who decide, that, one day is better than other days. There are also some people who say that, all the days are level (=equal), one day is not better than another day. Each person must decide for him/herself about that matter/issue.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Some judge one day to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Some judge one day to be better than another, while others judge all days to be alike. Let all be fully convinced in their own minds.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ladhe dhèu pangee, na, abhu lod'o dhu be'a risi nèti lod'o leo, nèngu tao sèmi èèna, sèna ka pakab'ua Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Dhèu dhu na'a sisi dènge nganga'a dhu leo, bisa na'a ho pakab'ua Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, lula na manèngi makasi mi Lamatua. Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge dhèu dhu na'a boe sisi. Nèngu neo pakab'ua kahèi Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, aa nèngu manèngi makasi mi Lamatua kahèi.<bt>If a person thinks one day is better than the other days, he does like that to show honour/respect to our-inc Head/Ledaer Yesus Kristus. People who eat meat and other foods, can eat to show respect to our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus, because s/he gives thanks to God2. It's the same way also with people who don't eat meat. He/She wants to show respect to our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus, and he/she also says thankyou to God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Those who observe the day,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Those who observe the day, observe it in honor of the Lord. Also those who eat, eat in honor of the Lord, since they give thanks to God; while those who abstain, abstain in honor of the Lord and give thanks to God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Lod'o èdhi mamuri, èdhi mamuri boe dhoka hia ngi'u èdhi mesa ti. Aa ladhe èdhi madhe, madhe boe dhoka pala ngi'u mesa ti.<bt>When we-inc live, we don't just live only for our own selves. And if/when we die, we don't die only just for our own selves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We do not live to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: We do not live to ourselves, and we do not die to ourselves.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te ladhe èdhi mamuri era, èdhi pa'èki dènge Lamatua èdhi. Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe èdhi madhe, èdhi pa'èki era dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. De masi ka èdhi mamuri, do madhe, èdhi j'aj'i dhèu unu Na era.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if we-inc are still alive, we are bound/linked with our Master/God2. In the same way also, if/when we die, we are still bound/linked with our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus. So (consequently), whether we live, or die, we still are His possession.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If we live, we live"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: If we live, we live to the Lord, and if we die, we die to the Lord; so then, whether we live or whether we die, we are the Lord's.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Nèti èèna ka, Kristus madhe, hèia mamuri hari. Na tao sèmi èèna, sèna ka Na bisa j'aj'i Kètu bagi mi dhèu dhu madhe le, dènge dhèu dhu mamuri era kahèi.<bt>That's why Kristus died, then came back to life. He did like that so He can be Head/Leader to the various people who are already dead, and to the people who are still alive also.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For to this end Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For to this end Christ died and lived again, so that he might be Lord of both the dead and the living.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />De, nga tao ka èu ded'e iisi mu, tao sèmi dhèu pama'ète lii langu, ho karitik leli lii padhai a'ari mu dhèu sarani? Nga tao ka èu pahahe ne? Te bèli-camèd'a èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti hud'i lati asa madha Ama Lamatua, ho Na parisa mamuri èdhi èci-èci.<bt>So (consequently), why do you-sg lift yourself up/elevate/appoint yourself like a judge, to criticize your Christian sibling thoughtlessly/arbitrarily? Why do you look down on/despise him/her? Cuz (elaboration) later we all must go face God, so that He examines each one of our lives.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Why do you pass judgment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Why do you pass judgment on your brother or sister? Or you, why do you despise your brother or sister? For we will all stand before the judgment seat of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 5:10</note><v n="11" />Abhu dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Ama Lamatua, dhu peka na,<bt>It is written from long ago in God's Clean/Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ama èdhi mesa Na dhu peka, na,<bt>&lt;&lt;Our Father himself is the one who tells/makes known, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dhèu aa'i-aa'i pe patitu kètu urutuu, ho pahaha iisi mi Ja'a,<bt>&lt;Everyone will kneel to humbled themselves/ worship Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dènge pakab'ua Ja'a.<bt>and show respect/honour to Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bèli-camèd'a, nèti d'ara hèb'a dhèu èci-èci, ra mangaku, na,<bt>Each person will use their mouths to acknowledge/ confess,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ja'a j'aj'i Kètu rèngu,<bt>saying, I am their Head/Leader,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lula Ja'a ne, Ama Lamatua.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>because I here, am God.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exomologew: confess, acknowledge, praise, express praise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">exomologew: confess, acknowledge, praise, express praise or honor, with a possible implication of acknowledging the nature of someone or something NRSV: For it is written, “As I live, says the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall give praise to God.”<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="14:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 45:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />De èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti, bèli-camèd'a hud'i dhaa ètu madha Lamatua, ho peka na, èdhi tao tasamia, aa nga tao ka èdhi tao sèmi èèna.<bt>So (consequently), we-inc all must be accountable/ responsible before God2, saying, what we did, and why we did like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lógon doósei: give an account of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">lógon doósei: give an account of ourselves, explain why we did what we did NRSV: So then, each of us will be accountable to God.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Baku ad'u-ue j'ara ho pamanahu a'ari dhèu sarani [\s2]<bt>Don't do anything to make your Christian sibling fall [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Uru èèna, miu ètu Roma pèci sasala taruu mi a'ari miu dhèu sarani sèra. Tao ia ka sèmi èèna! Be'a risi èdhi pama'ète sèmi ne'e: èdhi baku tao sèna ka a'ari èdhi kadhunu. Èdhi baku tenge j'ara ho sii pamanahu si, sèna ka ra tao sasala.<bt>Previously, you-pl in Roma kept accusing/blaming your-pl fellow Christian siblings. Don't do that anymore! It's better/best, if we decide like this: we won't make our siblings stumble. We won't try to find ways to make them fall, so they do wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meekéti: we were criticizing each other,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">meekéti: we were criticizing each other, but we are supposed to lay off próskomma: stumbling, something that makes someone stumble, occasion to sin<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>skándalon: trigger of a trap, the thing that gets you into trouble, occasion to sin NRSV: Let us therefore no longer pass judgment on one another, but resolve instead never to put a stumbling block or hindrance in the way of another.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Lula ja'a dhu pa'èki dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, ja'a ke'a mèu, sèmi ne'e: abhu boe ngaa èci sa dhu bisa pakaj'alu dhèu, toke na bisa boe sabaj'a mi Lamatua. Te ngaa ladhe abhu dhèu èci dhu pangee, na, mèdha èci tao ne kaj'alu, toke nèngu ngee na, bisa heka dènge hak sèna ka sabaj'a, na, hud'i laa mèdha ne j'aj'i mèdha luri hia nèngu.<bt>Because I am bound/linked with our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus, I know clearly like.this: there is nothing that can make a person defiled, to.the.point that he/she can't pray/worship God2. But if a person thinks one thing makes him defiled, to.the.point.that he/she feels he/she no longer has the right to pray/worship, just let/allow that thing become taboo for him/her. [EXEG: Is this a broad principle, or just talking about food in this context? Morris, Moo, NRSV, and TB keep it broad (which includes the issue of food). I (CEG) think limiting it to food because of the context is unfortunately narrower than the text, and I disagree with SSA, NLT, NIV, and CEV here. Others (mentioned above) include its application to food as part of a broader principle. My bias as a missiologist and cross-cultural scripture use worker is showing through here. If Paul was limiting his discussion to food, he's already using the vocabulary necessary to do so explicitly. But he doesn't. He phrases this as a much broader principle or generalisation. And that's why missiologists can appeal to the broader principle in this verse to apply it to cultural customs and other hot issues (like abortion and embryonic stem-cell research) that the scriptures do not address directly. So narrowing the application here and in vs. 16 to food I think is beyond the text and actually unhelpful and limiting.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I know and am persuaded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: I know and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus that nothing is unclean in itself; but it is unclean for anyone who thinks it unclean.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Conto sèmi èu mu'a sisi, aa papèd'a d'ara a'ari mu, na, èu pad'elo boe sasue èu mi nèngu, si? Ladhe sèmi èèna, baku mu'a! Baku pa'ele iie a'ari mu, lula èu neo mu'a nganga'a èci! Te Kristus madhe pala mi dhèu ne'e kahèi.<bt>For example, if you-sg are eating meat, and that makes your sibling's insides distressed, na, you are not showing your love to him/her, right? If that is the case, don't eat! Don't ruin your sibling, just because you want to eat a certain thing! Cuz (elaboration) Kristus also died for that person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupeitai: cause someone to be sad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">lupeitai: cause someone to be sad, sorrowful, or distressed apollue: ruin, destroy, injure<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>NRSV: If your brother or sister is being injured by what you eat, you are no longer walking in love. Do not let what you eat cause the ruin of one for whom Christ died.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Be'a boe ladhe èu ad'u-ue j'ara èci dhu madhutu a'abhu èu, be'a, te ngaa dhèu leo padhai kakoli kolongara èu, lula ra pangee na, tatao èu deo na, karehe.<bt>It's not good if you-sg do something which you consider good, but other people speak making your name/reputation rotten (=slander), because they consider what you just did/are doing is bad/defiling. [EXEG: See comment at vs.14.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So do not let your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: So do not let your good be spoken of as evil.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ngee paie-iie! Te Ama Lamatua ka, Dhèu Aae èdhi. Te ngaa èdhi j'aj'i boe dhèu unu nèti Dhèu Aae, lula èdhi ta'a-tinu madhutu dhoka atora di. Aad'o! Ladhe èdhi neo j'aj'i dhèu unu nèti Dhèu Aae, èdhi hud'i tao dhu lèke, d'ara mola-mèci, mamuri mola dènge mera-milu, aa d'ara dhu karej'e-karae. Aa'i-aa'i se bisa j'aj'i, ladhe èdhi pa'èki taruu dènge Roh Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci.<bt>Think carefully! Cuz (elaboration) God is our King. But we don't become the King's people only because we just eat-drink following regulations. No! If we want to become the King's people, we must do what is right/correct/true, our insides are clean/holy (doublet), our lives are straight (=righteous) and peaceful (relationships) (doublet), and our insides are happy (doublet). All this can happen/ eventuate, if we are continually bound/linked with God2's Holy Spirit. [SSA, HCE; NOTE: righteousness &amp; peace have internal &amp; external manifestations]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For the kingdom of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: For the kingdom of God is not food and drink but righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dhèu dhu lalau-lalo'o hia Kristus sèmi èèna, pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua. Aa dhèu leo lee kahèi mamuri dhèu ne'e, hèia padedha kolongara dhèu ne'e, peka na, &lt;&lt;Nèngu ne, be'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>People who serve (doublet) Kristus like that, make God2's insides happy. And other people also carefully examine that person's life, then lift up that person's name/reputation, saying, &lt;&lt;He's good/he's a good person!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: explicated to better reflect full meaning of Gk word and to link better with high level theme.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dókimos: approved after being tested, being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">dókimos: approved after being tested, being respected on the basis of proven worth NRSV: The one who thus serves Christ is acceptable to God and has human approval.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />De èdhi hud'i pa'èra ètu d'ara mamuri padame, aa maj'èni pa'èra èci dènge èci.<bt>So (consequently), we must strengthen/prepare ourselves (=strive hard) to live in mutual.peace (relationships), and be diligent to strengthen/ encourage each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireénees: inner peace, or a peaceful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">eireénees: inner peace, or a peaceful relationship with other people (more likely here) NRSV: Let us then pursue what makes for peace and for mutual upbuilding.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Baku pa'ele iie sasab'a Lamatua ètu d'ara mamuri dhèu leo, lula dhoka nèti j'ara ta'a-tinu di. Lamatua dhu peka le, èdhi bisa ta'a ngaa èèna ka, te aa'i-aa'i dhu mola-mèci. Te ngaa ladhe èu patao-palaha dènge a'ari mu lula j'ara nganga'a-nganginu di, èu sala le. Baku sèmi èèna!<bt>Don't destroy/ruin God2's work in another person's life just because of eat-drink disputes/issues. God2 has already said we-inc can eat whatever, cuz (elaboration) everything is clean/holy (doublet). But if you are in a mutual dispute (doublet) with your sibling because of an eat-drink matter/issue, that is wrong. Don't do like that! [EXEG re "the work of God": Morris says "There is wide divergence as to the way we should understand it here. Thus Boylan holds that it refers to what God does in the individual Christian, while Barrett denies this and sees a reference to the church. Wesley combines the two ideas: “Which He builds in the soul by faith, and in the Church by concord.” ... Cranfield to what God does in the weak brother, and Haldane to what he does in the believer. Without some further explanation we cannot be sure of the apostle's full meaning, but he is certainly including what God has done in the weak brother, for it is that that is to be built up or broken down. There may be a fuller meaning, but we cannot be sure."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not, for the sake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not, for the sake of food, destroy the work of God. Everything is indeed clean, but it is wrong for you to make others fall by what you eat;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Hua iia taha iisi mu. Mu'a ia ka sisi, do minu ia ka èi anggor, do baku mu'a-minu ngaa dhu leo, dhu tao a'ari mu kadhunu.<bt>It's better/best, if you-sg just restrain yourself. It's not neccessary to eat meat, or drink wine, or eat-drink other things anymore which make your sibling stumble.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: it is good not to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: it is good not to eat meat or drink wine or do anything that makes your brother or sister stumble.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Madhutu a'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e ka: ladhe èu more lii èci dènge Lamatua, hèia èu pama'ète, na, èu neo parcaya Ne lula-nèti nganga'a-nganginu, na, èu oto aa dènge heka lii langu. Pangee ia ka ngaa-ngaa dhu peka na, èu tao sala, do aad'o. Te èu dhu pama'ète more le sèmi èèna.<bt>My meaning/intent is like this: if you-sg already consulted/ came to an agreement with God2, so you decided that, you want to believe/trust Him about eat-drink issues, na, you are fortunate and have no more dispute/issues (=dealt with the issue and come out with acceptable results/made things right). Don't keep htinking/worrying to find out if you are doing wrong, or not. Cuz (elaboration) you have already come to a decision like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The faith that you have,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: The faith that you have, have as your own conviction before God. Blessed are those who have no reason to condemn themselves because of what they approve.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Te ngaa ladhe d'ara èu kajari, ka mu'a mèdha èci dhu èu ngee na pakaj'alu èu, Lamatua pasala èu, lula èu madhutu boe ngaa dhu èu parcaya lod'o dhu èu mu'a. Te ladhe èu neo ad'u-ue ngaa sa èci, te ngaa èu parcaya, peka na, èèna lèke boe ètu madha Lamatua, na, èèna èu sala le.<bt>But if your insides are forked (=indecisive, in doubt), and/then you eat something which you feel can make you defiled, God2 accuses/blames you, because you didn't do according to what you believed when you were eating (it). Cuz (elaboration) if you want to do (doublet) something, but you believe/trust that it is not right/correct before God2, na, that's wrong/sin. [SSA, NLT, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara èu kajari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">dara èu kajari</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But those who have doubts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: But those who have doubts are condemned if they eat, because they do not act from faith; for whatever does not proceed from faith is sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tenge j'ara ho pa'èra lalèka dhèu leo<bt>Make.an.effort to strengthen other people's faith2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Èdhi dhu parcaya èra, hud'i dènge d'ara maho'o ho bara dhèu dhu parcaya èra mèka, sèna ka rèngu taha ètu d'ara sasusa. Be'a boe, ladhe èdhi dhoka pakarej'e ngi'u èdhi mesa ti.<bt>We-inc who believe strongly, must be patient/ kind/gentle to help people who are not yet strong, so that they endure in.the.midst of difficulty. It's not good if we only just make ourselves happy. [EXEG: higher level introducing theme; see v.2,4,5; see also NLT, SSA, Morris]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maho'o = kind, patient, tolerant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">maho'o = kind, patient, tolerant</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asthenemata: failings, scruples, weaknesses bastazw: bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">asthenemata: failings, scruples, weaknesses bastazw: bear with, endure patiently, help to carry the burden, tolerate<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>areskw: to please LITERALLY: We who are strong ought to bear with the failings of the weak, and not to please ourselves.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Madhutu a'abhu ja'a hud'i sèmi ne'e ku: èdhi èci-èci ka tenge j'ara, sèna ka tao dhu be'a hia a'ari èdhi dhèu sarani, ho parcaya ra asa tabha èra. Dènge j'ara ne'e, rèngu bisa karej'e dènge èdhi.<bt>My intent is like.this: each one of us-inc must find ways to do what is good for our Christian siblings, so.that their faith becomes increasingly stronger. In that way, they can become/be happy with us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plesion: neighbor, Christian neighbor LITERALLY: Each"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">plesion: neighbor, Christian neighbor LITERALLY: Each of us should please his neighbor for good, to build him up.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te Yesus Kristus mesa Na, pakako boe sasab'a Na ho pakarej'e d'ara Nèngu unu Na, te ngaa Na neo pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua kahèi. Èèna nuka sèmi dhu suri tèke ètu d'ara Sasuri Lamatua lula-nèti ngaa dhu bèli-camèd'a j'aj'i mi dedha Yesus, dhu peka na,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Yesus Kristus himself didn't do His work to please himself, but He also wanted to please God. That is the same as what was written ahead.of.time in God2's Writings about what would later happen to Yesus, saying, [NOTE: explicated from UNS confusion at Belu check.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lii pa-aape rèngu hia mi Èu,<bt>&lt;&lt;Their slandering/blaspheme/insulting of You-sg,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lii pa'ape = merendahkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">Lii pa'ape = merendahkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">noto mi dedha Ja'a kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>falls/applies to Me also.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noto = jatuh, berlaku (ex. from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">noto = jatuh, berlaku (ex. from children's game, congkak, not drop, but wind up in)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oneidismos: insult, reproach, abuse LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">oneidismos: insult, reproach, abuse LITERALLY: For even Christ did not please himself, but, as it is written: "The insults of those who insult you [God] have fallen on me [Christ]."<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 69:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Aa'i-aa'i dhu uru èèna dhèu suri ètu d'ara Sasuri Lamatua, sèna ka nori èdhi. Nèngu pad'elo j'ara sèna ka asa pa'èra èdhi, taha pa'èra-èra, aa Lii Holo-Nori Na pa'èra d'ara èdhi kahèi. Dènge j'ara sèmi èèna ka, èdhi bisa taha ètu d'ara tatae neo tèdhi Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi èdhi.<bt>Everything which people previously wrote in God2's Writings, are written to teach/advise us-inc. He/It shows the way to make us-inc be increasingly stronger, endure stronger, and His Words (doublet) also encourage us. In that way, we-inc can endure while waiting wanting to see God2 show His good insides (=grace/goodness/kindness/ generosity) to us [HCE].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For everything that was written"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For everything that was written in the past was written to teach us, so that through endurance and the encouragement of the Scriptures we might have hope.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Lamatua ka dhu hia dhèu a'èra, sèna ka ra bisa taha ètu d'ara j'aj'èra. Aa Nèngu ka dhu pa'èra d'ara èdhi kahèi. Ja'a sabaj'a, manèngi Lamatua pad'elo j'ara, ho miu mamuri d'ara èci madhutu dad'èi Yesus Kristus.<bt>God2 is the one who gives people strength, so they can endure in suffering/abuse. And He is the one who strengthens our insides (=encourages us). I pray asking God2 to show the way so you-pl can live with one insides (=united, in harmony, same purpose), according to Yesus Kristus' will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà: according to the standard of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">katà: according to the standard of Jesus, following his example, doing things his way LITERALLY: May the God who gives endurance and encouragement give you a spirit of unity among yourselves in accordance with Christ Jesus.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te ladhe miu mamuri d'ara èci, miu bisa sama-sama koa-kio Ama Lamatua. Nèngu èèna, Ama nèti Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if you are one insides (=united) like that, you can together praise (doublet) God. He is the Father of our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homothumadon: with one purpose LITERALLY: That"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">homothumadon: with one purpose LITERALLY: That you may with one mind and one mouth glorify God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii Lolo Be'a Lamatua hia mi dhèu Yahudi dènge dhèu Yahudi boe<bt>God2's Good News is for the Yahudi people and for the non Yahudi people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />De miu isi-aanga mi hud'i sèmi mere èci dènge èci, sama sèmi Kristus sèmi nare le miu. Te ladhe miu mamuri sèmi èèna, pe dhèu ae j'oka padedha-dedha kolongara Lamatua.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must accept each other, the same as Kristus has accepted you-pl. Cuz (elaboration) if you live like.that, people will lift God2's name/reputation up high. (=glorify)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="isi aanga mi = sesama bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">isi aanga mi = sesama bosong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proslambánesthe: same as 14:1 -- let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">proslambánesthe: same as 14:1 -- let each odda come in, accept each other LITERALLY: Accept one another, therefore, just as Christ accepted you, in order to bring glory to God.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ja'a peka sèmi ne'e: Kristus tao iisi Na nuka sèmi Ana pua-paleha, sèna ka hia dhèu Yahudi re'a mèu, peka na, Ama Lamatua padhai lii lèke mola-mola. Aa Kristus tao iisi Na nuka sèmi Ana pua-paleha kahèi, ho pamèci aa'i mèu ngaa-ngaa dhu Lamatua padhadha neo tao, hia mi bèi-baki èdhi sèra.<bt>I'm telling like this: Kristus made himself like a servant/slave (person who gets ordered around) (doublet) so that the Yahudi people understand that, God speaks truth. And Kristus also made himself like a servant to fulfill/complete all the things which God2 had promised to do for our-inc ancestors (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bebaióosai: actively make the things promised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">bebaióosai: actively make the things promised happen (it could have the sense of "assure people that the things God promised really will happen some day", but in this context it's action, not just information) LITERALLY: For I say that Christ became a servant of the Jews on behalf of God's truth, to confirm the promises made to our fathers.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Dènge j'ara ne'e, dhèu Yahudi boe aa'i-aa'i koa-kio Ama Lamatua. Te rèngu re'a, na, Nèngu dhu rasa kasia mi èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti. Sèra nuka sèmi dhu Daud suri uru èèna ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na,<bt>In that way, all non Yahudi people, praise (doublet) God. Cuz (elaboration) they understand that, He feels mercy/pity/ compassion for all of us-inc. That is the same as what Daud wrote long ago in the Holy Writings, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nèti èèna ka, ja'a neo ded'e padedha-dedha kolongara Èu,<bt>&lt;&lt;That's why I want to lift up Your-sg name/reputation up high,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mi suku dhu leo sèra.<bt>for the other ethnic.groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ja'a neo sod'a lii koa-kio kolongara Èu<bt>I want to sing praise (doublet) songs/psalms about You</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ètu katanga madha udhu rasa dhu leo sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>in the other tribes' face (=in front of them/ before them).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exomologeésomai: be up front about my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">exomologeésomai: be up front about my relationship to you. But by parallel to the second line, it might be interpreted as "praise" LITERALLY: so that the Gentiles may glorify God for his mercy, as it is written: "For this reason I will praise you among the Gentiles; I will sing hymns to your name."<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 22:50, Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 18:50</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ètu era leo, d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci suri kahèi, na,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings it is written, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;We! Miu dhèu leo rai kara dhu nèti rai leo.<bt>&lt;&lt;We! You-pl outside people from other places.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tao d'ara miu karej'e kea rae-rae,<bt>Make your insides reaaly happy (=be joyful),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">palere-lere dènge dhèu unu Lamatua sèra.&gt;&gt;<bt>together with God2's own people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euphrainw: rejoice, gladden LITERALLY: And again"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">euphrainw: rejoice, gladden LITERALLY: And again it says, "Rejoice, Gentiles, with his people."<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 32:43</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ètu era leo, d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, Daud suri, peka na,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings, Daud wrote, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Miu dhu nèti suku leo sèra.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl from other ethnic.groups</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lami peka palème mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i lula-nèti dadedha Lamatua,<bt>go tell everywhere all people about God2's high-ness/ glory,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sèna ka rèngu koa-kio Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus kahèi.&gt;&gt;<bt>so that they also praise (doublet) Yesus Kristus, our Head/Leader.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: This is a typical parallelism of Biblical Hebrew poetry. The two stanzas are technically classed as “‘synonymous’ (where two lines say the same thing in different ways)” rather than ‘antithetical’ or ‘synthetic’. Don't to force it to be making two different points.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ainew: praise epainew: praise, laud|i(11) (11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">ainew: praise epainew: praise, laud<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: And again, "Praise the Lord, all Gentiles, and let all peoples praise him."</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 117:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ètu era leo hari, d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci, Yesaya suri, peka na,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings, Yesaya wrote, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nèti dhèu aae Daud, ana Isai,<bt>&lt;&lt;From king Daud, the offspring of Isai,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bèli-camèd'a cèu mai ana-èpu na ca dhèu.<bt>later (doublet) one of his descendants (doublet) will come out/appear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nèngu ka dhu nèd'u paredha mi suku leo sèra.<bt>He is the one who will hold authority/govern/rule over other ethnic groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Rèngu dhu re'a le, naneo mamai Nèngu èèna.<bt>They already know He is coming.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hèia rèngu mate tatae Ne,<bt>So they are waiting (doublet) (=waiting expectantly) for Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te rèngu re'a mèu, na, Nèngu ne, cee.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) they know who He is.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="riza: root, like when a ti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">riza: root, like when a ti plant comes out of the ground from a root that was put there a long time ago LITERALLY: And again, Isaiah says, "There will be a root of Jesse, and he will rise to rule over the Gentiles. The Gentiles will hope in him."<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 11:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ama Lamatua ka dhu j'aj'i mi kapua nèti aa'i-aa'i dhu èdhi sanao-maena. Ladhe miu parcaya Ne, Nèngu ka dhu pakarej'e d'ara miu aa pamau d'ara miu. Hud'i laa sèna ka koasa nèti Roh Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci, tao miu asa me'a mèu lula-nèti ngaa dhu Nèngu neo tao.<bt>God is the root/source/base of everything which we hope for (doublet). If you-pl believe in Him, He is the one who will make your insides happy and calm/peaceful them. Let the power/authority of God2's Holy Spirit, make you increasingly assured/certain about what it is He wants to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: May the God of hope"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: May the God of hope fill you with great joy and peace as you trust in him, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lamatua pua Paulus la'e peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a Na<bt>God2 commissions/ed Paulus to go tell (doublet) His Good News</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a ke'a tare'a, na, d'ara miu pènu dènge madha j'ara-madha j'ara dhu be'a, j'ara ae-ae dhu miu me'a mèu le, aa me'a holo èci dènge èci.<bt>Siblings! I really know that, your-pl insides are full of various good things, you already understand many things, and you know how to give advice to one another.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="autòs egoò: me, whether anybody else"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">autòs egoò: me, whether anybody else feels that way or not mestos: full<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>plerow: complete, filled nouthetew: advise, instruct, teach (not in a classroom sense), warn, admonish<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: But my brothers, I myself am persuaded that you yourselves are full of goodness, complete in knowledge, and able to advise each other.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ja'a suri paled'a-led'a ètu d'ara sasuri ne'e, ho pasanèd'e miu catèka hari nèti rupa-rupa madha j'ara. Ja'a suri sèmi ne'e, lula Lamatua pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ja'a,<bt>I'm writing clearly/boldly/openly/frankly in this letter, to remind/warn you one more time about various issues/ things. I write like this, because God2 showed His good insides (grace) to me,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apò mérous: from parts, concerning certain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">apò mérous: from parts, concerning certain specific matters teèn khárin: not theological "grace", but a specific privilege spelled out in verse 16: God gave me the privilege of serving Christ to benefit the Gentiles. Disregard the verse boundary<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: I have written you quite boldly on some points, as if to remind you of them again, because of the [grace / privilege] God gave me</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />ropa Na ded'e ja'a j'aj'i mi dhèu pajuu-paleha Yesus Kristus, ho laku peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a Nèngu asa dhèu Yahudi boe sèra. Ja'a pakako sasab'a ja'a èèna, nuka sèmi ama agama èci dhu neo pa'èra dhèu ae-ae dhu j'aj'i mi persembahan èci dhu pamaho'o d'ara Lamatua. Te Roh Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci ka dhu tao si j'aj'i mola-mèci, sèna ka Ama Lamatua sèmi nare si.<bt>when He lifted me up/appointed me to become Yesus Kristus' commissioned.one (*apostle) to go tell God2's Good News to the non Yahudi people. I carry out that work of mine, like a religious leader (*priest) who wants to strengthen/prepare many people to be an offering (loan-not sacrifice) which pleases3 God2's insides. Cuz (elaboration) that Holy Spirit of God2's, makes them become clean/holy (doublet), so that God2 will accept them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tóon ethnóon: the Gentiles are the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">tóon ethnóon: the Gentiles are the offering; not the offering that they bring. Paul presents the Gentiles to God as the results of his efforts LITERALLY: to be a servant of Jesus Christ to the Gentiles, with the priestly duty of proclaiming the Good News of God, so that the Gentiles might become an offering acceptable to God, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Lula ja'a dhu pa'èki le dènge Yesus Kristus, nèti èèna ka ja'a bisa boti kètu ètu madha Ama Lamatua.<bt>Because I am bound/linked with Yesus Kristus, that's why I can lift my head (=not be ashamed, justifiably proud) before God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, I glory in Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, I glory in Christ Jesus in my service to God.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ja'a bani boe padhai lii j'ara leo. Ja'a dhoka lole tatao dhu Kristus ad'u-ue, aa dènge j'ara sèmi ngaa Na pake ja'a. Limuri ne, abhu dhèu Yahudi boe dhu madhutu Kristus, lula Lamatua pake ja'a ho pad'elo j'ara pake lii padhai dènge tatao ja'a.<bt>I don't dare speak of other things. I only speak explaining just about Kristus' deeds, and how He is using me. Now there are non Yahudi people who listen to/obey Kristus, because God2 used me to show the way using my speaking and deeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I will not dare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I will not dare to speak of anything except what Christ has done through me in leading the Gentiles to obey him by what I have said and done,</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kristus pangèd'u le mi ja'a koasa nèti Roh Lamatua, sèna ka bisa tao rupa-rupa tadha malaa. Na pangèd'u koasa èèna mi ja'a, sèna ka neo pad'elo, peka na, Kristus ne cee. Dènge j'ara ne'e, ja'a peka-padhai le aa'i-aa'i lula-nèti Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus dènge dhèu ètu mia-mia. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a lole nèti kota Yerusalem, pale-lème toke d'ai rai Ilirikum dètu dènge Italia.<bt>Kristus has handed over power/authority to me from God2's Spirit, so that I can do all.sorts of amazing signs (=miracles). He gave that power to me in.order.to show who that Kristus is. In that way, I have told (doublet) people everywhere, everything about Kristus' Good News. That is why I tell from Yerusalem city, going around until the region of Ilirikum near Italia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: by the power of signs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: by the power of signs and wonders, through the power of the Spirit. So that from Jerusalem all the way around to Illyricum, I have fully proclaimed the Good News of Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Karèi nèti uru ka, ja'a dhu pangee, na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a d'èi titu kèna lole lula-nèti Kristus mi dhèu-dhèu dhu tadèngi rèdhi mèka Lii Lolo Be'a Na!&gt;&gt; Te ja'a d'èi boe aj'a-nori ètu era dhu dhèu leo aj'a le.<bt>From long ago, I was thinking that, &lt;&lt;I yearn to tell about Kristus to the people who have never heard His Good News!&gt;&gt; Cuz (elaboration) I don't like to teach (doublet) in places where other people have already taught.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thus it has always been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thus it has always been my ambition to preach the Good News where Christ was not known, so that I would not be building on someone else's foundation.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua, dhu suri, peka na,<bt>In God2's Holy Writings, it is written, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Suku dhu tadèngi rèdhi mèka lula Lamatua,<bt>&lt;&lt;Ethnic.groups which have not yet ever heard about God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">rèngu sèra ka dhu bèli-camèd'a ladhe rèdhi Ne.<bt>they are the ones who later will get to see Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dhèu dhu tadèngi rèdhi mèka ngaa-ngaa,<bt>People who have not yet ever heard anything,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">rèngu sèra ka dhu pe re'a mèu lula Nèngu.&gt;&gt;<bt>they are the ones who later will understand about Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But just as it has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But just as it has been written, "Those who were not told about him will see, and those who have not heard will understand."</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus nelu neo la'e asa kota Roma<bt>Paulus compiles a plan to go to Roma city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Lula sasab'a ja'a ae sèmi èèna, ka lake kore mèka dhiu pa'asu-pareo dènge miu.<bt>Because my work is like.that, I have not yet been able to actually stop in and visit (doublet) you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nelu = rencana (v)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">nelu = rencana (v)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That is why I have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That is why I have often been hindered from coming to you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 1:13</note><v n="23" />Te ngaa limuri ne, sasab'a ja'a ètu ne'e èla aa'i le. Aa ja'a nelu nèbhu ae le pèri-pèri tèu kèna, dhiu paraga dènge miu.<bt>But now, my work here is all finished. And for a long time, already several years, I have been planning to go meet with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now that there is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now that there is no more place for me to work in these regions, and since I have been longing for many years to see you,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />De ladhe ja'a laku asa Spanyol, ja'a neo dhuli miu. Aa ladhe ja'a dhuli taha ètu era miu, miu bisa ogo ja'a kahèi laku asa Spanyol.<bt>So (consequently) if/when I go to Spanyol country, I want to stop by and see you. Then, if I have stopped off temporarily with/at your place, you also can cover the cost of my journey to Spanyol.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="propemphthéenai: be sent onward -- they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">propemphthéenai: be sent onward -- they will help out with his travel expenses LITERALLY: when I go to Spain, I will come to you. I hope to see you on my trip and to have you assist me on my journey there [to Spain], after I have stayed with you [enjoyed being with you] for a while.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Te ngaa limuri ne ja'a neo laku uru asa Yerusalem, ho lalau-lalo'o dhèu parcaya Lamatua ètu nèi.<bt>But now, I want to go to Yerusalem first, to serve (doublet) God2's believers yonder (remote).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakonóon: probably refers to delivering the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">diakonóon: probably refers to delivering the collection Paul took up that he talks about in 2 Corinthians, an in the next verse LITERALLY: But now I go to Jerusalem to [minister to / serve] the saints.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te a'ari èdhi ètu propensi Makedonia dènge propensi Akaya, hia le doi kolete, sèna ka soru-bara dhèu dhu dènge boe ngaa-ngaa dhu parcaya Lamatua ètu Yerusalem.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) our siblings in Makedonia province and Akaya province, have given collection money (loan) to help (doublet) the poor people who believe in God2/Lord in Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For Macedonia and Achaia were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For Macedonia and Achaia were pleased to make a contribution for the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 16:1-4</note><v n="27" />Rèngu neo tao sèmi ne'e, lula ra pangee, na, rèngu oe sèmi pakèlu sa, mi a'ari èdhi ètu Yerusalem. Te dhèu-dhèu nèti suku leo ètu mia-mia, rèngu abhu le j'ara hua iia kahèi dhu uru èèna Roh Lamatua hia le mi dhèu Yahudi sèra. De lèke mola-mola ladhe dhèu sarani dhu dhèu Yahudi boe, pake mèdha-panyau ra ho soru-bara a'ari ra dhèu Yahudi sèra.<bt>They wanted to do that, because they felt there was almost a debt owed to our-inc siblings in Yerusalem. Cuz (elaboration) people from other ethnic.groups all over the place, also have received good things which previously God2's Spirit had given to the Yahudi people. So (consequently), it's truly appropriate if the sarani people (=Christians) who are not Yahudi, use their possessions/belongings/wealth (doublet) to help (doublet) their Yahudi siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="isi aanga mi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">isi aanga mi =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They were pleased to do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They were pleased to do it, and indeed they owe it to them. For it the Gentiles have shared in the Jews' spiritual blessings, they owe it to the Jews to share with them their material blessings.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 9:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />De ladhe ja'a pabagi kore ka doi se'e mi a'ari èdhi ètu Yerusalem, ja'a neo dhuli pangad'o dènge miu, ropa laku asa Spanyol.<bt>So (consequently), if/when I have finished distributing this money to our siblings in Yerusalem, I want to stop over and see you when I travel to Spanyol.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So after I have finished"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So after I have finished this job, and have made sure that they have received this fruit [benefit], I will go to Spain and visit you on the way.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ladhe ja'a dhiu, kèti dènge mèngi-nale ae-ae nèti Kristus.<bt>If/when I come, I will bring lots of blessings from Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I know that when I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I know that when I come to you, I will come in the full measure of the blessing of Christ. / bringing an abundant blessing from Christ</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Lula Yesus Kristus j'aj'i Kètu miu, aa lula Roh Lamatua ka tao miu pasue èci dènge èci, nèti èèna ka ja'a manèngi ho miu sabaj'a patare'a-re'a, sèna ka Lamatua soru-bara ja'a.<bt>Siblings! Because Yesus Kristus is your Head/Leader, and because God2's Spirit is who makes you love one another, that is why I request that you really pray for God2 to help (doublet) me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I urge you brothers, by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I urge you brothers, by our Lord Jesus Christ, and by the love of the Spirit, to join me in my struggle by praying to God for me.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Manèngi sèna ka Lamatua bhiri-sarobho ja'a ètu propensi Yudea, ho dhèu dhu ro'o boe parcaya Lamatua baku tao bhelu mi dedha ja'a. Aa manèngi ho ladhe ja'a lalau-lalo'o dhèu sarani ètu Yerusalem, rèngu sèmi rare ja'a dènge be'a.<bt>Request that God2 protect (doublet) me in Yudea province, so that people who do not want to believe in God2 don't do evil to me. And request that if I go serve (doublet) the Christians in Yerusalem, they will receive me well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bhiri-sarobho"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">bhiri-sarobho</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeithoúntoon: not simply &quot;unbelieving&quot;, but &quot;refusing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">apeithoúntoon: not simply "unbelieving", but "refusing to act in faith, rejecting the faith", a more negative idea LITERALLY: Pray that I may be rescued from the unbelievers in Judea, and that my service in Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints there.<span class="Italic">(31)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Èle èèna, ladhe madhutu dad'èi Lamatua, ja'a bisa dhiu asa miu dènge d'ara karej'e, lula ja'a neo ae kore ciki dènge miu.<bt>Then, if it is according to God2's will, I can come see you with happy insides, because I want to rest a bit with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kora &lt; kore ; ae kora"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">kora &lt; kore ; ae kora = istirahat (barenti ame sadiki)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunanapauswmai: experience restorative rest together with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">sunanapauswmai: experience restorative rest together with someone else LITERALLY: Then by God's will I can come to you with joy, and together with you be refreshed.<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ja'a sabaj'a sèna ka Lamatua bera-bera dènge miu. Te Nèngu ka dhu bisa tao ho dhèu mamuri dame dènge mera-milu. Lèke tare'a!<bt>I pray that God2 be with you. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who enables people to live safely (situation) and peacefully (relationships). It's true!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The God of peace be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The God of peace be with you all. Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus pa'adhu lii maho'o asa a'ari ètu Roma<bt>Paulus sends greetings to the siblings in Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Dènge sasuri ne'e, ja'a neo patadha miu dènge ana hèni èdhi Febe, aa manèngi ho miu sèmi mere ne. Nèngu ka dhu ra ded'e ho ladhe-leru juma'at ètu kota Kengkrea.<bt>By means of this letter, I want to introduce our-inc sister Febe to you, and request that you accept/receive her. She is the one whom they lifted up/appointed to serve/minister to (doublet) the congregation (loan) in Kengkrea city. [NOTE: It has been observed for over 100 years that the female Phoebe in this verse is described in Gk as a “deacon”, rather than using the grammatical feminine “deaconess”. Most authorities agree that this implies she was in a leadership role of a congregation. A few have tried to argue that she was not an office-bearer, but that has been shown to be a reflection of their own worldview and values, not of the Biblical text. See any good commentary, as well as articles on CBE website. I (Chuck) have an article by a Baptist minister in the 1890s that I can send you. He was an off-sider to D.L. Moody. Even Tran Handbook and NEB says she was an ‘office holder’ (ie. not a helper of office holders). See Nyland for a pg long footnote on the term.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="synísteemi: I give you a recommendation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">synísteemi: I give you a recommendation for Phoebe. Used in letters of recommendation. NRSV: I commend to you our sister Phoebe, a deacon of the church at Cenchreae,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ja'a manèngi ho miu sèmi mere ne dènge be'a. Tao dhu pantas mi nèngu, nuka sèmi hia dhèu sarani sèra, lula nèngu ne pa'èki dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Ladhe na parluu ngaa, soru-bara ne. Te nèngu biasa soru-bara le ja'a dènge dhèu ae-ae, karèi nèti uru ka.<bt>I request that you receive her well. Do what is appropriate for her, as you would for any Christians, because she is bound/linked with our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus. Whatever she needs, just help (doublet) her. Cuz (elaboration) she has often helped me and many people from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prosdéxeesthe: welcome, take into your group,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">prosdéxeesthe: welcome, take into your group, make her feel at home hymóon: from you<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>prostátis: benefactor, patron, protectress, helper, of great assistance NRSV: so that you may welcome her in the Lord as is fitting for the saints, and help her in whatever she may require from you, for she has been a benefactor of many and of myself as well.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="3" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi ana hèni èdhi, Priskila<bt>Give my greetings to our-inc sister Priskila</bt><note reference="16:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani ètu ne'e, suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Priska&gt;&gt;. Priska dènge Priskila èèna, ngara nèti ca dhèu èèna ka.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, saying, “Priska”. Priska and Priskila are names for the same person.</bt></note>dènge dhèu èmu na, Akila. Ji'i ka dhu sama-sama pakako sasab'a ae-ae nèti Yesus Kristus.<bt>and her spouse, Akila. We-exc have together carried out lots of Yesus Kristus' work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Prisca and Aquila, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Prisca and Aquila, who work with me in Christ Jesus,</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 18:2</note><v n="4" />Dua ra oe madhe sad'i neo pamamuri ja'a. Te ngaa mesa boe ja'a di dhu manèngi makasi mi dua ra. Te dhèu Yahudi boe dhu j'aj'i le dhèu sarani, nèti juma'at aa'i-aa'i buli mia-mia, manèngi makasi kahèi, lula tatao ra dhu be'a.<bt>The two of them have almost died in.order to save me. But it's not just me myself who gives thanks to the two of them. Cuz (elaboration) non Yahudi people who have become Christians from all the congregations all over the place, also are giving thanks because of their good deeds/behaviour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tón heautóon trákheelon hypétheekan: they put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">tón heautóon trákheelon hypétheekan: they put their life on the line for me, they stuck their necks out to save my life ethnóon: churches made up of Gentiles<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>NRSV: and who risked their necks for my life, to whom not only I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="5" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu pakaboko ho manèngi-mangaj'i ètu d'ara èmu Priskila dènge Akila.<bt>Give my greetings to all people who gather to worship (doublet) in Priskila and Akila's house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi angalai ja'a, Epenetus. Nèngu ka, dhèu uru tèka parcaya Kristus ètu propensi Asia.<bt>Give my greetings to my friend, Epenetus. He is the one who was the first person to believe in Kristus in Asia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet also the church in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet also the church in their house. Greet my beloved Epaenetus, who was the first convert in Asia for Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="6" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi ana hèni èdhi, Maria. Nèngu dhu sab'a ne'a boe j'èra ètu talora aae miu.<bt>Give my greetings to our-inc sister Maria. She has worked (idiom=extremely hard) in the midst of you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Mary, who has worked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Mary, who has worked very hard among you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Andronikus dènge ana hèni èdhi, Yunia.<bt>Give my greetings to Andronikus and sister Yunia.</bt><note reference="16:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani dhu be'a risi, aa dhu uru tèka, suri peka na, <span class="Italic">Yunia</span> (ngara dhèu bhèni). Abhu cahag'e kahèi dhu suri, peka na, <span class="Italic">Yulia</span> (ngara dhèu bhèni). Karèi nèti abad ka-13, abhu cahag'e hari dhu suri, peka na, <span class="Italic">Yunias</span> (ngara dhèu mone). Dhèu heka-dhèu heka Kristen, karèi nèti uru-uru, pangee na, a'a Andronikus dènge susi Yunia ne, dhèu èmu-kamali dhu sab'a hia Ama Lamatua, nuka sèmi a'a Akila dènge susi Priskila.<bt>The best and oldest Yunani language Bibles write, saying, <span class="Italic">Yunia</span> (a woman's name). There are some others which write, saying, <span class="Italic">Yulia</span>(a woman's name). Beginning from the 13th century, there were some others who wrote, saying, <span class="Italic">Yunias</span>(a man's name). Christian leaders/elders from long ago considered older brother Andronikus and older sister Yunia to be husband-wife who worked for God, like older brother Akila and older sister Priskila.</bt></note>Dua ra dhèu Yahudi, sama sèmi ja'a kahèi. Dua ra parcaya uuru Kristus nèti ja'a. Uru èèna, rèngu sama-sama dènge ja'a ètu d'ara bèdho. Dua ra j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Lamatua, aa dhèu ae tadhe si.<bt>Thetwo of them are Yahudi people, just like me. The two of them had already believed in Kristus before me. Long ago, they were in jail together with me. The two of them also became God2's commissioned.ones (apostles), and many people know/recognize them. [EXEG: Morris, NRSV, NLT support feminine Junia [common name] (Moo says unanimous before 13th century, supported by recent scholarship). NIV, CEV, TB support masculine Junias -said to be contracted form of Junianus (13th cent mss onwards), but no attestation of such a contraction outside this verse. Some discussion in CBE about a later change to the text that didn't support assumptions/ biases of the time.] [EXEG: Gk is ambiguous here, so it could be /sama-sama deng beta/ “together with me” OR /sama ke beta/ “like me”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sungeneis: 1) kinsman, relatives, person who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">sungeneis: 1) kinsman, relatives, person who belongs to the same extended family or clan, 2) fellow countryman (Morris, SSA, LN argues for #2, also TB2, HCE; but NIV, NRSV, NLT, CEV take #1 en tóis apostólois: either "they are well known by all the apostles, or even more likely, "they are apostles, and everybody knows them" or "they are important apostles"<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>NRSV: Greet Andronicus and Junia, my relatives who were in prison with me; they are prominent among the apostles, and they were in Christ before I was.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Ampliatus. Ja'a sue ne, lula nèngu dhu pa'èki dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Give my greetings to Ampliatus. I love him, because he is bound/linked with Yesus Kristus, our Head/Leader.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="9" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Urbanus. Nèngu kahèi pakako sasab'a Kristus sama-sama dènge èdhi.<bt>Give my greetings to Urbanus. He also carries out Kristus' work together with us-exc.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Stakis, dhu ja'a sue.<bt>Give my greetings to elder.brother Stakis, whom I love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Urbanus, our co-worker in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Urbanus, our co-worker in Christ, and my beloved Stachys.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="10" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Apeles. Masi ka nèngu lèke dadugu-rariu, te ngaa na segi ka nare li'u, lula lèka èra Kristus.<bt>Give my greetings to Apeles. Even though he was tested/tampted (doublet), nevertheless he victoried and got.through (came out the other end in one piece), because he believes firmly in Kristus. [EXEG: Gk /dokimon/ (LN) “pertaining to being genuine on the basis of testing”; MESSAGE picks this up with “a tried and true veteran”; HCE also reflects this with “da tings dat wen happen to him, dass jalike one test fo make proof dat he stay tight wit Jesus fo real kine.” I think English “approved” used to have this meaning about the time the KJV was done (or before) but it no longer means what the Gk word here does. Morris says “This man was tested and approved. We have no way of knowing what test he had undergone, but he was a man of tested excellence and Paul approves of him accordingly.” Moo says “Paul honors him by saying that he is “approved” in Christ. By this Paul might mean that he had proved himself in a difficult test of faith…”. SSA says “The word dokimov means “approved (by test)” (BAGD, p. 203.1). It entails three separate events: (1) being tested by trials of some kind, (2) successfully enduring those trials, and (3) being approved by God as a result.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sai1 = jump out ; sai2"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">sai1 = jump out ; sai2 = belah, sayat (slice into strips)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o mi a'ari aa'i-aa'i nèti Aristobulus.<bt>Give my greetings to all of Aristobulus' family.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimon: genuine, sincere, approved NRSV: Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">dokimon: genuine, sincere, approved NRSV: Greet Apelles, who is approved in Christ. Greet those who belong to the family of Aristobulus.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="11" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi a'a Herodion. Nèngu dhèu Yahudi kahèi, sama sèmi ja'a.<bt>Give my greetings to elder.brother Herodion. He is a Yahudi person, just like me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi isi èmu Narkisus dhu parcaya Kristus.<bt>Give my greetings to all of Narkisus's household that believe in Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet my relative Herodion. Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet my relative Herodion. Greet those in the Lord who belong to the family of Narcissus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="12" />Hia lii maho'o mi ana hèni èdhi, Trifena dènge Trifosa. Rèngu pakako kahèi sasab'a nèti Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Give my greetings to our-inc sisters, Trifena and Trifosa. They also carry out the work of our Head, Yesus Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o mi angalai ja'a, ana hèni èdhi, Persis. Te nèngu kahèi sab'a bia hia Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus.<bt>Give my greetings to my friend, our-inc sister Persis. Cuz (elaboration) she also works heavy (=very hard) for our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet those workers in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet those workers in the Lord, Tryphaena and Tryphosa. Greet the beloved Persis, who has worked hard in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="13" />Hia lii maho'o mi Rufus. Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus ka dhu hag'e nare ne.<bt>Give my greetings to Rufus. Our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus is the one who chose him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Hia lii maho'o mi ina na kahèi. Te nèngu ne, nuka sèmi ina d'èlu ja'a.<bt>Give my greetings to his mother also. Cuz (elaboration) she is like my own mother.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eklektòn: chosen, choice, outstanding NRSV: Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">eklektòn: chosen, choice, outstanding NRSV: Greet Rufus, chosen in the Lord; and greet his mother-a mother to me also.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 15:21</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="14" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Asinkritus, Flegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas dènge a'ari aa'i-aa'i dhu pea dènge rèngu.<bt>Give my greetings to Asinkritus, Flegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and all the siblings who stay with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers and sisters who are with them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="15" />Hia lii maho'o ja'a mi Filologus, ana hèni èdhi, Yulia, Olimpas, Nereus dènge ana hèni na, dènge dhèu-dhèu sarani aa'i dhu sama-sama dènge rèngu.<bt>Give my greetings to Filologus, our-inc sister Yulia, Olimpas, Nereus and his sister, and all the various Christians who are together with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Philologus, Julia, Nereus and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Philologus, Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ladhe miu pakaboko, na, mi pa'uu èci dènge èci, dhu pantas mi dhèu parcaya. Juma'at Kristus aa'i-aa'i ètu se'e, hia lii maho'o mi miu kahèi.<bt>If/When you gather together, na, reciprocally kiss each other, as is appropriate for believers. All of Kristus' congregations here also send greetings to you. [SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phileémati hagíooi: an appropriate, warm, Christian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">phileémati hagíooi: an appropriate, warm, Christian greeting, not a sexual advance. NRSV: Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet you.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 16:20, 1 Tesalonika 5:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii pasanèd'e nèti Paulus<bt>Reminders/advice from Paulus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a manèngi sèna ka miu mage-mage! J'aga paie-iie, te abhu dhèu dhu tao miu mae-manyèla, aa dhu neo sii pabèbhe miu. Ngaa dhu rèngu peka dènge miu sèra, palab'a dènge ngaa dhu ji'i aj'a-nori le miu. De baku pa'angalai dènge dhèu sèmi sèra!<bt>Siblings! I request that you-pl be careful! Guard carefully, cuz (elaboration) there are people who make you divided (into groups/factions) (doublet), who want to trick/ensnare you making you fall. What they are telling you, is in opposition to what we-exc have taught (doublet) you. So (consequently), don't be mutual friends with people like them! [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful to phrase this last sentence so that it is not directly at odds with a number of commands of Jesus, and of Paul himself (e.g. Gal. 6, Rom ). What we are aiming for is something that allows ostracism, discipline, reconciliation and restoration, without being influenced and corrupted in the process. KM actually achieves this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palab'a = berlawanan, bertangtangan ; pasala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">palab'a = berlawanan, bertangtangan ; pasala = different from, in another direction</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dichostasias: divisions, discord, division into opposing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">dichostasias: divisions, discord, division into opposing groups, skandala: obstacle, trap, offense<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>NRSV: I urge you, brothers and sisters, to keep an eye on those who cause dissensions and offenses, in opposition to the teaching that you have learned; avoid them.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dhèu sèra sab'a boe hia Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Rèngu sèra dhoka sab'a ho pa'oto ngi'u rèngu unu ra. Dhèu sèra dhoka hèb'a mènyi mi dhèu dhu dhae re'a mèka mia ka dhu be'a, aa mia ka dhu karehe. Rèngu hèb'a mènyi ho kapod'e-kabèli dhèu.<bt>Those people don't work for our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus. They only work so that they can get benefit for themselves. They oily mouth (speak slippery-flatteringly to be deceptive) with people who do not yet understand which (of options) is good and which is evil. They oily mouth to deceive (doublet) people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèb'a mènyi = flatter"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">hèb'a mènyi = flatter</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akákoon: inexperienced as far as evil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">akákoon: inexperienced as far as evil is concerned, innocent-minded NRSV: For such people do not serve our Lord Christ, but their own appetites, and by smooth talk and flattery they deceive the hearts of the simple-minded.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu tadèngi le, na, miu loe boe madhutu dad'èi Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka d'ara ja'a karej'e titu kèna lula miu. Dad'èi ja'a ka, ladhe miu d'èlu-mèu ètu j'ara-j'ara be'a, aa baku pakihu kee dènge j'ara-j'ara karehe.<bt>All people have heard that, you do not cease to follow God2's will. That's why I am sooo happy because of you. My desire is that you become knowledgeable about good things, and don't mix/get involved with evil things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakihu kee = campur aduk (lit."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">pakihu kee = campur aduk (lit. campur manis) = pab'ali ; CHECK ALL d'èlu-mèu &gt; d'èlu-mèu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akeraíous: not mixed up in what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">akeraíous: not mixed up in what is evil NRSV: For while your obedience is known to all, so that I rejoice over you, I want you to be wise in what is good and guileless in what is evil.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ama Lamatua ka dhu bisa hia èdhi mamuri dame dènge mera-milu. Nèngu ka dhu èèna na palaho koasa nèti dhèu aae nidhu, aa pad'elo, peka na, miu ka dhu segi. Se'e se nèbhu heka j'aj'i. Ja'a sabaj'a, manèngi sèna ka Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi dedha miu.<bt>God is the one who can enable us to live safely (external), and peacefully (relationally). He is the one who later will destroy the evil.spirit's king's power, and show that, you are the ones who win. These things are not much longer (=soon). I pray requesting that our Head/Leader Yesus Kristus show his good insides (grace/ kindness/ favour) to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaan: da Devil hypò toùs pódas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">Satanaan: da Devil hypò toùs pódas hymóon: under your feet, make him subject to you<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>NRSV: The God of peace will shortly crush Satan under your feet. The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="21" />Ari èdhi, Timotius, dhu sab'a sama-sama dènge ja'a, hia lii maho'o mi miu kahèi.<bt>Our-inc younger.sibling Timotius, who works together with me, is sending greetinigs to you too.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lukius, Yason, dènge Sosipater, hia lii maho'o kahèi. Rèngu se dhèu Yahudi, èci èèna ka dènge ja'a.<bt>Lukius, Yason, and Sosipater also send greetings. They are Yahudi people just like me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Timothy, my co-worker, greets you;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Timothy, my co-worker, greets you; so do Lucius and Jason and Sosipater, my relatives [/fellow countrymen--see above].</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 16:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="22" />(Ja'a ne, Tertius, ka dhu suri sasuri ne'e madhutu ngaa dhu Paulus pua ja'a suri. Lii maho'o nèti ja'a, te ja'a ne dhèu unu Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus kahèi.)<bt>(I, Tertius, am the one who is writing this letter according to what Paulus orders me to write. Sweet greetings from me also, cuz (elaboration) I am also our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus' person.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I Tertius, the writer of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: I Tertius, the writer of this letter, greet you in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="23" />Ja'a, Paulus, manubha ètu èmu Gayus. Dhèu sarani aa'i-aa'i tema pakaboko ètu èmu na ho manèngi-mangaj'i. Nèngu hia lii maho'o kahèi.<bt>I, Paulus, stay.temporarily in Gayus' house. All the Christians here usually gather to worship (doublet) in his house. He also sends greetings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Erastus, dhu j'aj'i bendahara kota, dènge a'ari èdhi Kuartus, hia miu lii maho'o kahèi.<bt>Erastus, who is the city treasurer (loan), and our sibling Kuartus, also are sending greetings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Gaius, who is host to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Gaius, who is host to me and to the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the city treasurer, and our brother Quartus, greet you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 19:29, 1 Korintus 1:14, 2 Timotius 4:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />[Ja'a manèngi, sèna ka Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi miu aa'i-aa'i mi! Lèke tare'a!]<bt>[I request that our Head/Leader, Yesus Kristus, show His good insides (grace/kindness/generosity) to all of you. That's all!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: [The grace of our Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: [The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you. Amen.]</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:24" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab lii Yunani dhu uru tèka aa dhu be'a risi, dènge boe ayat 24 ne.<bt>The oldest and best Yunani language Bibles don't have this verse 24 here.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua ne, kapai titu kèna!<bt>God is great/amazing/incredible!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Koa-kio mi Ama Lamatua! Te Nèngu ka dhu unu koasa, sèna ka tao miu j'aj'i èra. Lii Lolo Be'a Na peka sèmi èèna ka, aa ja'a aj'a-nori dhèu sèmi èèna kahèi, ropa ja'a peka dènge rèngu lula-nèti Yesus Kristus. Lamatua ka dhu bhoke paled'a hia mi èdhi j'ara aa'i-aa'i lula-nèti Kristus, dhu uru-uru sèra dhèu dhae re'a mèka, lula dhu pahuni era.<bt>Praise God! Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who has the power/authority to make you become strong. His Good News says that, and I also teach (doublet) people like that, when I explain to them about Yesus Kristus. God2 is the one who has revealed clearly to us-inc all matters concerning Kristus, which people long ago didn't yet know about, because they were still secret. [DISCOURSE: First clause is genre driven to signal that this section is a doxology.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now to God who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now to God who is able to strengthen you according to my gospel and the proclamation of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery that was kept secret for long ages</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te ngaa j'ara-j'ara dhu uru sèra dhèu rèti lii padhai Lamatua suri ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, limuri ne mèu aadha-aadha le. Ama Lamatua dhu madhe nèdhi boe, Nèngu ka ator sèna ka dhèu nèti suku aa'i-aa'i, re'a mèu madha j'ara dhu pahuni uru sèra. Dènge j'ara ne'e, dhèu sèra bisa parcaya Ne, aa tao madhutu dad'èi Na.<bt>But matters/issues which God2's *prophets (spokepeople) have written about in the Holy Writings, are now very clear. (The) God who never dies, He is the one who arranged for people from all ethnic groups to be able to know matters which were formerly hidden. In that way, they can believe in Him, and do according to His will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèu aadha-aadha = very clear (\lf"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z">mèu aadha-aadha = very clear (\lf Max (relating to understanding) ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: but is now disclosed, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: but is now disclosed, and through the prophetic writings is made known to all the Gentiles, according to the command of the eternal God, to bring about the obedience of faith-</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Dhodhoka Nèngu mesa-mesa Na di, Ama Lamatua. Dhodhoka Nèngu mesa-mesa Na, dhu ne'a aa'i mèu-mèu j'ara. Ja'a d'èi j'oka padedha-dedha Ne, lula tatao Yesus Kristus! Lèke tare'a!<bt>Only He alone is God. Only He alone is the one who understands all things. I like to lift/exalt Him on high, because of Yesus Kristus' deeds. That's true!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: to the only wise God,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:48:27Z" status="Information">NRSV: to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever! Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sasuri ja'a d'ai sange ne'e ka,<bt>My letter just reaches this point,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saloom,<bt>Saloom,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>